column2: Curse our lack of shot! If only we had more.
Keep the line straight! No weak points!
Get onto the wall and kill the first bastard you see!
By Camulus! They have no one left after this lot! Take them off the field today and we will have destroyed their military might! So spare no one. Run them through and seize this victory!
Come on! I'm not afraid! Face me!
When the might of the Britons faces off against the might of Egypt there can be only one result. Death to the Easterners! Hit them hard and seek out their leader. They cannot fight without him!
Ankou walks with us today! The enemy over there!
Gods above! They are creditable shots, at least!
With respect, sir, I think you are allowed to duck.
Don't let the others see you like this!
Watch out! Arrows and stones do not care about courage!
Black magic against us. The druids shall hear of this.
There they are, a herd of gazelles blind to the approaching lion. Attack! Attack them now!
I am a reaper of souls.
What do they want\? Are they coming to fight\?
I am your champion, my lord!
My words are yours to direct.
We stand here, the last defenders of our people. When we are gone, nothing stands between our homes and the tender mercy of the enemy! We have no choice then: we fight!
It is an honour to serve you.

We are the last army, men. If death and defeat are to be our fates, so be it! The gods have settled that, but we shall make such a show of glory that, in a thousand years, men will talk of it! Make ready!
We are the last of us, but that does not mean we are beaten yet! Let the enemy come in their arrogance! Let them have their mock glory! We are beaten only when I say that we are beaten!

Until today, the gods have frowned upon our efforts, for we are the last army of our people! It falls to us to stand bravely and triumph, or see all that we treasure cast into darkness. I say: we fight!
We are the last army, men. After us, our people have no further shield against the world and all their enemies. We cannot, will not, fail them, or shame our gods! Make ready!
I will speak in honesty. There have been mistakes in this war. That is why we are the last army. But today, there will be glory! Put aside the past, and fight for the future! Make ready!

Stand to, lads, stand to! This is the last struggle for many of us, but we will do our utmost here to make sure it is not the last moment of our people! We must be their shields, their protectors! The gods be with us!
I will not lie to you. We are the last hope of our people. If we fail here, even the gods will forget us. Our wives and children will be slaves. So, we must have victory!
He always was a bright one!
Hold, you dogs! Put these fires out!
Gods help me! I will not!

Their numbers will count less than our courage. Let Ba'al drive any doubt or fear from your hearts for, in his name, we can triumph this day! There is no greater gift that we can offer him than victory over our foes!
Do you think me a fool\?
Silence is the door of consent.
The Goddess will show them the right path.
You cannot ask me to do this!
Have you taken leave of your senses\?
You expect me to do that!\?
The dog that barks seldom bites.
I will make them understand our ways.
Let us pray they have a blackened soul.
For Rome I would journey to the ends of the Earth!
For Rome I would journey to the ends of the Earth!
Steady, steady. Just a few noisy idiots!
Hmmm! The enemy are about some sneaky business!
I do not like all this strategy. It is not... honest.
May the gods be with you, men!
I wonder how the wife is\?
I hope your insides smell better than your outsides!
Draw your blades! This is not over.
Let them come and taste our iron!
Only cowards will stay and die in this thing! Now, get ready!
They seem damned hostile today, the buggers!
I'm bored. Will anything ever hap-arrrghghg!
A merry meeting, how can I help\?
I am the destroyer of men!
I am a sage of the forest.
Gods of my fathers! Give us victory today. I do not ask for more men, only the courage to stand and fight as you would wish! Now, men, say your own prayers and then make ready!
Well met, what do you wish of me\?
Honoured forefathers! Give me the strength and wit to command this army in our hour of peril! I have brave men beneath my hand, and I would see them victorious today! Give them your strength!
Fire! Have those barbarian curs no honour\?
I'm hit! By Ankou, I'm hit!
What would you have of me\?
I am the knife in the dark.
I will introduce them to my staff…
A well placed threat has great power.
The Gods will bring them to us.
That head would look better on my wall…
I will give them sweet words and hard choices.
Foul, animal, godless cunning! That is what we face!
To me! To me! Form up!
I would travel the world for Parthia.
I would travel the world for Parthia.
Egypt asks much of it's servants.
The gods guide my foot steps.
The gods guide my foot steps.
The gods guide my foot steps.
Egypt asks much of it's servants.
Egypt asks much of it's servants.
Egypt asks much of it's servants.
I need a dump. Cover for me.
Those boots have seen better days.
By the gods, you look good enough to eat!
The gods guide my foot steps.
We'll have to engage them hand to hand… Bring us closer!

Carthaginians! Sons of whores and and temple sluts, the lot of them! Do not be afraid, men, they lack courage thanks to their low breeding! I promise you we will break them! Hold the line and we will be victorious!

Let us drive these merchants and nomads into the seas and deserts from whence they came! Let us cast them out! Find your courage, men! We are not bought lackeys, but soldiers, and we will be victorious!
Watch your mouth, or I'll nail it shut!
If I come through this, I will sacrifice to Bellona!

Long has Carthage held power to her bosom. Today we break that power, and show it not to be absolute! Come, men! Come, let us drive back these traders and merchants, and claim the riches of these city folk!

Most of that army are mercenaries or levies, but I have heard Carthaginians have some honour. If we face them, be prepared for a hard fight! They will not yield easily! We will have to cut them down, for they may not run.
Hold them! Cut down these dogs!
One more step and we will crush them.
It's SUPPOSED TO HURT, you idiot!
I am not moving from this spot, not for any-AARGGHGH!
The banner, man, keep it up!
What does Pharaoh wish of me\?
May the blessings of Isis be upon you.
Time for us to earn our spoils, boy.
A merry meeting, how can I help\?
Today we face a loathsome thing: a Seleucid army. I cannot bring myself to speak of their vile ways towards captives. Offer them no mercy. Be cruel and resolute. We must win today!
I am the destroyer of men!
I am a sage of the forest.

There is a strain of foaming madness in the army yonder! It is the insanity of overwheening arrogance, of cruelty, and of bad blood! A Seleucid army infects that ground it stands upon. It is our duty to exterminate them!
Well met, what do you wish of me\?

They are a fine looking bunch, our Seleucid foes! Their looks are the best thing about them for they are, to a man, given over the most perverse and debased vices imaginable! We cleanse the world by killing them!
The Gods would not allow it.
That is beyond even my considerable talents.
Where the bloody hell did that come from\?
Don't jest, boy! Pray we're not in Ran's net this day.
How can I be of assistance\?
Don't worry, lad, you're safe… You're nicely damp with that piss.
It's like fishing… But with bigger nets!
What would you have of me\?
I am the knife in the dark.
What do you wish of me\?
I will pour honey into their souls.
I will introduce them to my staff…
The Gods will bring them to us.
That head would look better on my wall…
The Goddess gifted me with sweet words.
Praise Mithra! They're on the run!
Well, if it's gone, it's gone. We fight without artillery!
Drowning for my people is not what I had hoped to do!
Put your backs into it, you men!
Put your backs into it, you men!
Hard on the oars you men!
Hard on the oars you men!
All-Father be praised, excitement at last!
Sword and shield to my people!
Sir, is the twitching thing normal, sir\?
Everyone on this ship, hear me! No quarter to the enemy!
Sword and shield to my people!
All-Father be praised, excitement at last!
Sword and shield to my people!
All-Father be praised, excitement at last!
All-Father be praised, excitement at last!
Sword and shield to my people!
What now\? Want us to throw curses at them\?
I'd throw you at them if it would hurt!
Next, lad, we earn our pay!
I will have discipline! Or I will use the rod!
I say, all this shooting is ruining my day!
Duck you foo-- Ah, too late!
She's not here, so shut it!
How may I be of assistance\?
I am a reaper of souls.
I am a priestess of the old ways.
And find our parts, should they be scattered.
This is the worst part… Fighting is easy after this.
Well met, what do you wish of me\?
I am your champion, my lord!
My words are yours to direct.
The Goddess blesses you. How can I help\?
It is an honour to serve you.
The enemies of Carthage must die.
The enemies of Carthage must die.
The enemies of Carthage must die.
The enemies of Carthage must die.
All-Father be praised! How can I help\?
All-Father be praised! How can I help\?
Death to the enemies of Carthage.
Death to the enemies of Carthage.
Death to the enemies of Carthage.
Death to the enemies of Carthage.
The way appears to be blocked.
Someone seeks to bar my passage.
That's it! Light the way for us, lad!
I fear they'd rather watch us burn first, sir.
Cowards! Why don't they face us\?
What would you have of me\?
Gods help me! I will not!
Everyone has dark secrets they wish to hide.
I will make them an offer they can't refuse.
Do you think me a fool\?
Silence is the door of consent.
You cannot ask me to do this!
Have you taken leave of your senses\?
You expect me to do that!\?
The dog that barks seldom bites.
Let us pray they have a blackened soul.
A little gold buys many friends.
Never mind, man. We are the gods' playthings, that's all!
QUIET! Listen to orders, curse your souls!
I don't understand what's going on…
Why didn't I stay in camp\?
Fellow Gauls! Some of you have fought many battles. You have the scars to prove it. But today is the most important fight of your lives. Today we defend our capital. Today we win or die!
True, it was fun to watch
Well, that's a pity. I liked the way our artillery could kill them!
By Teutates! I'm sweating like a bear.
Then make sure you fight like one, boy!
All hands! Look! The wind lifts our banners, and our spirits!
Ares and Artemis have been kind today! This will be a hunt rather than a battle! But though we are braver than our foes, remember that a cornered rat can still bite! Now, await your orders!

Sons of Egypt, hear me, victory will be ours. In the name of Pharaoh, Who shelters and feeds us all, we will vanquish that rabble! All I ask is that you fight, and give no ground to these wretched whelps!

Lighten your hearts! Cast aside fear and doubt lest the gods judge you wanting! Death should not trouble us today: we have the advantage! And we will win a great victory in blessed Pharaoh's mighty name.
That should have dampened their spirits at least.
I'll get the men ready to attack.
Fill their mouths with the taste of their own blood.
That man! Cracked leathers! Put yourself on report!
Umm. Over there, in camp. I'll just go get it…
Be still, man! Do you want to be killed\?
Battle\? Battle\? This is murder, not battle!
Look out! Duck! Duck, man, duck!
How may I be of assistance\?
By the gods, they're approaching. I'm scared.
Well, looks like they've taken the bait. At the ready men!
I am a priestess of the old ways.
Don't worry, boy. We'll look after you.
Well met, what do you wish of me\?

By Taranis, we have them cornered now! Take these walls and then take this settlement! They will have prepared some fun for you inside! Yes, men! Enjoy yourselves today! Ravage and pillage this place!
The Goddess blesses you. How can I help\?
The way appears to be blocked.
Pikes at the ready! Form phalanx!
Someone seeks to bar my passage.
Stop shouting and put him out!
Who wants to see an outlanders head\?!
The gods love blood and war!
Cowards way of fighting, using fire.
What would you have of me\?
Gather, I have tales of blood and glory to tell!
Everyone has dark secrets they wish to hide.
I will make them an offer they can't refuse.
Who's for a song\? A rude one about Dionysus\?
A little gold buys many friends.
Never mind, man. We are the gods' playthings, that all!
QUIET! Listen to orders, curse your souls!
I don't understand what's going on…
Why didn't I stay in camp\?
We fight for you, my lord!
True, it was fun to watch
Curse them! That was a vital part of our general's plans!
Well, that's a pity. I liked the way our artillery could kill them!
Ares! I beg a longer life, so that I can slay many enemies!

My courage was forged in the fire of war, some say by Haephestus himself. I do not claim such an honour, as it is honour enough to lead you in war. I do claim, though, that I desire victory above all else! To arms!
Noble sons of Ares, you are the beacons of glory for our people! When you march, men and women swoon for very different reasons! Now, prove your mettle! Conquer and gain your victory!
It is an honour to serve Rome!
All-Father be praised, excitement at last!
Sword and shield to my people!
All hands! Look to your duties!
Sword and shield to my people!
All-Father be praised, excitement at last!
Sword and shield to my people!
All-Father be praised, excitement at last!
All-Father be praised, excitement at last!
Sword and shield to my people!
That's everything! We're out of shot.
I do not plan to live if we do not win…
Pray, lad. Pray we hold! The Gods don't listen to me…
I'll put in a good word for us both!
Be brave! We're only facing a few girls today!
Of course it hurts, you idiot!
Arrrchhh. My blood. But I will not end like this!
Girls with bloody big choppers, mind…
What does Pharaoh wish of me\?

I have heard the Seleucid rulers style themselves the heirs of Alexander". Gods above! What foolish presumption! I imagine noble Alexander's ghost styles the mighty Seleucids as "his horse's dung"! Make ready!"
Come on, then. Come to daddy…
May the blessings of Isis be upon you.

I see that our Seleucid enemies are busy getting themselves in order. Ha! If they wanted to bring order to their ranks, they should kill their general, for he is a perfumed morons, followed by morons! Very well, let's begin…

I do not care for Seleucid armies. They are full of tricksters, perfumed fops, eastern dandies, brigands, bandits and thieves! And that's just the women! Ha! Never mind, they'll all be running or dead soon. Let's to it!
I do not like these Seleucid soldiers. Even their banners annoy me as being insolent! We must, and will, beat them then enjoy plundering their baggage train. Save me a skin of good wine! Ha!

Do not make the mistake of respecting those Seleucid soldiers! They are not your equals! Their degrading, infamous and squalid ways make them less than beetles beneath your feet! Prepare to kill them all!
The Gods would not allow it.
This way is closed to me.
Never leave your purse where a Seleucid can see it, men! These people would suck gold coins out of a camel's arse if that is where you kept your money! They need to be killed! Let's to it!
That is beyond even my considerable talents.
The Seleucids call themselves the heirs of Alexander! Bah! They are less than the dung of Alexander, less than the dung of Alexander's horse! They are… they are… soon to be dead by our hands!
Roll him in the dirt! Now!
How can I be of assistance\?
Yeah. Good times. Better than this.
Remember that fire we started\? Spread to the tower\?
What do you wish of me\?
I will make them doubt their leaders.
I will offer them my council…
I will pour honey into their souls.
I shall make a few suggestions…
How dare they stand before me!
I will show them a better way.
Trust in one's superiors is vital…
Block my path\? Do they know who I am!
Blocked\? Do they know who I am!\?
How dare they seek to delay me!
Their men will doubt their authority.
I am unable to travel this road.
I will bend them to our purposes…
The Goddess gifted me with sweet words.
There are few who can resist my words.
We stand outside the walls of Rome! Within, the Romans are now begging their gods for help! They are convincing themselves of their bravery. Both are a waste of time! Forwards, soldiers!
Within those walls cower the old men of the Senate, their floozies, and the frightened gods of Rome. All fear our coming! When we have entered, we will make the city a slaughterhouse! Make ready!
Our forefathers dreamed of glory such as we are about to gain! We stand outside once-proud Rome! Soon we will assault and sack the city! Then, we shall know glory! And we'll drink ourselves stupid!
We stand before Rome, a city humbled by our very presence! Now, we must fight our way inside and make humility the least of Rome's problems! Leave nothing! Fight hard! And make these Romans suffer!

By Ares and Nike, this will be a glorious day! We stand before the gates of Rome and, before tomorrow's dawn breaks, the city will be ours! When it is, men, take what or who you will! Now, stand ready!
Well, if it's gone, it's gone. We fight without artillery!
Draw swords, men. And pray that Ares favours us!
Ares be praised! Here comes honour aplenty!
I do not want to draw the sword in anger, but by Ares, once it is drawn I will fight! I expect nothing less of you, brave soldiers! The gods, too, look on in keen expectation! Let us show them glory!
It is an honour to serve!
Look to your own weapons, be ready to fight!
Before we ran out of ammunition\?
All the gods curse them! Why haven't they died\?
Dry land, sir. The druids' sacrifice worked!
Defeat\? Better to be beneath the waves than carry this shame.

These insolent blue idiots will know the divine justice of noble Pharaoh before the day is done! They will have bitter defeat at our hands! We shall drive them back to the mist-shrounded island they call home! To arms!
Those bastards are altogether too keen on shooting at us, I think.
I told you that was sharp, you twat!
I will have order! Keep your spacing!
Everyone's scared! The trick is not to show it!
The boars will feast upon their flesh…
The boars will feast upon their flesh…
The boars will feast upon their flesh…
Morrigan, we give their soul to you.
Morrigan, we give their soul to you.
Morrigan, we give their soul to you.
How long are we going to wait\? We can hit them from here!
Hold fast, men! Get ready to spill their blood.
This way is closed to me.
Put him out of his misery!
The gods love blood and war!
Tales of victory gladden the heart!
A man without a weapon is nothing!
We were born to fight, ask your mothers!
I will make them doubt their leaders.
I will offer them my council…
I shall make a few suggestions…
We’re going to be surrounded at this rate!
How dare they stand before me!
I will show them a better way.
A well placed threat has great power.
Oi! Less of the prattle! Form up!
Block my path\? Do they know who I am!
Trust in one's superiors is vital…
They're trying to hit our flank.
Blocked\? Do they know who I am!\?
How dare they seek to delay me!
I will give them sweet words and hard choices.
I am unable to travel this road.
Their men will doubt their authority.
I will bend them to our purposes…
There are few who can resist my words.
Are we having a staring contest, or a fight\?
Enemies\? Bah! Townsmen with a nasty temper!
Who's for a drink\? There's time!
Wasps are really awesome at staring contests.
Not in my unit there isn't!
To me! To me! Form up!
Forget them! Tyr and his spear shall clear our way!
Check your weapons! And then check again!
This bloody helmet's given me a blister!
Good work, men! That's one less thing to worry the admiral!
Right, my lucky lads! Give them a taste of iron!
Stand to! Prepare! Remember your training!
I don't like the look of 'em!
No, boy! We're the hard cases here!
It is an honour to serve!
Waves will drown you. Wind overturn you. Men only kill you.
Our shots have done their work… Make ready to fight!
I've never seen anything like it.
Unless you stand fast you never will again!
Stop blubbing, man! Your mum has more guts than you!
Fortune does not favour us... If we still can, make for port.
In the name of Camalus, come back here and fight!
Senior men! I think, it's time to--AAARRRGGGHHH!
Sir! Get yourself to a surgeon, sir!
Curse them ten thousand times! That was my best cloak!
Sir, NOW they're trying to kill us!
Anyone! Please! Bind my eyes and point me at the foe!
Sir, don't let the men see any weakness!
My honour is my oath to serve!
I wish you good luck, my brothers!
Ancestors! Protect me now, if you don't mind…

Children of Tyr! Draw your weapons and be ready to fight! Hack your way through this rancid enemy with all the fire of Garm burning in your hearts! They will fall and they will be crushed in our wake!
By Tyr, I look upon you all and feel the pride of a father. I hold you all as family and would lay down my life for you if necessary. Let us fight as one and kill this unholy rabble!
Honourable sons of Tyr! I am happy to say we go to battle! I have chosen to the fight to this enemy and force them to answer our swords and spears. Make ready!
Freya warms the bed for the dead tonight! She will wash your wounds and rouse your flesh with her fine breasts. The rest of us will have to content ourselves with victory and wine!

By Garm's fangs, this enemy looks good enough to eat! I am ravenous for death and slaughter! They say we are savages. I fear they will meet a savage fate today! I cannot wait to see their blood on my sword!
What does he think I'm doing\?
The sword should never be sheathed.
A man without a weapon is like a camel with 3 legs!
No! No! I have yet to do great things…
The wise are always ready for war.
Watch our flank! We must not let them overwhelm our ranks.
Dirty bastards! They're coming from over there.
The Goddess will show them the right path.
I will make them understand our ways.
Check your weapons! And then check again!
Anyway, I heard this story that…
Nonsense! No leader of ours would do that with a goat!
Can you shut up about dying for a bit\?
Ancestors! I will join you soon!
Steady, steady. Just a few noisy idiots!
Hmmm! The enemy are about some sneaky business!
Not quite all the jar, sir!
Not in my unit there isn't!
I'm not a lord. Sir" will do."
We fight for you, my lord!
O, gods! Grant me quiet! How much did I have last night\?
Who's for a drink\? There's time!

Britons! I can hear the enemy praying to their god Tanit! They are scared! They have never seen the likes of you ugly bastards! They look to their gods to protect them for they know their shields will not!
Excellent work! Once again our enemies are frustrated!
Does that mean we've won\? Can we go home\?
Your village is missing an idiot, boy!
No, boy! We're the hard cases here!
Stand to! Prepare! Remember your training!
I don't like the look of 'em!
Right, my lucky lads! Give them a taste of iron!
I would travel the world for Parthia.
I would travel the world for Parthia.
I would travel the world for Parthia.
I would travel the world for Parthia.
It is an honour to serve Rome!
Egypt asks much of it's servants.
Stop hauling, you louts, and prepare to fight!
The gods guide my foot steps.
The gods guide my foot steps.
Egypt asks much of it's servants.
A dark day for us... Battle's done, lads, and we've lost.
Get them moving, if you please!
Order the file commanders to make ready their men.
See father! I told you I'd be a great man!
I will find them, my lord.
I am a daughter of the night!
Hold your fire, men. Wait until the order is given.
A man will see what he sees.
My skills blossom under your guidance.
Aim at the body! Make sure of the hit!
This is what you've trained for! Don't let your homeland down!
Bards far and wide know my name!
The Gods shower me with blessings.
The power of the Gods flows through me!
My skills have bloomed like the lotus!
This isn't going to end well…
By the gods, they're coming from the sides.
Seen it all before, boys. Let them come.
It might be standing now, later, not so much.
Destruction, aye, I'll see to it.
Shall we start getting the men ready, sir\?
Excitement, glory and money, lad, same as us!
Why did I leave my nice farm\?
Ami has struck! We are on fire!
Do you ever stop thinking about your stomach\?
Do not shame the gods today! Fight!
Kill them, and I'll buy you as many whores... as you can eat!
A nice cheese. And some wine. That's what I want.
Shall we start getting ready, sir\?
Poseidon be thanked! A fine day for a voyage!
At the ready, men! We are going to hit them hard!
Stand close to me and you'll be all right.
Thank you. This is my first time
Poseidon's big trident! Are they gutting fish over there\?
Had trouble finding it I expect.
Anyway, I told her to grab it and have a go.
I've heard the Romans bathe in ox's blood.
Where are you off to\? Stand your ground.
Right lads! If you get lost, take the nearest tavern and hold it against all comers!
All this way… All that… And for what\?
By the gods and waves! Have we come to this\? Defeat\?
It's not us I'm worried about!
I look for enemies worthy of my sword!
Everyone is scared! DON'T worry! FIGHT!
Remember warriors, our ancestors watch over us!
I will tend to the needs of our warriors.
Death in service of the tribe is honourable!
I was born in the darkness.
So they want a closer look, do they\?
Make ready! We'll show these curs how warriors fight!
No one can stand in my way.
The night has made me her own.
Patience. They're only just in range, lad.
With great patience comes great skill.
My skills are a gift to be treasured.
Why won't he let us fire yet\?
I am swifter than the wind.
I am swifter than the wind.
The wise warrior knows his training is never complete!
I am the fist of the Goddess!
A true champion always seeks improvement!
I'm the one your mother warned you about!
I have learnt much in your service.
I have the strength of ten men!
My sword sings with the cries of 100 dead men!
Skill and wisdom must be earnt.
My hard work has been rewarded.
We'll earn our brazen shields at this rate.
Fair point. She was a bloody old cow!
Leave the wife\? I left her mother. This is better.
One hand builds while the other destroys…
By the gods they're crafty bastards!
Oh, so that's their game, is it\?
Sabotage, a most excellent choice, my lord.
Mischief and mayhem, yes, my lord.
A nice cheese. And some wine. That's what I want.
Death is coming. For the lucky ones!
Shall we start getting ready, sir\?
Do you ever stop thinking about your stomach\?
Thanks. I feel so much better now.
By Mithra I hope she stays together!

My fellow gauls! Behind these walls are riches beyond your wildest dreams! Our enemy has been hording and it is all here! We shall dine tonight on the finest foods and drink the best mead. The city is ours!
Quite, sir. Good luck with that.
Shall we start getting the men ready, sir\?
Now is my hour of glory!
Look! The artillery! They got it!
And they've got this huge arena for fighting. Make a fortune you can.
I'm fed up with all this. I'm off.
What's happening now\? I can't see anything.
That's everything. It's hand to hand, or nothing now...
Has he gone a bit… odd\?
Ha! You cannot be serious! Garm's bollocks to you!
Why have you stopped shooting\? Did I say you could\? Did I\?
I do not think I am a tortoise, today.
What has happened to Roman honour\?
If we're lucky we won't have to swim home.
These seas are the homes of evil spirits! I have seen them!
Don't wave that sword around near me, you fool!
Remember warriors, our ancestors watch over us!
I will tend to the needs of our warriors.
Death in service of the tribe is honourable!
Roman brothels are said to be the best in the world! When we have raided this city and routed their army, I trust I shall see you all in one of them to find out! Let your lust guide your sword!
I was born in the darkness.

Rome! Romans! They love themselves and this city. Make sure you rout them and then plunder their homes and their temples. Burn it to the ground if need be. Rome shall not be Roman any more! It belongs to us now!
If they charge, hold them. Then push them back!
That's a pity. I think we needed that.
With great patience comes great skill.
Don’t waste your shot. Make them count.
My skills are a gift to be treasured.
They won't know what's hit them.
The wise warrior knows his training is never complete!
A true champion always seeks improvement!
I have learnt much in your service.
I have the strength of ten men!
Skill and wisdom must be earnt.
My hard work has been rewarded.
No... Those dogs have us like rats in a trap.
As our navy commands the seas, so we shall command these shores! The great Ba'al watches over us: for his glory, and Carthage, we will carve out a great victory here and bring our light to this land!

These Parthian peacocks will not trouble us long! Today we repay them for every insult laid against us and our people! We shall cry out the names we bear on our brazen shields, and put fear into their hearts! Who is with me\?
Can you feel it\? The ghosts here are troubled!
I wish my old mother was here.
By the gods I feel good today. We shall fight them with the respect they deserve, eh\? None whatsoever! Look at them. Pathetic. Who dares fall to these soft bastards\? Kill them all!

As I look at this proud army I am certain the day shall be ours! We fight for ourselves, to bathe in the blood of battle! We fight for each other, to protect and serve! We fight for our homeland, to crush and conquer!
Shut it. You're upsetting the lads!
So do I. Your cooking's rubbish!
I will stand here until ordered!
Breakfast, sir, might be your last chance!
Praise the gods, but that was well done, lads!
It's not rose blossom, that's for sure…
I do not think Poseidon approves of foreigners all over his waves.
What on earth is that SMELL\?
Why is there so much hate in the world\?
He said, what you do in life echoes in eternity.
Keep your hands to yourself, you dirty bastard.
That's it! All I've got left is sharp words.
Let us be honest, your wit isn't that sharp!

The strength of Carthage is bought with gold! What we face are merchants and mercenaries, all of them! If we hold today, if we defeat them, the gold in their purses will be your reward! Remember that! On to victory! To glory! To gold!

We face Dido's misbegotten spawn, the coin-counters of Carthage! Do not be fooled, for fine armour does not make fine warriors. We will defeat these pedlars, and strip the armour from their bodies! Make ready!
We shall break this rabble from Carthage! Break these whoreson merchants, and send them scurrying back to their counting houses. To arms, men! Let us put these cheap carpet salesmen to flight!
Make ready! Won't be long now!

Wealthy and fat: that is Carthage! We shall bring down this army and take their riches for ourselves. Their merchants have grown fat on their trade, and we shall cut open their ripe bellies to get at the meat! To arms!
Why the fallen face\? We're still here aren't we\?
Wondered when he'd get round to that…
I will tend to the needs of our warriors.
Honour those who protect our people!
Our warriors will want for nothing!
Bloody hell. They're coming over here.
This is where we teach them a lesson, boys.
Get ready, lad. And pray to any Gods that might favour you.
See father! I told you I'd be a great man!
Stand fast, men, stand fast! Faith and honour!
Bugger me sideways with a battering ram! They got it!
I will find them, my lord.
Don't waste our ammunition. Wait till they're closer, men.
A man will see what he sees.
Thank the gods! We don't have to put up any more crap coming this way!
This is it! In range! Prepare to fire!
Curse them! Can we win now\?
Praise be to Bata! We will strike them down today!
Bards far and wide know my name!
The Gods shower me with blessings.
The power of the Gods flows through me!
Strengthen our flank! We can still break them!
Aye! I could murder a bit of crackling!
By Poseidon's windy arse! How much longer\?
I wonder if the pigs are well…
Look out! There's a right bunch of flankers over there!
I will stand here until ordered!
I see nothing in front of us but putrid peasants and crusty old maids. I want them dead within the hour, do you hear! Show no mercy! Give no quarter! Death to all who stand in our way!

I praise the gods I command such an army. It is a privilege to fight with you today. We are brothers, one and all and we shall show the enemy the power of that brotherhood. So take up your arms and fight!

Here we go, lads! Now we make orphans of this lot's children, widows of their wives and their old hags of mothers shall cry a sea of tears! Come, show your strength and blast these bastards from this world!
Come, men! We go to take our place in history. Live or die, the gods watch us with pride and our ancestors sing our praises! Can you hear them, men! They sing of our glory! The glory of victory!
I guarantee those who fight and live to tell the tale today shall be heroes to our people! We take our tribe's honour onto the field with us today. I want to see true warriors out there!
I am angry today, men! Furious that these weak-livered girl-children have chosen to stand in our way. I want to see their guts strewn before me. Cut them down! Or I'll take my anger out on you lot!
I have made the decision to attack, my warriors. Prepare yourselves. Look to me in battle. Listen for your orders. Stick hard and fast to them. Only through discipline shall we win!
I have chosen to attack first, men. They shall not know what's hit them. Then if they dare stay on the field we shall rent their bones from their bodies and crack open their skulls.
I need a drink! I am thirsty! So let's get this over quickly. Batter them and beat their heads so hard their eyes pop out. Then we shall drink and I shall get royally pissed!

I have waited for this day to come! The omens tell us this battle will be remembered for a hundred years. Children shall hear of our deeds around the fire and our names will be invoked by warriors for centuries to come!
Do you talk about anything except drink and death\?
Not surprised, the way you eat!
Seniors! Look to your men now!
By my honour, I am getting a little bored.
A good cup of wine! That's what's needed before the end!
Lads! Well done! That one earns you a drink on me!
At the ready, warriors! Fight well today!
Why can't we just try and talk with them\?
What on earth is that SMELL\?
It's not rose blossom, that's for sure…
Wish I was back on the farm.
Cut them down, my fellow warriors!
Just like taking down a boar back home.
Remember who you are! Now fight!
Sheath your weapons, lads, it's done… And badly at that.
I do not like the taste of defeat. Never have.
Defeat\? Not me. You lot got beaten. I didn't.
Foul smells and sick everywhere. Just like my childhood on the Rhine…
Be brave! We're fighting girls today!
A pity. That was my grandfather's…
Let horses do any farting that's needed, man!
Ancestors! Watch me, and be proud!
Your very best, now, men- ATTACK!
I will tend to the needs of our warriors.
Honour those who protect our people!
For the further glory of Pharaoh, attack!
Our warriors will want for nothing!
Yes! They look like they want a fight!
Then let's get ready to greet them, shall we\?
Wait for the order… Let the bastards get a little closer.
No. We hold as we are… They'd never dare attack.
You know, I won't be troubling Charon. Not today!
Look out! Look out! There to the flank!
Sabotage, as you order, my lord.
I will come from the darkness.
I will call forth the power of the djinn.
I shall make my family proud today.
My great warriors! I speak to you before this battle in the knowledge that today you shall crush skulls, break bones and slice through flesh for the honour of our forefathers! To arms, my brothers!

My brothers in arms, look to each other. Mark the man at your side. Fight with him, guard his flank, protect his rear. Work together and we shall double our strength in battle. Fight as one and we shall be victorious!
That's nice, sir. For your family and all…
I want you all to take a good look at the enemy. Take it all in… Debauchery, drunkenness, pillaging and disgusting over-eating! That is what I promise you if you kill this lot! See you at the feast!
I trust we are all ready, men. I trust you have sufficient fire in your bellies for this scum we face. They mean to kill you today. Well, we shall attack first and we shall crush them!
Listen to me! Those bastards over there are quaking in their boots at the sight of you lot! Look at them! Shitting where they stand! Draw you weapons! Get over there! And kill the sods!
Let our deeds this day be the stuff of nightmares! Summon up all the anger from the black depths of your hate-filled hearts and minds! We shall teach them the way of the warrior!

Men, we have grown to be brothers in battle. Some of you will fall today. Mark each other. Bid your farewells, make your offerings to the gods. Then draw your weapons and cleave a path to the glory of our homeland!
Look at this enemy! An army of women and children would be more of a threat. Get ready men! Go to war on these cowards and break their bones. They tremble already at the sight of us!
My brothers in arms, I address you with a burgeoning pride in my heart. We go into battle to strike first at the heart of the enemy. Follow me, friends, and we shall be victorious!
Men, you are looking wonderful today! Just as I expected, the enemy has played right into our hands! We have fortune on our side and the wind in our hair. And we have a lot of hair! So let's dance!
I will kill any man who shows fear or mercy!
I will not go to my death quietly!
Soldiers! We are all that stands between our people and the enemy! We are their shield in these dark times, and we must not fail this day. Find your courage, find your strength, and make ready!
Shut up, or I'll kill you myself!
We are all that is left between our enemy and our families! But we are enough to defeat this rabble! More than enough to guard our lands! Do not forget duty! Draw your swords, and make ready!
Can I go, sir\? I was meant to be a farmer, not this!
We are the last hope of our people. Should we falter today, should we be defeated, our people, our families will be enslaved, or worse! This shall not be! I ask you to fight! Fight with me!

We cannot fail this day! We must not fail! We are the final army of our people! If we fall they fall, so fill your hearts with courage, fill your stomach with hate for our foes! And let us claim victory for our people!
Artillery masters, to work! Smartly, now!
Here they are! Our battle guests. Give them what they deserve, warriors!
How many days we been on the road now\?
Do not shame the gods today! Fight!
Nothing fancy today! Just kill the buggers!
That is it then. Our strength broken on the rocks like waves.
I think I'll stay in bed next time someone says battle!""
Ten thousand curses! And ten thousand more!
Come on! They are supposed to fight us!
How stupid! They want a fight!
That lot reek! Can you smell it\?
Cut their heads off and then let Garm do the rest!
Bastards! They got to the siege equipment, curse them!
Why aren't we firing at them\?
Steady your aim. Wait for it!
Garm the hell hound is loose, boys, and shitting on us from on high!
These men are violent, tough, uncouth, repulsive looking and they mean to scale these walls. They will try to take us here and we must defend the ground. Come children of Andarta! Fight to the last!
Look to our flanks! They're moving on us!
I don't believe it, they're trying that old one.
I will kill any man who shows fear or mercy!
I will not go to my death quietly!

Today, in the heat of battle, when you are wounded and bleeding and Death seems your only friend, remember your ancestors and take courage. For today they fight with us! Draw your weapons to venerate our forefathers!
Today we take the initiative and seize this opportunity to attack! Today we will show this pathetic enemy our appetite for battle! Today they shall flee or die! Today we fight for glory!
Look out, sir, here comes trouble!
No great poetry ever won battles, no big speeches can take down the enemy in front of us. That is up to you. Draw your swords! Obey my orders! And unleash terror on these pitiful beasts!
My proud warriors! Today we have the chance to die for our people! For the glory of our home! For the honour of our ancestors! Take up your weapons and rejoice in this battle!
See the enemy there, pissing themselves with fear. I cannot believe they chose to stay and fight! You should run, you fools! Today you will learn to bow down and worship your betters!

Now, men, we go to battle to fight for all we hold dear. For today we shall defeat these sons of whores, take their land, their women and then feast on their animals and drink the last drop of their mead!
This enemy believes we are wild animals. They call us barbarians. Today we shall show them how animals fight. Tear them limb from limb! Cleave their heads from their bodies! And we shall win the day!

This enemy believes they can better us! They think they can match the might of our swords! Well, they do not know what they face. For today we shall shock the very bones from their bodies. Shock and awe, boys! Shock and awe!

Today our foes have made a grave mistake. They have foolishly decided to stay and face our attack. I trust, my friends, when we are among them we shall teach them to respect their betters! Today they will learn or die!

Today my friends, let loose the fury in your hearts! Summon up the great courage of our forefathers whose blood you hold in your veins! You are warriors indeed! Great warriors! And you shall crush these weaklings!
That's nice, sir. For your family and all…
I shall make my family proud today.
I've done things you wouldn't believe.
Stop! Have a breather, men, and well done!

Ancestors, give us strength! Give me the wisdom to lead and outwit our foe. Your people stand here, the last of us! Should we fall-- Men, we must not fall! We must not disgrace our ancestors or gods! We fight!

And so it falls to us,  the last hope. If we fail today, if our courage flees, all is lost. But do not abandon hope, my soldiers. Victory is within our grasp if we stand and fight. Who is with me\? Who will fight\?
Artillery masters! Target their captain, if you please!

Gods, give us strength! Aid us in this battle! We are the last hope of our people in dark times! We know our duty, and it is an honour to fight for our families, our ancestors, and in your names! All we ask is your aid!

Men, I would not throw your lives away. This battle can be won! This battle must be won! We are the last army of our people, and our ancestors stand with us! Our gods watch over us! We must not shame them! To arms!
Draw swords, and pray the tritons are friendly!
Are we fighting them as well\?
Hold this, will you. I'm taking a dump.
Move will you. I can't see.
To the Pillars of Herakles, if you wish.
To the Pillars of Herakles, if you wish.
Right! I want a nice clean assault this time!
When this ramp drops, you move! No hanging about!
It's a bitter taste, defeat, but better than salt water.
May the Olympian gods protect us!
That's the day done, then. And to end like this…
On my command: kill them all!
If they want a fight, they've come to the right people!
My fingers have gone all wrinkly…
I see they want to play.
Steady, lads. Wait for the word…
No one can stand in my way.
The night has made me her own.
Let's hope we've got enough ammunition.
Excellent! Destroying that artillery is no small victory!
Swift and silent as a shadow.
Swift and silent as a shadow.
Look to the injured! Put out the fires!
I am the fist of the Goddess!
I'm the one your mother warned you about!
My sword sings with the cries of 100 dead men!
One hand builds while the other destroys…
Sabotage, a most excellent choice, my lord.
Mischief and mayhem, yes, my lord.
I will kill any man I see with mercy in his heart!
Bad place to die. Spirits aren't quiet here.
I always hate fighting in weather like this!
And too many well-fed crows, I think…

You want some fancy rip roaring, rousing speech, do you now\? Well, I can honestly say you are the ugliest, hardest, most degenerate bastard sons of bitches I've ever seen. That's it. Now let's go to work.
When I was a lad I dreamed of leading men such as you! The greatest warriors of our tribe! Now I shall show you the way! Listen to my commands and we shall be triumphant! To battle!
You will listen to my every command! You will obey my orders! I will not stand for any who disobey or who cannot stomach the fight! We are warriors! We are winners! Do you understand\?
You are definitely mental, my lad…
What's going on, then\? You men\?
Bad place to die. Long way from home…
You know, it's at times like this I quite miss home cooking…

Rome! The great city of the greatest civilisation in history lies before us! Or so they tell us! What will they say when we conquer them, run riot in their streets and take their city right in front of their eyes!
Nicely done, you men! Now, what's next\?
May sea-worms gnaw at their guts for a thousand years!
Look! The artillery! They got it!
Eyes front! No flinching! Show them how noble Greeks behave!
Swords, my boys! Swords! They are upon us!
Artillery masters! Take your shots in your own time!
I can feel my whole body shake!
Shut up and keep your place!
I love the smell of blood in the morning.
Sometimes I miss home. Sometimes I don't.
We're going in and we're going to conquer! You hear me\?
May the gods show us mercy if they don't.
Cheer up, lads. You're still mostly alive!
A reward to any man who takes an officer's plume!
Oh dear. I think they've chosen the wrong fight today.
Our die is cast it seems. Get ready, men!
I am a daughter of the night!
Wait for it... Wait for it…
My skills blossom under your guidance.
No fancy stuff! Make every shot count!
To the Pillars of Herakles, if you wish.
To the Pillars of Herakles, if you wish.
To the Pillars of Herakles, if you wish.
To the Pillars of Herakles, if you wish.
It burns! It bites… It burns a lot!
My skills have bloomed like the lotus!
Bastards! They're going to flank us!
I would walk to the Otherworld for my tribe.
I would walk to the Otherworld for my tribe.
I would walk to the Otherworld for my tribe.
I would walk to the Otherworld for my tribe.
Think they can get us that way, do they\?
It might be standing now, later, not so much.
Sabotage, as you order, my lord.
I will come from the darkness.
Destruction, aye, I'll see to it.

Ahura Mazda, give us strength to smite these Britons! Curse these blue-arsed Britons from the end of the world! They are a blight to all that is seemly! Let us drive them back, men! That, or kill them all!
I will call forth the power of the djinn.
What's going on, then\? You men\?
Sir! Wanted a life of adventure, sir!
So I've been repeatedly told, sir…
Just a load of old women round here, sir!
I will kill any man I see with mercy in his heart!
Why are you here, you unwashed goat\?
A swallow of wine always steadies the hand!
I have yet to see a truly beautiful woman…
Who gave that man permission to relieve himself\?
I have a morbid horror of drowning. Foolish, I know…
Always nice when what you shoot is done for, lad…
I didn't like the look of it anyway.
It is a great honour to share this fight with you, men!
Artillery masters! Look to your crews, now!
Swords, my boys! Swords! They are upon us!
How many times have I told you. Use it or lose it!
Shift your fat arse. I want a better view.
I am an agent of Hades.
All the gods curse them! Why haven't they died\?
Vulcan's enormous iron hammer! That was close!
Venus' rather splendid bottom! They are good shots!
Before we ran out of ammunition\?
Wind from any direction is bad news…
We can only spit at the dogs now!
A wind from that direction is ill-news.
Damn the admiral! I had hoped to redeem my family's honour today!
Be still sir! You're upsetting my rowers!
I am afraid. Not of death, but of drowning…
We shall never set foot on land again. Never see our home.
Is it too late to start believing in all those gods\?
Enough for the fishes, lad, enough for them.
Pontus! Too long have these goat fondlers and their masters plagued our people! We shall put them to flight to their mountains, and claim a great victory for Parthia! For Parthia we fight!
I told you that was sharp, you twat!
Devotion to the gods has many rewards!
Gods bless you! Enjoy your next life!
My skills are gifts from the Gods.
Victory! And life! Sweet indeed, like good wine…
We won, then. How many drowned, do you think\?
I have much to be thankful for!

The enemy stands at the gates of our great city, ready to unleash slaughter! But have courage, men. Our people, our gods, are with us. Our enemy will break on these walls, and we will drive them back!
So was yours, lad. Cheap, too…

We cannot let this great city fall! Do not forget why we fight. Our people, our families, take shelter in the temples and houses. We cannot let the enemy be victorious, men. We stand! We fight to the last!

This great city, this great capital, cannot fall to our enemy! If they breach our walls, the streets will run red with our people's blood! Our temples will be desecrated! This cannot be! We must hold!

We defend this great city and our people this day. Should these walls fall, should we fall, nothing stands between our enemy and their slaughter! We must hold, men! Must weather whatever storm is hurled against us!

We cannot yield this great city. We shall not let our people be enslaved or slaughtered. No! No! We shall fight to hold these walls. Find your courage, men! We will hold back this storm, our capital will not fall!
Ha, the Carthaginians! My father used to tell me tales of these people of Africa. They are wild beyond our dreams. Their city is made of gold. And the squeal like girls when they bleed!
I will walk the old tracks.
I will walk the old tracks.
The old tracks are open to those who know the way.
The old tracks are open to those who know the way.
I cannot stand the sight of the Carthaginians! They love their animals I am told! Most of all their elephants which they sleep alongside after feasting on children! They are scum one and all!

The heathens of Carthage lie yonder! Scabby with their pus and diseases they fester and rot. I can smell them from here! I charge every man here to cleave off a head and take it home to show our people who we fight! Vermin!
The road goes ever on and on.
The road goes ever on and on.
The only good Carthaginian is a dead Carthaginian! When we are done with them we shall take all of their gold and loot! Dispatch them, men! For the glory of the gods!
Carthaginians! At last we get to kill us some Carthaginians! I love it! May we carve this place into history as the place where their god of death welcomed so many of their so called soldiers!

Take these walls, take their capital, and I promise you shall be rewarded! Hunt down our enemy in the streets, houses and temples. Any that resist put to the sword. Do this, and you may claim your choice of the spoils!
The earth will guide my feet.
The earth will guide my feet.
Child loving, human sacrificing, elephant-mounting bastards of Africa! Here they come to meet a proper army and fight against real warriors! May the gods favour us against this infidel! To battle!
Gods, grant us victory this day! Permit us to take their capital in your name, and dedicate new temples in your honour! Let us honour our gods, men, and pray they grant us strength! Make ready!

Behind these walls our foe cowers, lamenting our strength! We stand at the gates of their capital, ready to take them for the glory of our people and our gods! What greater prize can we find\? Make ready, men!

Before us lies the capital of our enemy. In the sacking of it, what greater glory can we bestow on our people and on ourselves! Its streets and temples will run with blood, and its riches will be ours! To arms, men!
This ugly lot worship a god called Bile! Ridiculous! Bile! I want them to meet with all the bile you can give them. Cut open their stomachs and let their bile flood this field of battle.
You! Stop gaping like a fish and get working!
Soldiers! To the decks! No quarter!
We can still do this, men! Stand fast for the glory of Parthia!
Jupiter's noble prick! Raise a cheer for the general, men!
You lot! You fishermen! Yes, you! Got any squid for sale\?
Any man who slacks at the oars will be shorter by a head!
Men! Now is the moment of truth!
Brace yourself! We're going to hit hard!

Make ready, men. Make good your preparations, for today will be long and bloody work! These fools are like wheat to be harvested! We will cut down this crop, and sow the field afresh with their corpses.

Make ready, men. Make ready, for today we crush our enemies! We will drive them before us! And, when our bloody work is done, we shall hear their lamentation and the cries of carrion birds! And it will be glorious!

I have chosen the time, and I have chosen this place! We have the advantage here, cast any doubt from your hearts. We will drive these curs before us, and cut down any who stand! Who will fight for me this day\? Who will fight\?
Let us take battle to our enemies. We shall chase these birds away, put this army to flight! They lack our resolve! They lack our discipline! Draw your swords, men, and let us chase them off!

Stand ready, you dogs! I will not have you bringing shame upon me or our people this day. We will have victory or an honourable death. I swear by the gods, I will not suffer cowardice! Victory or death!

These pig-dogs are beneath us, beneath our contempt! Let us punish their insolence with terrible retribution! Answer their arrogance with spear's thrust and arrow's flight! Send these craven swine fleeing! Make ready!

Our prayers have been answered, the day of battle has finally come. We shall not dishonour the gods by failing at our task! With sword, spear and arrow, we shall bloody our foe and bring them down! Make ready!

Quell any doubts, discard them! Such base fears should plague the hearts of our foe. It is they who need fear us! It is they who come unprepared! We press battle upon them. That, and our courage, will break them!

They take to the field, but those fools would do better preparing their own funeral pyres. We have the advantage: we have pressed forwards and I would have not done so if victory would not be ours. Make ready, men!
This is really going to hurt them.

This rabble of unwashed swine do not trouble me, men, and they should not trouble you. They are an unworthy foe, hardly a match to our strength. Let us make this swift and quick! Let us cut down this filth! To arms!
Carpenter sends word, sir. His men are ready.
The Captain\? He's as caring and kind as a shark!
I have a horror of fish!
The fishing is rubbish round here…
Soldiers should be on dry land. This is unnatural!
AT THEM! Boarding party to me!
Aye, but he wins, the bugger!
With your face, you should be at home with them!
Good fortune to you all, and all our comrades!
Sir! Take care, I beg you!
I want to go back to the fields!
Come on! Come on! You march like old women!
I am the servant of Pluto.
Check the chests and lockers! What, no more ammunition\?
By all the Gods of Rome! That was a bit of clo-AARRGGH!
I don't believe it! Nothing left and they're still there!
Empty! Not a single bloody thing left for them now!
Barnacles and blisters! Clear these bodies!
I ache for landfall, deckmaster. More than victory…
These waters are troubled. The gods cursed them long ago.
Now we fight only for our honour! It has been a privilege, men!
Sir, don't let the men see any weakness!
This will be a profitable day!
One day, we'll greet the Ferryman! But not today!
Your mother was a goat! And she smelt worse!
I hunger for blood and glory!
I hunger for blood and glory!
I hunger for blood and glory!
I hunger for blood and glory!
I was born to end lives!
I was born to end lives!
Draw swords! Let us make ready!
They sail too well for my liking.
Our foes are no better than the sharks!
You've slept with lepers harder than them!
Did his wetnurse drop him on his pointy head\?
Oi! Have you come for a fight, or just to look at real sailors\?
Come on, men! Imagine it's me over there on their deck!
You maggot-eaten sea-slugs! I've seen lepers harder than you!
Stand still! You are Romans, not bloody dancing girls!
AT THEM! Boarding party to me!
Be ready... Oars clear before we hit!

Be prepared, men, this day will be long and bloody. But if we hold to our purpose, if we yield no ground to them, we will drive these filthy swine before us! We shall cut them down and chase any that flee!
Do not let yourselves be unmanned by these wretched dogs, men! That they stand against us is an insult to our people. We shall not let that pass! We shall answer with sword and blood! To arms!
Row faster, you spawn of harpies!
Row faster, you spawn of harpies!

Drive any doubts you may have from your hearts, for there is no room for fear this day. Fill your hearts with hate and fire instead. Give fuel to your wrath, and spit it upon our enemy! Do this, and they shall break!

Drive fear from your hearts, there is no place for it here! We are watched by the gods, and they'll grant us a glorious victory or a noble death today! But for those craven enough to flee, the gods grant nothing, but an eternal shame!
The Captain's mad, son, mad! But he knows his work!
The gulls circle! An omen of good fortune, I think!
I need a drink. Several drinks. A skinful of good wine…
There are horrors, even now, below our keel! Horrors!
The sea is best left to fishermen. Warriors have no business there.
Men! Now is the moment of truth!
You! Do not do that! I want a neat and tidy battlefield!
Shall we send them to Anubis, sir\?
Hit them hard, brothers. For the glory of Egypt!
Buck up, sir, it's only a bit of crow shit!
Hold on tight, lads! And pray!
Hold on to your sword, there!
Sir, the enemy really do mean to kill us.
I do not like the omens, decurion!
Do not rush! There's time to kill them properly!
Lift the standards high! Now, for glory!
Do not rush! There's time to kill them properly!
Master Archer! Check the ammunition stores, if you please!
Is that your armour\? Are you BLEEDING on the Senate's armour, worm\? Did you pay for it\?
By Mars! They are now enemies of my blood!
Sir, sir, sir! Bosun reports that we're being shot at, sir!
Oarmaster! I know they are tired! Keep the men moving!
I'll thank you to do your duty and fight!
Be still, man! Do you want to be killed\?
Look out! Duck! Duck, man, duck!
Umm. Over there, in camp. I'll just go get it…
I promise you, men, in the name of Belatu Cadros, if we destroy these gallic imbeciles you may feast on their women tonight. The only good Gaul is a female Gaul! We shall enjoy them until dawn!
You unwashed, swine lovers! Run home to your pig wives!
Just like me and that whore the other night.
Gods! If only it was that quick.
Why not give up now and spare yourselves.
Clean those blades, boys! They're going to be busy.
That's it! We're in! Come on!
Ha! Now we begin to fight!
This is getting very hot, decurion!
No retreat! No stepping back! Be as the wall is to the city and make stone of your bodies in the face of this foe. Deflect his blows, counter with greater blows! Hold your station!
My father taught me that when a foe attacks it is often weaker than those who defend. But only if the defence is well prepared. So make ready. We do not have much time for they are coming.
Draw your weapons men and prepare to defend this position. The enemy will come at us hard. They will be ruthless in attack. Do not shirk your duty but stand proud and strong!
Just like ploughing a whore back home! We'll thrust right through them!
Men! We defend this position today! I have chosen to let them come and do their worst. We will take this chance to show the gods we have warrior hearts and no one can match our bravery.
Do not flop about like a landed fish!
The enemy\? Pay them no mind! You do your work!
The next man to touch a rope without orders will feel my sword!
I once took a fish here that were bigger than you, sir.
There are moonfish in these waters, I tell you! Moonfish!
They're only islands if you look at them from the water…
Make ready, men! This enemy is a sly one. They shall employ various tactics to displace us but I am confident we shall hold this ground and win this battle. To your positions!

I trust you all prepared to face down this attack. We must stand firm against this foe and we must then push them back. Use their might against them. Parry their blows and counter at every opportunity.
Fight as one! Look to your brothers! Aid them in battle! Give no quarter and let there be no weakness in the line. Hold strong and true and we shall defend this position!
What are you wittering about\? They're always bloody islands.
Send these dogs to Anubis! Break their charge!
Keep a weather eye open, men!
Keep a weather eye open, men!
Vulcan farts on our efforts today! Why did they even get near the artillery\?
Now we show them courage, men! Stand by!
I think, sir, we should make ready!
Ignore those fools! They only want to kill you!
Any man who leaves his place will be cut down!
Ignore those fools! They only want to kill you!
Jupiter curse them! They've shot my crest!
I'm out! Anyone got any spare\?
Maybe not, but it brightens the memory!
You have to be alive to feel the aches, lad…
Honour will not fill a sail, or calm the waves, sir!

Carthage is a city of monsters: child-killers who have no respect for family or ties of blood! They love only gold and the depraved pleasures it buys! I count it a Roman duty to exterminate them all! To arms!
Girls with bloody big choppers, mind…
Be brave! We're only facing a few girls today!
Of course it hurts, you idiot!
Arrrchhh. My blood. But I will not end like this!
I do not believe in cowardly ways such as duck-arrrrgghghghgh!

We have cornered our foe here, driven them to tremble in this last refuge! Carthage and its people require one last effort from us, one last great task: to take this place and bring our foes back home in chains! Begin the attack!
You pig loving, barbarian inbreds, come and kiss my arse!
Draw your weapons! When this thing gives…
Smells like another load of Egyptians for the slaughter! They live in the dust of the desert and ride beasts with humps. And they can't take a drink! What a waste of Tyr's talents!
Woah! You're even uglier than the last lot we killed
Clear the way! Clear the way!
This is it! This is what we've waited for!
Gods above! Their captain is a most insolent man!
I do not know which smells worse: crab farts, or them!
Get hold of something and hang on, you fool!
Men! Send the enemy to their watery graves!
Hold on! We're going to hit!
Today I shall defend this ground! We shall not give them an inch! What say you, friends\? Are you with me\? Are you tough enough to stand up to this enemy\? Come, to the fray!
This morning I prayed to the gods. I received their bidding and we shall enact their wishes here in the next few hours. They desire this attack to be repelled and this enemy to be destroyed!
Prepare your positions, my brothers! This opposition shall try and remove us from this ground. Make sure you can hold it! Parry and block then cut these weaklings down! Do not give in!

One day I shall ask you to attack for me. But today we must defend and strain every sinew in the protection of this ground. The enemy shall have to come to us. And we will inflict great pain upon them!
Who will defend this position with me\? Who will stake his life and pride on this piece of earth and fight until his last drop in its defence\? Take up your weapons!
Gull-shit! All over the armour! Bah!
Worry about your supper, lad! Let the Captain see to the enemy!
There is a simple honesty to a sea battle, you know.
I used to fish when I were a lad…
Wine warms a sailor's heart, man!
Water, water, everywhere. Give me land!

We stand together today ready to do battle with this enemy. They shall try to come at us hard and throw everything into the fray. We must repel them. All of you, on each flank and at the front! Look to it!
We stand today in great danger. The enemy is to attack and we must fight to the last. There is no fleeing from here. We will meet all they have to throw at us and we shall be victorious!
Warriors! I have every confidence in your ability to defend this ground. You know what is expected of you and you know what to do. So take up your positions and fight!
And eases his joints after rowing…
The eyes of the Senate and all Rome are upon us today. We must make them proud that we are their defenders! More than that: our Roman gods are watching! Make sure they are not ashamed!
Get ready! I think, it's time to--AAARRRGGGHHH!
Cold steel, men, cold steel! Our one true ally today!
I'll tell you a secret: everyone's scared.
Any man who runs will answer to my rage!
I've seen corpses with more life than you! Move!
Any man who runs will answer to my rage!
This is butchery, not warriors' work.
By the gods, finish them off now!
That's the spirit! Keep driving home, men!
All things considered, I'd sooner be at the games!
Jupiter's windy gusts! I felt that one!
Why did I ever leave Capua\?
Look everywhere for ammunition! We're out!
Working parties, be about your duties now!
Roust them, I'll have no slacking aboard today!
The banner, man, keep it up!
I am a favoured son of Mars!
I am not moving from this spot, not for any-AARGGHGH!
Rome will be proud of her son!
All for the glory of Rome!
We who are about to die!
The great god Tyr walks with us today. We shall honour him and defend this position with our last breath. Do not give up this ground. Protect it or we shall all be meeting Tyr face to face!
Make ready to defend this area, men. We shall not give them anything! Our people expect glory! Tuisto expects it! We shall not disappoint! To your positions and prepare! We shall not fall today!
Come on, lads, welcome our guests…
What\? Oh… (shouting) Come on then, you bastards!
The Legions have gathered nearby, their general is trying to put his lazy troops in order. How does one mount an attack when one is a yellow-bellied craven\? We are about to see, men! Be prepared!
To the gates of Hades if you want, sir!
Strip the dead of weapons and armour!
My blade is itching to cut you open.
Gauls! Gauls! Gauls! I love the Gauls! At last an enemy who will cuss and bite and claw! They fight like women and smell like the shite on my boots! For Tyr's sake, kill some Gauls today!
Don't worry those fish-faced gits, you land-fool! Worry about me!
Careful what you ask for, sir!
A denarius to the man who finds my vine stick!
By Jupiter, I am tired of waiting!
Put some effort into it! Smash them!
Hold tight! This is going to be nasty!
We need more speed at this angle… Increase the count!
Row! Row! Row! Faster you, dogs.
Charge home! No quarter! No mercy!
For the honour of our families!
Fight, O my brothers, fight! Glory and honour!
Exactly! I intend to ram them lad!
Sir! We'ra going straight for them, sir!
Deckmaster, beat that man! No spitting on my ship!
You! Punishment later! I will not have puking on my decks!
I do not like water. Drowning is a dishonourable death.
Oi! Your mum does fishermen! For food!
I do not like these waters. They are troubled.
Well, your mum does fish! For fun!
Well, there's enemy ships all over them.

These Germans look fierce and warlike, but compared to the soldiers of Carthage, they are bandits! They find easy courage in wine or mead, but are easily chased back to their rain-soaked forests! Today, then, we hunt pigs!

Blast! I've got my bits caught in this armour.  Why won't someone come up with better combat gear. Can't even take a piss in this lot. Anyway, here we go again, men! Batter and bonce them, etc, etc… Really can't be bothered today…

Did you see that\? Pink faeries and pixies from the otherworld calling me to battle! We go forward men with the Minstrels of the Damned playing our tune and fluffy, fat dragons bringing in air support! Hoorah!
Forget the enemy! Be afraid of ME!
I told you, just like a nice parade!
Hold to your duty, no matter what!
Any man who falls back will lose his head!
I am the chosen one! In my name you will slaughter! Tell me that I'm a hero! Some of you are going to die. Martyrs, of course, to the freedom I shall provide!
My brothers and sisters, I love you! I do! If I could I would marry you all and have your children I would! But instead we go to our deaths bonded as one big happy family! Follow me!
This is butchers' work… Chop them down!
They do seem like useless bastards, sir!
That's it, men! Let them have it!
By Vulcan's hammer! I rather liked that helmet!
They couldn't hit the side of the Senate from inside the Senate!
We didn't know we would need so much, sir.
I told you to be more careful with supplies!
Wake up! I don't care how tired you are!
Ration of wine for all, sailing master!
She's not here, so shut it!
My mind is sharper than any sword!
Duck you foo-- Ah, too late!
Excellence is not an act, it is a habit.
I am the favoured son of Ares!
My wit is but educated insolence!
Pleaure in the job puts perfection In the work.
My mind soars higher than Olympus!
Tyr bless us and give us strength!
Come on, cheer! Let's here you, lads! My mother can do better.
Aye! Still here. You got any wine\?
The Iron helm of Mars! Are you STILL alive\?
Oi! Spotty! Do you get a good price for your sister\?
Row, or feel the kiss of the whip!
Pull! Pull until your backs break!
Pull! Pull until your backs break!
Gods in the deeps! I can smell them from here!
Row, or feel the kiss of the whip!
Put your backs in to it!
Row faster, you squid-sucking sons of…
Put your backs in to it!
Put your backs in to it!
Row faster, you squid-sucking sons of…
Put your backs in to it!
If anything happens, tell my father I died like a Roman!
I don't hold with thinking in battle. It's not Roman!
Put your backs into it! Let's cripple these bastards!
To arms! Attack! To the fight, men!
Oi! Does your mum still work the docks\?
Do NOT flinch! I will beat any man who is weak!
I have a powerful fear of fish!
May Donar give us strength today as we breach these walls and take this city from the heathen. Carthage is a mythical place but I have brought you here so that you may become legends!
Only if I don't do it first…
You just like worrying honest folk, don't you\?
I've heard they don't like you either, you girl!
Keep a weather eye open, men!
Keep a weather eye open, men!
Form on me! Steady now! Draw swords!
If you can stand, you will fight! Got it, sunbeam\?
Any man who falls behind will answer to me! So, steady!
If the man alongside falls, so be it! Keep to your place!
I am the servant of Pluto.
Get onto the wall and kill the first bastard you see!
That's it, sir! Nothing left to chuck at them!
This is no way for Romans to fight!
Bellona's tasty backside! Who fired that\?
You heard the captain! Keep at it!
If he supplied us better we wouldn't run out of ammunition.
Oarmasters! See to it that your men have an extra wine ration!
This is getting a touch uncivilized!
Men of Carthage, let us put an end to the presumption of these Romans. Let us put their legions to death, and make the Senate and people of Rome wail at the loss! Let us have victory!
My mind is sharper than any sword!
Don't let the others see you like this!
Watch out! Arrows and stones do not care about courage!
Excellence is not an act, it is a habit.
I am the favoured son of Ares!
My wit is but educated insolence!
Pleaure in the job puts perfection In the work.
My mind soars higher than Olympus!
May the Old Ones protect us us today.
Put yah backs in to it!
Call that a weapon\? Mine's bigger when I take a piss.
Put yah backs in to it!
Put yah backs in to it!
Put yah backs in to it!
Put yah backs in to it!
What are we waiting for\? We should charge.
Come and see just how much I want to kill you.
I am with you my lord!
I am with you my lord!

Long have the Seleucids dared to match their strength against Egypt, but they shall be found wanting this day! We shall prove the greater and, in mighty Pharaoh's divine name, we shall slaughter them! Make ready, men!
Keep it up, men! Keep it up!
Are they Germans\? They're ugly enough to be Germans.
Aim low! Aim low! Give them death!
Aye, lad, but they sail like little girls!
And this, grandmother, is how you…
Gods of wind and tide preserve us! The foe look fierce!
I do not like the look of this, by Mars, not one bit!
Be ready to withdraw, men. Or board if we can't!

We stand... we stand here to defend our honour and people! We stand here in sight of our gods and ancestors! We stand here ready, and we shall not be found wanting! They have pressed for battle, and we will answer!

Make ready, men! Make ready, for the storm is here! Our foes assail us, but we can weather their worst, and we can triumph! We will not be beaten down or pushed aside but will stand firm, as our ancestors did!

Many here have fought before in defence of our people! Fought for the honour of our gods and of our ancestors! Some, well, some of you just like to fight! This day is no different! We can vanquish this pack of mange-ridden dogs! Who's with me\?
Smash them to pieces, men! Get ready to board!

I count myself fortunate to stand here. To stand with my warrior brothers, to stand here for our people! I would not wish to be anywhere else this day! For, if the gods will it, we shall break this enemy, and put them all to the sword!

We did not seek battle, men, but nor shall we run from it. These curs believe us weak, but they shall find us as lions! For I know you, each of you is worth ten of them, and together we shall triumph this day!
Quiet! Do you want to be fish food\?
Has anyone seen my anchor stone\?
I do not trust these tides. The spirits are capricious here.
Still, nice day for a bit of rowing.
I used to fish in mountain streams…

We have let them come to us. We have let them choose this battle, but does that mean we're cowards or that we are weak\? No! We let them come, let them overreach themselves! Today we shall break them!
Take heart, men, for we stand ready to meet our foe. This rabble, these dogs, may bark and cry out, but we are above such petty taunts, and words shall not rob us of our courage or our purpose!

This battle has been forced upon us, but that does not mean we are unprepared. Our numbers are great enough if we hold! And great enough to break them! Put your trust in me, men! Put your trust in the gods! For we can win a great victory today!
I used to piss in them. So what\?
Oi! Spotty! Do you get a good price for your sister\?
Somebody kill that moaning bastard! NOW!
This is it then\? I thought it would… I would...
Swim for it, lads! Stay clear as she sinks!
The enemy\? The enemy\? Keep your eyes on me, damn you!
Hold the men in check! Some of them may run mad!
Sir! Gods! Sir! They really don't like us!
I am an agent of Hades.
Fight for the glory of our sacred isles, brothers!
That's it! We're out of ammunition!
Blistering barnacles! What a bunch of dockside whores!
Steady, man! Have you left your bravery in the winesack\?
Can't I cower like a girl for a bit\?
I am a favoured son of Mars!
Devotion to the gods has many rewards!
Down lads, down! They make a nasty noise but---arrrrgghhghghh!
Come on, stand like a man!
I'm bored. Will anything ever hap-arrrghghg!
My skills are gifts from the Gods.
I have much to be thankful for!
Rome will be proud of her son!
All for the glory of Rome!
Annoy the bastards… Lets see what they're made of.
When we go… Don't hang back, men.
Poseidon curse you! Sink the bastards!
Well, here's a good day and no mistake!
Hope you kissed your wives goodbye.
Because we'll soon be kissing them hello!
Truth may walk through the world unarmed.
Truth may walk through the world unarmed.
I go in dread Pharaoh's name.
I go in dread Pharaoh's name.
Just another stroll in the fields, lads!
Hold fire, you idiots, until you have a good target!
Already done, sir! All at the ready!
Senior marines! Look to your weapons! NOW!
Annoy me again, and I'll use you as a latrine sponge. Got it\?
In what is about to come, Fortuna smile on us all…
At least it will be quick!
Is that what you say to all the girls\?

We will show these foreign dogs our mettle today! They did not seek this battle: we have forced it upon them and that is to their shame! Their lack of courage means the battle is won already! We need but drive them before us!
What arrogant fools! Let us teach these wretched swine what it truly means to be a warrior, to be a soldier! We shall put them to the sword or put them to flight! Make ready!
Unwashed peasants and their foolish leaders, that is who we face! They would hardly be a match for half our count! This is slaughter, not battle! Draw your swords, men, and let us make this quick!
We stand here, ready for battle, and not all of us will see another day. We will have victory,though, and the honoured dead shall be remembered. Bravery and glory will not be forgotten!

Would you be unmanned by these dogs\? Would you have it known you fled before them\? I would rather fight and die, than be known a coward! And, if you fight, if you find your courage, I can promise you victory! What say you\?

Would you be unmanned by this rabble\? Would you bring dishonour upon us, upon our people and the gods\? No! No, cowardice is the little death, which gnaws at you each day! Better to fight and die a warrior! Make ready!
What insolence! Do they not know who I am\? Who we are\? Let us put a quick end to this affront, men. Let us put these arrogant curs to the sword! Such mockery must not go unanswered! Make ready!
With the gods as my witness, I promise you victory if we hold to our purpose! If you give no ground! If you fight! We will whip these dogs! We take the fight to the enemy, men!
Silence! I want no gossip on my battlefield!

Would you dishonour your people and the gods, by being unmanned by this rabble\? No! I will not suffer cowards to live! I will cut down any that run! We will have victory, or we will have an honourable death!
Ha, ha, they don't stand a chance.

Would you let these dogs insult you\? Insult our ancestors, our gods\? No! We will put an end to this affront. Let us see if they still taunt us as their guts spill upon the ground! As we hack them down! Make ready!
Sea air. Very bad for the armour.
Of course it's wet, you idiot!
I do not want to feed the crabs.
The crabs will bless their gods for their feasting today!
No! No, no, no, no. Men! With the faces of fish!
I've seen graveyard whores three days dead with more about them than you!
No! No! This is most unfair!
No need to rush in, boy. Don't lose your head.
Swim! Don't let her pull you down.
Something just swam past my leg!
Do not let the crabs near me.
Cut your armour free! Then swim!
Keep your aim low! Hit them in the centre of the body!
That's it! Loving those angry faces! Grrrr! Go on pull those really barbaric ones, they make me laugh! Ha, ha! Yes! Brilliant! Get me every time. Oh, I'm going to enjoy this one, boys! Top form!

You know it's funny, last night I had this dream that my strategy was all wrong and we were all massacred! I was captured and castrated while all prisoners were burned at the stake. Strange, eh\? Oh, well, ONWARD!
Remember what I said, men. No swearing! Keep it clean out there! If you lose an arm or a leg keep it to yourself and button it. If we are defeated, take it with a damn or a blast. And no buggering!
