Right, I have been up all night planning and my advisors have told me we haven't got a hope today. I'm not so sure. Tufty the Rabbit's ears were pointing straight up this morning. Always a good omen. To battle!
Hold steady, lads, not much longer!
The enemy\? What are they\? Goats and little girls!
Now I've played this lot before. They're a crafty bunch of foreigners, lots of foul play. Just keep it tight at the back and hit them on the counter. Remember, it's a game of two halves!
Oh, I love the smell of death in the morning. Bring me the heads of every enemy born on the solstice! I want to make a big fat cake! Ha, ha! Yes! That's right! It's my birthday!
It's at times like this, I wish I'd listened to my mother…
Any man who dies will answer for his weakness!
File leaders! Look to your men now!
When this ramp drops, you move! No hanging about!
Deal with this lot quickly and cleanly.
Our lads can do quick, sir, but not clean.
And so we face the forces of Carthage. Pathetic. I bet we could drink them under the table any day. Will you please get them from my sight as quickly as possible. In Rudianos' name!
War is the natural habitat of men.
I would travel the world for Parthia.
A champions work is never done.
I would travel the world for Parthia.
True sons of Ares never rest!
A Greek without a sword in hand is no Greek at all!

I feel a weight of expectation on my shoulders, men. I will bear that burden for you. All you must carry is shield and sword. Use them well, and bring sorrow to our enemies here, at the gates of Rome! Make ready!
Sons of Mars! Sons of Rome! We stand alone! Before us is the anger of our enemies! If it triumphs, then Rome is lost… I, for one, would not see that happen! So, make ready to die for Rome, and glory!

Today we will write a new page in history! We shall stand, the last defenders of Rome, and we shall defy the enemy! And when we have done so, the poets will compose epics in our honour! Prepare yourselves!
We stand as the last defence of the Senate and People of Rome! No prouder moment awaits us after today! Here we prove that we are worthy of the name of Romans". Here we stop our enemies!"

Here, at the gates of Rome itself, we are the last line of defence. There can be no more steps back! There can be only victory, or death. And I did awake today desiring death! We fight! We fight for Rome!
I would walk to the Otherworld for my tribe.
I would walk to the Otherworld for my tribe.
I would walk to the Otherworld for my tribe.
I would walk to the Otherworld for my tribe.
When it gives, charge in, lads. Cut them down.
We'll smash the flank of these goatherders, sir.
Only when the moment is right.
To the Pillars of Herakles, if you wish.
To the Pillars of Herakles, if you wish.
To the Pillars of Herakles, if you wish.
To the Pillars of Herakles, if you wish.
Put your backs in to it!

Hah! Has it come to this\? Enemies loiter in front of the gates of Palmyra, eager to plunder her riches and murder her people! But know this - as long as I, Zenobia Augusta, stand the city will not fall!
Put your backs in to it!
I can't wait to get at them!
When we're in show no mercy! Kill everything!
Put your backs in to it!
Put your backs in to it!
Put your backs in to it!
Aim low, you bastards, aim low!
Right, you lot. I know you can swear like sailors, so give it some!
Up your bums, you bench-sniffing bastards!
At them, men! With a will!
Men! I want them dead! Do you hear\?
Fight! FIGHT! Are you stupid, boy\?
YOU! Stand still, man! Or I'll cut you down myself!
So was your dad! But I got a refund!
Bath the earth with their blood!
Oi! I had your mum! She was rubbish!
By Sekhet! By Anqet! By Bastet! By Nun! We have destroyed them!
No! No! I have yet to do great things…
If I see you retreating… I'll kill you myself.
Come on, you old rat! We can make it!
It's too far to swim… I'm done…
How come that fat bastard's floating and I'm sinking\?
When an order is given DO NOT hang about!
Wine for the man who kills a standard bearer!
Come on! Crush these sons of whores!
I want to see their entrails!

As Baal is my witness, many a general has faced me, Zenobia, in battle! They underestimated me and this was their downfall. Then they grovelled at my feet! Today will be no different; follow my orders and we'll feast before sunset!
Cheer up, lads. You're still mostly alive!
Peace is for the women and the weak!
Kill them or, by Mars and Venus both, I'll see your guts!
Rome honours those who fight for her!
A true Roman can never rest while Rome's enemies live.
To live in peace we must prepare for war.
A well placed threat has great power.
I am sure we will be able to come to some arrangement.
Carefully chosen words are as powerful as any weapon.
Ba'al's bushy beard! That was close!
Once we've broken through, we must hold the gap.
We'll this is a merry dance.
I'll take dancing over dying any day.
If it's one thing I like more than a flank it's a--
Shut up! Keep your voices down!
I want to see their heads on spikes within the hour!
When we're in there I want them to wish they had never been born!

These walls will not stop us, men! Once their defences have fallen, we shall overrun their capital! Glory will be ours, and you may claim what you will. Take your choice of spoils. This is my gift to you!
Druids and wise women! All demons in the shape of men!
Bath the earth with their blood!
Oi! Piggy-boy! You want some of this\?
Bastards! I will cut out your hearts and eat them!
Curse Dagon's breath! More of the filth!
How many are there do you think\?
I've failed… May the sea take me!
There are sharks in these waters!
May the gods be merciful! Save us!
I would travel the world for Parthia.
I would travel the world for Parthia.
I would travel the world for Parthia.

Smell that! That's the smell of victory, boys!
What the smell of them shitting themselves\?
Praise, Nun! The unclean cowards flee!
I suppose you are right. Incovenient, though…
Up my arse, waiting to be shat out!
Sir, they are the enemy. They are supposed to be hostile. Sir.
Now is the hour! Draw your swords!
Where are the foes worthy to meet me\?
May Angra Mainyu visit destruction on these Carthaginians! May winds and tempests drive them back to cower in their hovels! Men, we will be the tempest, the fists of god! Make ready!
That's buggered, then... Might as well build a ramp of bodies.
Carthage will always rule the waves with men like our admiral in charge.
Cut their bowels open! Slice their limbs! Castrate the bastards!
We'd be doing better if we'd chucked the admiral overboard and put some sacred chickens in charge!
Are there any women here\? Or are you warriors\?
We must stamp out this rebellion. As true warriors, true Britons, we spit on such treachery and dishonour. I cannot believe they will fight as one. They must be butchered as a warning to others!
Do not despair... See, the admiral is with us!
Can I be of more assistance\?
There is more I could do…
If you don't get a move on I'll run you through myself!

These Britons are men of no consequence! Honest Greek writers have nothing at all to say about them. From this I conclude that they are completely barbarous! One day, they will thank us for Greek culture and decent food! Ha!
Watch out! They're firing! Get to cover!
What you all gawping at\? Never won a battle! Get to work.
Look to your weapons. Make sure you're ready.
Is that them or the fish I smell\?
Over the side with the dead. The gods will look after them now!
Keep at it, men! Keep at-ARRRGGHHHH!
I'm getting too old for this, you know. At least we won.
I love the smell of sailors shitting it in the morning.
Look out sea scum, here I come!
Give me an oar! We'll get there faster!
Give me an oar! We'll get there faster!
Those things can dish it out, but never take it.
I love a good arm wrestle!
My strength could move a thousand ships!
Look out sea scum, here I come!
Look out sea scum, here I come!
So, they have some honour then!
I love a good arm wrestle!
My strength could move a thousand ships!
Look out sea scum, here I come!
Easy, lads! Form up, and make ready!
Do not forget why we stand here. Behind us are our people, our families! We hold these walls to defend them! Should they fall, should we fail, then nothing stands between our people and slaughter!
Courage, men! Do not let your hearts be gripped with fear, for these walls are strong and they must come to us. The gods willing, we will weather this storm, and we will answer hate with hate!

Courage now! Courage! We can hold these walls if we do not falter! We must not abandon our defences, there is nowhere to run, the streets would run red with the blood of our people! This cannot be! This will not be! We will stand!

Our defences are strong, but it is not barricades or walls that hold back foes, it is the men that guard them! We will not falter, we will not give! We will hold to the last, fight to the last, before we allow the enemy in!

Our ancestors and the gods are watching us defend their people! We shall not be found wanting in this task! Our duty is to hold these walls to the last, fight until our last breath, for the lives of our people!
May the gods grant us the strength to hold these walls and throw back our enemies! We defend this place in their name and for our people! There is no room for cowardice here, we stand and we hold!
No! My father! By Tyr we are weakened!

Here we stand! We will guard this place, guard our people to the last! Gods, grant us strength, the strength to hold and throw back our enemies! Soldiers, today we are the shield of our people and we must not shatter!

Soldiers, we are charged with a noble duty, to hold these walls and shield the people within! The gods willing, we will be a match for the task. Whatever happens, we must not yield, must not fall! To arms! Prepare and make ready!

Our defences will hold, and you will hold! Or, by the gods, I will throw any who run from the walls myself! This is no place for cowards today, for we stand between the enemy and our people! And we must hold!
I will cut down any man who runs!
We take this settlement for you, my lord!
We take this settlement for the tribe!
We take this settlement for the tribe!
We take this settlement for you, my lord!
Let them cower before our might!
Let them cower before our might!
Look! The admiral hasn't abandoned us.
That changes things, and not for the better.
All the more for us to fight, sir.
See the artillery fall, men! We fight for their memory now!
Be respectful to the trees and stones
Get out of the way! Let me at them! The dirty blighters!
Fight! You are sailors, but you are warriors also!
We fight on! It is only a flesh wound!
And praise us! For our blood, and our sweat…
We're under fire! Get to your posts!
We're victorious! Praise be to the gods!
I'm getting too old for this, you know. At least we won.
Make ready to fight! We're close now.
Now then, looks like they've chosen to fight.
You'll be alright, boy. You've still got one left.
They should not have taken us on. They deserved to die.
Never mind, man. We are the gods' playthings, that all!
QUIET! Listen to orders, curse your souls!
I don't understand what's going on…
Why didn't I stay in camp\?
Only a scratch. I still live.
Only a scratch. I still live.
It will heal, they always do.
It will heal, they always do.
Today we fight against a greater number, warriors of Tyr. Tonight we shall drink to the dead! These odds make my blood rise as there will  be more to kill. More to mark our glory!
Our enemy is upon us, men! Make ready!

We shall protect our shores from this invasion. The druids shall make an offering tonight! Let their blood flow into the waters so the gods may bless this victory and keep our shores safe from more marauders!
What cruelty do you wish, O Lord\?
What cruelty do you wish, O Lord\?
What cruelty do you wish, O Lord\?
What cruelty do you wish, O Lord\?
Any man who slacks at the oars will be shorter by a head!
Men! Now is the moment of truth!

I have no intention of letting the enemy take our capital! I have every intention of making them pay for their insolence! And when we are done, we will toast our success with the wine from their camp!
Steady! We can do without artillery.

For long years, these walls have stood, proud and defiant of all enemies! Today is not the day that they will fall! Today is not the day our capital is crushed beneath enemy boots! Today, we hold! And we win!
Oh, Poseidon's gentle trident! Come and stab me now!
That fat bastard on the right. He's mine.
That's not fair. He's the biggest target.
Men, my glorious warriors of Rudianos, stand tall! Be proud for once again we shall fight this day, side by side. And tonight I shall drink you all under the table! Follow me once more into battle!
Oh, for a bed and a warm woman!

By all that you hold sacred, by Cicolluis and Catuboda, fight with me today! You, who know me and know my name is feared by this enemy, bring glory on our people this day. We shall win and we shall be wondered at!
Look, men! Those that did not die run like cowards.
We won, then. How many drowned, do you think\?
It's quick like a fish. Moves like a fish… Sinks like a stone.
Artillery, open fire! Smash the enemy to pieces!
I don't like the look of them…
Foolish, foolish… and very ugly by the looks of them.
Enough for the fishes, lad, enough for them.
Lads! Well done! That one earns you a drink on me!
Battle group ready and awaiting orders!
Ha, ha! I got him! I got him!
This will bring us honour at home!
Battle group ready and awaiting orders!
Well done, lads. But don't get too cocky!
A wind from that direction is ill-news.
This will be a profitable day!
Wind from any direction is bad news…
We rule the waves! Aha! Take that you bastards!
No slacking! Either work or swim! What will it be\?
I am afraid. Not of death, but of drowning…
That'll show them. It's never going to fire again.
Chickens ahoy, lads! May Dagon finish them off!
You smell that\? Enemies always smell real bad!
Bastard inbreds, we needed that equipment!
Come on then! You'll be trying to hide again, soon enough.
Sign up lads, for a good and glorious life!
Sign up lads, for a good and glorious life!
We take this settlement for Rome!
We take this settlement for Rome!
AT THEM! Boarding party to me!
Then make sure you avenge him!
Quit your whining. So we lost some artillery. We still hold!
No, not the artillery! My brother was in there!
Fortune often grows in failure's soil.
Fortune often grows in failure's soil.
A man does not seek his luck, luck seeks its man.
A man does not seek his luck, luck seeks its man.
I offer thanks, great Mars, that you gave us victory!
Men are masters of their fates.
Men are masters of their fates.
The Gods provide us with fresh hope!
The Gods provide us with fresh hope!

You know my reputation: I do not lose battles! The veterans amongst you can attest to this! If you fight with courage, we will win… And the glory, the spoils, will be yours! Fight and we shall be triumphant!
After this we deserve to drown in wine!
Stand still, you slovenly, horrible, useless, crybaby, Greek fop!
Clear the deck of any bodies! To your stations!
Ow! Aaah! Right in the - aaaaah!
Battle is for generals and young men, I'm too old for this.
Your wife won't be happy with that, sir!
Artillery masters! Target their captain, if you please!
This will be a profitable day!
Artillery, pick your target and focus your fire!
Wind from any direction is bad news…
Everyone to their posts! No one shirks their duty!
To your stations! Let's give them a warm welcome!
A wind from that direction is ill-news.
Praise the gods, but that was well done, lads!
Battle group ready and awaiting orders!
I warn you! Any man who falls asleep will be killed on my order!
I'd do anything for an hour's sleep now.
Offer to pleasure the captain and I'm sure he'll oblige.
Battle group ready and awaiting orders!
Nicely done, lads. Raise a cheer!
Barnacles and blisters! Clear these bodies!
Enough for the fishes, lad, enough for them.
We won, then. How many drowned, do you think\?
Keep at it, you dogs! Battle's not over yet!
Keep them at their positions. They must not tire now!
I ache for landfall, deckmaster. More than victory…
These waters are troubled. The gods cursed them long ago.
Mark my words… We'll have to mend it later…
That's not going to fire again.
Could have been worse… Could have been us.
Look out, sir, here comes trouble!
Take aim, fire on the shore!
Make the lazy wretches carry more!
Did you spring from your whore-mothers like that too\?
Make the lazy wretches carry more!
I want every scrap of iron accounted for!
Make a few run the gauntlet!
Make a few run the gauntlet!
I want every scrap of iron accounted for!
The Old Ones have delivered us to these shores now it is our turn to make them proud. Show no mercy today as you cut and cleave! The bards shall write verses of our deeds. Forward to victory, men!

The Britons have always been our noisy neighbours. We share many traditions. Some of our druid priests have worked with theirs. Some of you may share blood relatives. But today we are blood enemies and will fight as such.
Looks like Garm himself is on their side!
Gods damn you! Sink the bastards!
We're going to need a bigger fleet!
We're going to need a bigger fleet!
Our artillery is lost! They've overrun it.
May the gods greet them with women and ale!
We stand on these walls, and we will hold or, by all the gods, I will fling myself off them in despair at our lack of courage. We can hold this place, and we will! Now, stand ready!
Thanks be to Mars! I still live!
Aim for the body! No fancy head shots!
Remember your training! Steady hands and a steady heart!
You heard him, lads! Shoot those bastards down!
We stand here for those who cannot fight, those who rely on us to defend their homes, their families, their gods. This duty may be a heavy burden, but it is a proud one. Now, to arms!
We must not let the enemy cross these walls! We must make them a monument to our bravery, stained with their blood and glorified with our own! Not one step backwards!
We hold these walls today because that is the task the gods have given us! It is a noble task! We will make our gods proud that their people have such sons as us!
Rain shots down on them, men. Aim for their leaders.
These walls are strong, but it is not walls that hold a place! It is strong men with stronger hearts! Men such as you! We will hold this place, no matter what comes against us! Prepare!

You know me, men. You know my reputation. Only the Fates know the outcome of this battle, but I will stake my life, and my reputation on victory. All I ask from you in return is to have courage and to follow orders!

We have won many victories in the past. Some, as your scars show, were harder fought than others. Battle is never easy but, although I promise you more scars, I promise you victory if your courage holds!
I have been here before, many times I have faced battle such as this. Only a fool gives out faint praise and assurances, and I am no fool! We can win this battle! What say you, men\?

I pray to the gods and my ancestors for victory this day. Pray that my leadership is a match for your courage, men! I count myself fortunate, blessed to lead our peoples' finest army in battle! Draw your weapons! And make ready!
Oh, for the old days of honour!

I have led many of you to victory before and, if the gods be willing, I shall lead you to victory this day! Our foe is not unskilled, but they lack your discipline and my leadership. You know your work! Make ready!

No ordinary man can know the future, that is for the gods and oracles to know! But we can win this battle, as we have won many times before! If you fight, if you follow my orders, we can win! Make ready!
If you know me, then you know I do not care for wasted words! We will win, if you will fight! Do that, fight for me today, and I can promise you another victory and your choice of the spoils!

We have stood together like this many times. What words can I say that will lift your spirits\? We are old hands at this! We've tasted victory before and will taste it again today! Draw your swords and make ready, men!
We have been tested before, in battle, and we have not been found wanting. Fight for me this day! Fight for me and I can promise you another victory! Fight for me, men!
All hands! Look! The wind lifts our banners, and our spirits!
This is a battle, and you will act like a soldier of Rome at all times!
All hands! Look! The wind lifts our banners, and our spirits!
Artillery masters! Take your shots in your own time!
Artillery! Do you worst! I want to sink her!
Choose your targets well, focus your fire!
We have the wind and the gods with us. Make ready, men.
Such a shame to think they will all die soon.
You have to be alive to feel the aches, lad…
Battle group ready and awaiting orders!
Rest when you're dead, my old man used to say.
Well, he was a stupid bastard, wasn't he\?
Thank the gods, that improves our chances.
It's fine. It just grazed me…
The battle isn't done, men. We must keep going.
Oarmaster! I know they are tired! Keep the men moving!
That is an end to it… Beyond salvage today!
Bastards! It's going to be much tougher without it.
A tempting target! Let's wait for a moment…

Why have the Moon People sent their celestial peltasts against us\? How can we fight against the heroes of two worlds\? Men, be careful in this coming fight for they are tricksy and invisible! Now, to arms!
There are those who say I have been touched by the gods. There are those who pray that the gods will inspire me in battle! And they all should fear, for I have seen the gods! I know their plans!

You know my reputation and worth, men, as do the enemy. Be courageous and remember this: we have bigger, shinier helmets than them! I promise you that my helmet is regularly polished! It gleams! Now, to arms!
Bloody admiral… He won't be so happy when the bloody Senate bloody gut him like a bloody fish!

Last night I thought long about tactics. And I came to a startling conclusion: quite frankly, men, I don't need you. What I need are some really angry wasps. But for today, you'll have to do! Fly, my pretties!
I see the enemy are wearing lovely hats. It will do them little good, for I have a fearsome gaze that can boil a man's brains inside his skull! Those hats are useless against me! Now, follow!

Sausage! Sausage! SAUSAGE! Now my enemies know that I have come, and they tremble with fear! Sausage! SAUSAGE! See! The fools! They hide their terror behind laughter! Soon they will regret silly smiles! Sausage! SAUSAGE!

Men, it's at times like these that I remember my grandfather's dictum that putting on a dress and a bit of slap solves most military problems. Who is with me\? Please yourselves, then. Fight the boring way!
What can I do for Egypt\?
What can I do for Egypt\?
Get hold of something and hang on, you fool!
Men! Send the enemy to their watery graves!
Oarmaster! Your best men to the helm!
All-Father be praised! How can I help\?
All-Father be praised! How can I help\?
All-Father be praised! How can I help\?
All-Father be praised! How can I help\?
Losing that artillery was a waste… More for us to fight.

Egypt is a land of death, and offers only death to its neighbours! Under their corrupt Pharaoh, the pretender god, they are monsters! Well, today we slay some monsters! Remember the honoured name of Parthia! And do not be found wanting!

There are worse places for battle than defending these walls. Let our foes wear themselves out  coming to us. Let them dash themselves to pieces! Then they will die at our hands! Prepare, then, soldiers!
Take up your arms, you soldiers! We are the shield of our people today, and we will endure this onslaught! Our foes are men of little worth and less courage, so we need have no fear! Only resolution!
Our honoured forefathers paid in blood for their glory and today we have the chance to do the same! Allow no enemy within our defences! Stand firm and never retreat! All will be well!
They will join us, my lord.
They will join us, my lord.
Noble defenders, listen to my words! We stand on the ramparts, ready to sell our lives dearly. If death is the price for victory, so be it! I hope that you live to celebrate victory with me!
May the gods grant us the strength to prevail against our foes, and keep this place for our people! I will bend my every effort to this struggle, and I know you will do the same! We will hold!
Here we stand! We will defend our people and our lands to the last breath. By all the gods, my sword will fall from my cold, dead hand before I retreat! Make the same oath! Be courageous!
Oh the agony and the ecstacy! Their agony, my ecstasy!
Out there, waiting like cowardly dogs, are an enemy keen to plunder our capital! By my honoured blood and ancestors, I will stop them having that satisfaction! We will bar the way! Make ready!

Our enemies mean to march into our capital and utterly overthrow us! They mean to cast down our gods, take our women, enslave our children! This we cannot allow! That is why we will hold these walls to the last gasp! Make ready!
My skills have swayed many men.
My skills have swayed many men.
There's one in the eye for you!
We will hold these walls, or die, men! The enemy cannot set one foot inside the city! Our gods would never forgive us if the capital were violated by filthy invaders! So, we stand! We hold! To arms!
Rome is mother to us all!
Rome is mother to us all!
Rome is mother to us all!
Rome is mother to us all!
Rome is mother to us all!
Rome is mother to us all!
Rome is mother to us all!
Rome is mother to us all!
Rome is mother to us all!
Everyone on this ship, hear me! No quarter to the enemy!
Curse the bastards! They're firing at us!
We must fire back! Or do something!
Really I never would have guessed!
Leave that to the captain, boy. He's seen this a hundred times before.
Artillery masters! Look to your crews, now!
Well, you heard... Get ready to fight!
Don't be too keen, boy. Battle's not going to be pretty.
Don't waste shot, make it all count!
Have them make ready for combat.
So they dare come to us. Today they die!
Sir, sir, sir! Bosun reports that we're being shot at, sir!
Oarmaster! I know they are tired! Keep the men moving!
Battle group ready and awaiting orders!
Come on, old man, there's life in you yet.
That seems to have left a mark... Well done, men.
Pull away or by Yamm, I will whip you!
Leave what… Oh, why's that sticking out my arm\?
Best to leave that for now, boy.
How can I serve the people of Makedon\?
Put your backs into it! Do not slow now!
What does Makedon require of me\?
How can I serve the people of Makedon\?
What does Makedon require of me\?
What does Makedon require of me\?
How can I serve the people of Makedon\?
What does Makedon require of me\?
How can I serve the people of Makedon\?
You have to be alive to feel the aches, lad…
Mark my words, lad, this is going to get worse.
I have carried out your orders.
I have carried out your orders.
By my hand it is done.
By my hand it is done.
May the gods bless our human sacrifice!
By Mithra, that was a good shot! Blew him in half!
What can I do for Egypt\?
What can I do for Egypt\?
What can I do for Egypt\?
What can I do for Egypt\?
Put some effort into it! Smash them!
Hold tight! This is going to be nasty!
There's still hope, men. See, the admiral continues to fight!
Bet he has a fast ship waiting though…
Let them go! Taranis and his thunderbolts shall provide!
Without that artillery this is going to be a bloody day for us.
A dagger to the throat, a gentle word…
A dagger to the throat, a gentle word…
He'll be our man when I'm done with him!
He'll be our man when I'm done with him!
I'm not what you might call subtle, but…
I'm not what you might call subtle, but…
Get here! I have something to tell you!
Get here! I have something to tell you!
They will join us, or die!
They will join us, or die!
People tend to agree with a sharp blade.
People tend to agree with a sharp blade.
I don't need words to persuade 'em!
I don't need words to persuade 'em!
Aim for their standard! Weaken the centre!
Surprise is ours! We have caught them off guard! Attack!
Show no mercy, men! Attack! Attack, before they can reform!
Now, men! Attack! We have caught them unprepared!
Do not give them chance to regroup! Attack! Kill them all!
Attack! Show no mercy! Give them no chance to regroup!
Put them all to the sword! Run down any that flee! Attack!
Praise the gods, that was well done! Now attack! Kill these dogs!
Praise our ancestors, that was done well… Now, attack! Show no mercy!
Our ambush has worked! Attack! Attack, before they can regroup!
To me! In Jupiter's name! HELP!
Bunch of cheating, cowardly scabs! How dare they!
Nodens spare us, if our hearts should sink.
Artillery masters! Look to your crews, now!
Fire! Blast them all to the underworld!
I want to see their decks painted with blood and guts!
Open fire! Make our artillery count, men!
Look to your work, men. They're coming in.
Always nice when what you shoot is done for, lad…
I didn't like the look of it anyway.
Wake up! I don't care how tired you are!
Can I see you nodding off at the back there\? Wake up!
She's gone! The bastards are all dead!
They never knew what hit them!
Stop skulking! Stay at your posts!
Don't stop! Not until your backs break and your hearts burst!
Good! That can't be repaired without a god's aid!
That's going to make this tough, but we have our orders.
By Ahura Mazda, they go to their deaths.
You heard the captain! Steady now!
Make ready all weapons, men! Take aim…
Bathe in their blood, boys! The gods are thirsty today!
gods of the seas! Drown our admiral so that we may win!
We must be as cruel as the sharks! No mercy!
That would be our glorious admiral!
What fool let that happen to the artillery\?
Another remark like that, and I'll have you flayed alive.
We're all safer without them! Fight on!
Fire! Bring those cursed dogs down!
We have them, men! Surprise is ours! Attack! Attack!
Aye. Some of us noticed that!
We have them now! Attack, men! Attack! Put them to the sword!
We have the element of surprise! Attack! Slaughter them all!
Swiftly, men! Attack! Attack, before they can regroup!
With me, men! Attack! Let us put these dogs to the sword!
We have them, men! Surprise is ours! Put them to the sword!
I'm hit! They've bloody hit me!
What orders, sir\? We can't just sit here while they attack!
It's only a scrath! Stop your moaning.
Blow the filthy scum out of the water!
Our artillery will smash them to pieces!
Put your backs into it! We're drawing close now.
Wait til you see the whites of their pathetic, putrid eyes.
Nicely done, you men! Now, what's next\?
May sea-worms gnaw at their guts for a thousand years!
Battle group ready and awaiting orders!
Someone hit that man! Hard! Wake him up!
Battle group ready and awaiting orders!
They won't be troubling us again!
Look! The artillery! They got it!
What do you mean\? That went right through your leg!
You're doing better than the last… He'd dropped dead by now!
Wake up! I don't care how tired you are!
Leave nothing that can be used.
The bastards! They've destroyed the machine!
Tritons of the deep! I give myself to your care!
Strip the dead of weapons and armour!
Let them come a little closer, I think… Make ready!
Watch it, lads, the enemy is here! Courage now!
May Sunna shine bright for us today! This is their last army, friends. This is all they have left. Vanquish them and we shall wipe them out. Then we can drink til dawn in celebration!

By Andarta they look strange! I have never seen such extraordinary looking soldiers. They are probably all mercenaries or slaves of Pontus. We shall vanquish them and drive them from here. Get ready men!
We were going to have to fight anyway.
They've helped but... Now we fight without them.
It'll take more than that to kill me!
It'll take more than that to kill me!
Not quite a you ordered, but close my lord.
Not quite a you ordered, but close my lord.
Well, that worked out in the end!
Well, that worked out in the end!
Well, that worked out alright in the end!
Well, that worked out alright in the end!
Jupiter's warlike visage! Is there anything to drink\?
Well, it's not all bad, my lord.
Well, it's not all bad, my lord.
Just like I planned, sort of…
Success and failure often walk hand in hand.
Just like I planned, sort of…
Success and failure often walk hand in hand.
Fire! Take down those barbarian scum.
I would walk to the Otherworld for my tribe.
I would walk to the Otherworld for my tribe.
I really fancy a bite of cheese. And some fresh bread.
Bastard's hit me! I've can't use my sword arm!
Damage party! Get to work, you lubbers!
You! Stop bleeding on my deck!
Stop hauling, you louts, and prepare to fight!
Stop hauling, you louts, and prepare to fight!
I don't want to die like this! I'd rather drown!
Are you a Greek\? Are you\? Stop that screaming!
Artillery crews, look to your machines!
May the gods favour us with victory... Make ready now!
Right boys, let's get ready for battle.
Stop! Have a breather, men, and well done!
Praise the gods, but that was well done, lads!
Battle group ready and awaiting orders!
Pray next time is as easy, boy.
By the gods, I'm knackered! I've just about had enough.
There she goes! Down to the watery depths!
May the gods honour you , sir!
Battle group ready and awaiting orders!
We did it! That showed them!
You heard the captain! Keep at it!
Bugger me! They're dropping like flies. Praise Anath!
I know you're tired, men. But we must push on.
May Ran gather them quickly in her nets.
We can still take them, men. Have faith!
Well, here's a good day and no mistake!
Take aim, fire on the shore!
You fire when the officer gives an order, not before!
These waters are spoiled, man. The enemy still float on them!
Steady! We can take them! Make ready!
Mithra! With this vanquished enemy we honour you!
We will hear the lamentation of their women!
Burn or steal, but take it from them!
We will hear the lamentation of their women!
Burn or steal, but take it from them!
They will never see it coming.
They will never see it coming.
Charge like the bear! Cut them down!
What cruelty do you wish, O Lord\?
What cruelty do you wish, O Lord\?
I am a spirit of the forest…
I am a spirit of the forest…
They won't miss a few men…
They won't miss a few men…
At least the scum didn't start firing it at us.
Choose your man and kill him!
This'll slice through them. They won't feel a thing.
Follow the man in front… Fire!
Slice them into pieces and feed them to the fish, men!
Stones and arrows cannot sink this ship!
No, but they can kill us, you fool!
Choose your targets! Fire at will!
May the sea gods favour us… As I don't like our chances.
Just as I thought, they want to fight. Let's rip them open, men!
How do we know which one's Will\? Stupid name anyway…
Battle group ready and awaiting orders!
Keep those men awake! Whip them if they slacken!
That's it! She's down! Good work!
Battle group ready and awaiting orders!
Well done! That will not trouble us again.
Haephestus pisses on my hopes! We needed that machine!
You can rest when the battle's done... Or when you're dead.
I can't… I can't take anymore…
I bet Neptune's scaley arse was sore after he'd shat you out!
Good news, lads! That won't be firing again.
Well, here's a good day and no mistake!
We try again... And we keep trying until we make it.
Sir, I have seen prawns with more fight in them, sir.
That ship! It still floats! Why\?
They're springing out of the ground now!
You! Fight! Or I'll feed you to the fish myself!
Are there any women here\? Or are you warriors\?
Dead or alive, push them into the water! Take the ship, men!

Honoured sons of Carthage, do not be unnerved by this Gallic wailing! Their whining is annoying, rather like their women! As Ba'al is my witness, I swear we will crush them if we but hold a line! For Carthage!
I did not come here to see Rome's honour shamed. No, like you I came for victory. I will not leave this place with less than victory. This I victory promise to you!
I will speak honestly, for as soldiers of mine you deserve honesty. I want, and need, you to fight as though the Furies themselves were your leaders! We will shock the enemy into defeat! To arms!
Quite, sir. Good luck with that.
In battle, men, bravery is a good quality for a soldier to have! But better yet, is a sense of duty, duty to his comrades, his officers and to his people. Remember your duties, and fight hard!
Cavalrymen! Ha! The horses are usually in charge!
Shall we start getting the men ready, sir\?
Do you think they've ever heard of washing\?
Now is my hour of glory!
Don't call me sir"! I fight for a living!"
Sir, wine, sir\? Good as can be, considering.
Come on, lads. A last effort for our glorious admiral!
I live to serve the people of Gaul!
Honour the gods and your ancestors!
Gaul is mother to us all!
Oh, gods, we pray to you so that you may look favourably on our efforts here today. May the world hear of our deeds and know that we did our utmost against a most cruel enemy!
Praise be to the gods of war! They see us now in our defence of this place and these walls. Take up your weapons and defend your people here! Do not falter. Do not leave your post!
It is our task to defend these walls. Forget all that has gone before. This is all that matters now. For the homeland! Fight, slice and behead these invaders. Protect the walls at all cost!
Look at this angry, ugly lot. They look like they'll stab you in the back as soon as blink. Well, I suppose we owe it to the ancestors to defend them. So get to your positions!
I am proud to lead the defence of this seige today! I know most of you well, some are great friends. I do not want to lose a single life in this battle. So make ready!

I know you all have waited for this moment. I wish I could serve up a nobler enemy but this lot will have to do. Be prepared, get angry and enjoy yourselves. There's nowhere to run so don't let them get in!
Slice off their heads and let's have 'em for dinner!
Smells like that Roman piss… Grum…
Garum\? That'll be all the open bellies and guts, boy.
Get them moving, if you please!
Yes, I kind of hoped for that.
It's not us I'm worried about!
I look for enemies worthy of my sword!
Everyone is scared! DON'T worry! FIGHT!
Were you expecting a quiet cruise up the Tiber\?
Bastards! I will cut out your hearts and eat them!
Yeah! That's what we want to see. The end of the artillery!
By Sucellos! Dis Pater! They're lost!
Get over it! We fight on!
I will cut down any man who runs!
Attack, men! Storm their ship, take no prisoners!
My legates have pledged a glorious victory here today! I like their confidence in you, men, I like it! Such confidence will, I am sure, be entirely justified by what you achieve today! Onwards!
Do you ever stop thinking about your stomach\?
Thanks. I feel so much better now.
Now, men, we are come to a battle again, and on ground of my choosing, at a time of my choosing. I would not have brought you here without absolute confidence in you! Now, to arms!
Do not shame the gods today! Fight!
Kill them, and I'll buy you as many whores... as you can eat!
A nice cheese. And some wine. That's what I want.
Death is coming. For the lucky ones!
Shall we start getting ready, sir\?
Our foes sneer at our honest, plain, Roman virtues. They sneer at our gods, our Senators, our people… Their contempt for Rome has no limits. So what\? Soon, we will have victory!
Glory to the gods! The admiral! He means to win or die!
We will stand! We will hold! And we will WIN!
To the standards! Here we hold! Here we may die! But here we fight!
To the standards! To the standards! Not one step back!
Right, men, form up! Form up! We can hold them off!
Steady! We can win this! Keep your heads and kill the buggers!
Look to your mates, men! Look to your leaders! Stand! And hold!
Right! We have a fight on our hands! Steady, men, steady!
Hold them off, men! Stand firm! We will win!
Keep together! Look to your comrades! Fight hard!
A cup of ale, a starry sky...
A cup of ale, a starry sky...
They will be unable to resist.
They will be unable to resist.
I can twist many a word.
I can twist many a word.
I know tricks no mortal woman should...
I know tricks no mortal woman should...
For our ancestors! For the gods!
They'll sell their own mothers when I'm done.
They'll sell their own mothers when I'm done.
Fight! You are sailors, but you are warriors also!
Rome is mother to us all!
Rome is mother to us all!
Rome is mother to us all!
Rome is mother to us all!
Rome is mother to us all!
By all that's sacred to Ankou! Let's fight to the death!
I look for enemies worthy of my sword!
Everyone is scared! DON'T worry! FIGHT!
Careful with that! You'll have someone's eye out!
It's not us I'm worried about!
Baduhunna give us strength to take on this perilous foe. We stand against the might of Rome and we ask you for aid in these coming hours. We ask for your blessing, oh, great Baduhunna!
Wine for the man who kills a standard bearer!
Get them moving, if you please!
When an order is given DO NOT hang about!
Wine for the man who kills a standard bearer!
Neptune's fishy beard! That was close!
So was your dad! But I got a refund!
Oi! I had your mum! She was rubbish!
Oi! I had your mum! She was shit!
There are Roman wounded to look after! Your gold can wait, Mars curse you!
Neptune's bloody trident! Are they stupid\?
My father was killed by artillery. I hope they burn!
Aye, any help gratefully received, you hairy divine bugger!
Any man who drops out is left behind!
March until your feet bleed! Then march some more!
I don't care how tired you are!
You will march 'til your feet bleed!
That's it! Can't face us like honest warriors.
You may as well get settled in, lads!
You may as well get settled in, lads!
Romans! Grip your weapons, lift your shields and prepare to meet death once again! But do not fear death! He is your friend, your ally- no, your brother! Let your enemies fear death!
They will never see it coming.
They will never see it coming.
Romans, you noblest of men! You are the sons of Aeneas and of Romulus, the step-children of the wolf! Do not consider anything other than how you will celebrate victory! And it will be yours!
Romans! I pray that to Mars there are enough enemies for us all to gain a little honour! Listen for commands and obey as you would your fathers! Then we will have victory!
They won't miss a few men…
They won't miss a few men…
Soldiers of Rome! I expect only victory, no matter how hard won, because that is our duty. And we are nothing without duty or honour. That is why we will triumph! Now, forwards!
Do you talk about anything except drink and death\?
Shut it. You're upsetting the lads!
Not surprised, the way you eat!
So do I. Your cooking's rubbish!
Soldiers of Rome! Hear my orders! Let your watchword be Obedience!" Without duty, you are lost! With it, you cannot be beaten! That is all that I need to say! Now, prepare your weapons!"
I am a spirit of the forest…
I am a spirit of the forest…
Any man who dies will answer to me at tomorrow's roll call!
Seniors! Look to your men now!
By my honour, I am getting a little bored.
A good cup of wine! That's what's needed before the end!
Can you feel it\? The ghosts here are troubled!
I wish my old mother was here.
Stand proud, you sons of Rome, you favoured of Mars! Our enemies shake at the sight of you! Let duty and obedience be your watchwords, and victory will be ours to enjoy!
See, the admiral! He looks completely knackered!
The admiral's hard pressed now. May the gods guide him!
Over there! It's the admiral. Nice helmet, I'll give him that.
Ankou! Welcome us, god of death!
Form up! Form up! Defensive positions! NOW!
Form! Watch your flanks! Watch to your rear! And fight!

Our great forefathers built this city. We fight now to defend this sacred earth. Defend these walls with your lives! And if they are breached and we are forced to fight in the streets, then repel the invaders!
By all the gods, where- what- Men! Hold them!

Today these bastards mean to sack our capital. They think they can breach these walls and come among our homeland families, our temples and our shrines. We shall not stand for this arrogance! They shall suffer for it!

These Seleucid curs march under their masters' whips. Their courage" is fear-inspired and easily broken! We shall inspire such terror in them that they will turn on their masters and drag them down in their haste to flee!"
Fight, curse you all, fight! We will not be beaten! I will not be beaten!

They make a fine spectacle, do they not\? But believe me, men, we have little to fear from these Seleucid pretenders. They are not soldiers like us, but perfumed caravan guards, or unwashed peasants. We shall break their spirit and run them down!
Ambushed! By the gods! Ambushed! Very well! Men, hold them!

They think themselves heirs of Alexander, but these Seleucids are shadows of his glory. We shall drive back this rabble of pretenders and unwashed peasants, and put an end to their arrogance! Make ready!
Blood of my ancestors! That was clever! Right, men, hold them! And then kill them!
Neptune's blood, man! Fight! This is your moment!

We face parade-ground guards, poor farmers, unwashed brigands and thieves: the sum of Seleucid greatness arrayed against us! There is not a true soldier amongst them! Let us put these pretenders to the sword, and steal the baggage!
Shut it, you dogs. Keep quiet.
Praise be to Tyr! Rich pickings today!
Ares' amazingly large spear! We have to fight them\?
Fight, curse your gizzards, or you are shark meat!
Right now, I could use a cup of good wine!
Dead or alive, push them into the water, boy!
Don't wave that sword around near me, you fool!
I have drunk deep of wisdom's cup.
Gather round, I have much to teach you.
I know what is best for our people.
Gather round, I have much to teach you.
I know what is best for our people.
Like the oak, our roots go deep.
Gather round, I have much to teach you.
I have drunk deep of wisdom's cup.
I know what is best for our people.
The Goddess will watch over us.
The Goddess will watch over us.
I know what is best for our people.
The Gods will watch over us.
Like the oak, our roots go deep.
The Gods will watch over us.
Gather round, I have much to teach you.
If we die, there is no shame! There is shame only in running!
I think they've taken a bit of a dislike to us, don't you\?
If we die, there is no shame! There is shame only in running!
Somebody kill that moaning bastard! NOW!
Wondered when he'd get round to that…
Stand fast, men, stand fast! Faith and honour!
Neptune boil them in garum! They ARE sailors!
Neptune curse them! They are good!
Any man who drops out is left behind!
Come on, you inbred bastards! We'll feed you to the fish!
Fight like the boar, my friends! We've lost the seige equipment!
March until your feet bleed! Then march some more!
I don't care how tired you are!
Come on, men! Imagine it's me over there on their deck!
You will march 'til your feet bleed!
That's a pity. I think we needed that.
They will trouble you no longer.
They will trouble you no longer.
I shall bring you their liver and lights.
I shall bring you their liver and lights.
Ares curse their eyes and entrails! We needed that siege gear!
Save an enemy for me! I will boil him with the crabs!
Attack! Let's take the fight to them!

The gods have spoken! The omens are right! This is a day of battle! It will be a day long remembered for our victory! Now, stand ready, stand as proud soldiers, watch for the enemy! Make ready to strike!

When we are done here today the survivors will pale every time they hear Greek spoken. The few foes who live through this day will suffer afresh all the horrors that we will inflict! Now, to the walls!
We stand here for Rome, the Senate and our families! All of them expect great things today! None of them will be disappointed, for I have every confidence in your bravery! Now, to arms!
No! The pointy end towards the enemy!
I will stand here until ordered!
You! This wine cup is dirty! Get me a clean one!
Breakfast, sir, might be your last chance!
What can I do for Egypt\?
What can I do for Egypt\?
The admiral looks like he's lost the battle already.

Let us put an end to these Seleucid pretenders, to their army of Persian and Greek peasants, and claim the rich pickings of their baggage train! Give me victory today, men, and I give you the spoils of battle! Make ready!

Perfumed fools playing at nobility, and unwashed brigands whipped into service: that is the true measure of the Seleucids! It will be an easy task to dispatch them, men, and their rich baggage train shall be your reward!
It's not rose blossom, that's for sure…
What on earth is that SMELL\?

Do not be disheartened, men! This Seleucid army is no more than a rabble of brigands, thieves and vagabonds! They were bought with Seleucid coin and are easily put to flight! We will loot the corpses of their rich paymasters!
This is never going to work…
Insolent pretenders, they are no more heirs of Alexander than the rotting Greek states! We shall put an end to their arrogance, drive these painted pretenders back to their hovels! To arms!
Sir, shall we kill them all now\?
Come on! Face me! I'll drag you down to the depths!
Take their ship, you curs! Send the filth into the black depths!

Long has Carthage claimed domination but today we will overthrow their might! We will destroy them and add to the lustre of divine Pharaoh's rule! Let them run all the way back to their foul city! To arms!
Better to push them down, boy, and stay up here.
Wondered when he'd get round to that…
Keep your aim low! Hit them in the centre of the body!
I want them driven off! Keep at it!
I want them driven off! Keep at it!
No! No! This is most unfair!
Leave him! Leave him! He's dead!
He's got a right nasty streak…
Let us make a thousand orphans!
Don't wave that sword around near me, you fool!
How can I serve the people of Makedon\?
What does Makedon require of me\?
What does Makedon require of me\?
How can I serve the people of Makedon\?
At last no more of that artillery! Praise Andarta!
That's a pity. I think we needed that.
Come on, you bastards! Come on! Or row that wreck back home!
How do we loot cities now!
We'll use your arse to blow the walls down!
Curse them! Can we win now\?
Thank the gods! We don't have to put up with more crap coming this way!
Bugger me sideways with a battering ram! They got it!
The Gods honour me with success!
The Gods honour me with success!
Let them feel the wrath of Garm!
What! Where did those bastards come from\? Get your weapons out! Defend yourselves!
Quick, my beauties! Make it quick! For Camalus!
Treachery! Infamy! Misery! Buggery! It's all here! Defend yourselves!
Protect your general! Form around me, you hairy bastards! Don't let them get me!
On me! Defend this position from this evil cunning. Defend your leader!
Have at them! Now! Heave the dead over the side!
Shit! Bloody cowards! Stick together now. Do not get separated. Fight!
Quickly, men! Defend yourselves. We're being attacked by some bastard, cheating, cowardly whoresons!
Take no prisoners! Send them all to a watery grave.
It's the only way they could hope to beat us! Make them pay!
It's a trap! By the gods, I hate deception of any kind! Fight back!
Oh, you cruel gods! Why have you foresaken us\? Protect us from this trap!
Move, move! Form a big circle, or a square, or something! Or we're done for!
That's nice, sir. For your family and all…
Do you ever stop thinking about your belly\?
My respects, sir, stop wriggling and relieve yourself.
I shall make my family proud today.
You! Dirty armour and is that RUST\? You dare spoil my unit!
I've done things you wouldn't believe.
Fish pie. That's what I fancy. Yes.
Good manners prevent me speaking ill of the admiral…
Get ready, men. Won't be long now.
Fight! Send them to the depths, men!
Ancestors! Watch me, and be proud!
Keep your aim low! Hit them in the centre of the body!
Sir! Stand aside, now, there's a good patrician!
Not what you said last night!
Hang on to anything that will float!
Swim! If you drown, you cannot take revenge!
Keep your men in order, until I give the word!
Keep your men in order, until I give the word!
Why did I ever leave the wife\? She wasn't this bad!
Germans! We come up against the mysterious east today in the army of Pontus! I cannot tell you they will be an easy foe but I can say they will scream the same as everyone when you cut them in half!
Ohhh! You dirty bastard! Clean that up!
Three days I floated on that wreckage… Nothing to eat or drink...
I think I'm seasick. Yes I'm definitely going to - Urgggghh!
All right! Very funny! Which one of you buggers has nicked my armbands\?
Cheer up, men! Think of the looting to be had!
Cheer up! They can only sink us once!
Bastards! They got to the siege equipment, curse them!
Bath the earth with their blood!
We are going to cut the flesh from your bones and feed it to the fish!
You're not worthy to be on these waters! Prepare to die, you fools!
Come on, men! For the glory of Carthage!
At least we're not upwind of those stinking sons of tripe!
To your posts! Make ready to fight!

Bloody Germanic bastards! Look at them! Think they own the place! I want them skinned alive and dragged along by their balls until they die. I hate the arrogant sods! To arms, men! And let's get this done!

Our people, the Suffets, the Hundred and Four, they look to us, look to us to fulfil our duty and oaths! Would you dishonour them\? Would you dishonour Carthage\? Our enemy may outnumber us, but it is our sacred duty to fight or die!
Kill or be killed, boy! What will it be\?
What\? Can they not face us in the open field! Cowards! Defend your position!
I'll take the first, old man.
They will come to fear the shadows.
They will come to fear the shadows.
They will never see it coming.
They will never see it coming.
They won't miss a few men…
They won't miss a few men…
Let's make sure they go well instead!
Waste of a woman, if'n you ask me.
I will come from the shadows…
I will come from the shadows…

These fish may have slipped through the nets of our fleet, but now we will throw them back into the water. Sons of Carthage, let us drive these beasts from our shores, and send them to a watery grave!
I will kill any man who shows fear or mercy!
With respect, sir, stop wriggling and go relieve yourself.
Any chance of rain, do you think\?
Will you give my eulogy, if things go badly\?
Bah! The enemy are scurrying rats! Nothing more!
I will not go to my death quietly!
Did you hear about their general and that…
By Neptune's very pointed trident! Make sure it hurts!
Put your last drop of blood into it, men! The admiral's watching!
When this battle is done the name Roman" will be a by-word for valour or- Ha!- I will call myself a Vestal and retire to the Temple! Now, let us take this place!"
Can't wait to see their faces.
This is nice and cosy, eh\?
Fight or swim\? Not much of a choice.
Somebody kill that moaning bastard! NOW!
Front rank! STAND STILL, Jupiter CURSE YOU!
Get rid of that, man! It will drag you down!
There is much to be said for the old ways!
Ancestors! Watch me, and be proud!
Your very best, now, men- ATTACK!
How can I serve the people of Makedon\?
What does Makedon require of me\?
How can I serve the people of Makedon\?
What does Makedon require of me\?
What does Makedon require of me\?
How can I serve the people of Makedon\?
What does Makedon require of me\?
How can I serve the people of Makedon\?
And, like fishing, wine speeds that wait.
We have no choice but to survive, men! We are the chosen ones. For whatever reason, the gods have decided we are the last of our kind and we must fight for all our people!
Like fishing, we wait for the right moment.
Fish... fish and oh, look, there's some more bloody fish. Sick of them, I am.
Bath the earth with their blood!
Come on, you cowards! Let's be 'aving ya!
I hope you can all swim!
I look out at your tired, worn faces and I see your scars and battle wounds. You have done much. I feel your pain. But now we are the last and you must rise again to the challenge!
Brave warriors! Think now of your home, your families, your children! For now we fight as one, the last army and their final hope. Raise up your weapons one more time. And let us storm to victory!
So it has come down to us, my brothers! You great warriors have fought many battles and spilled much blood. I ask you to do so once more! Fight for your futures!
If we must we will fall here today and die honourable deaths. Curse the gods for they have forsaken us! We are alone now. There is only us left. And I have never been more proud!
Oi! Have you come for a fight, or just to look at real sailors\?
Come on, men! Imagine it's me over there on their deck!
We are the last of us! The final warriors in the way of this enemy. I have never been prouder of leading such men. I know whether you live or die today you will make the gods proud too!
We are in great danger, my brothers! We stand as the final few. When we fall there is no one left to pick up our banner and fight on in our people's name. All ends with us! So we must prevail!
My mission was a resounding success!
My mission was a resounding success!
Bastards! They got to the siege equipment, curse them!
Bath the earth with their blood!
Fate awaits us, brothers! See you on the other side!
I'll see them, they'll never see me.
I'll see them, they'll never see me.
Sir! Wanted a life of adventure, sir!
So I've been repeatedly told, sir…
Just a load of old women round here, sir!
And too many well-fed crows, I think…
I will kill any man I see with mercy in his heart!
Why are you here, you unwashed goat\?
A swallow of wine always steadies the hand!
I have yet to see a truly beautiful woman…
Who gave that man permission to relieve himself\?
Bad place to die. Spirits aren't quiet here.
I always hate fighting in weather like this!
There he is. Our admiral. Bloody great loser.
Keep it quiet. We're going to remain here, unseen.
What\? Just like Ahura Mazda riding in the sacred chariot\?
I shall deliver them to you, my lord.
I shall deliver them to you, my lord.
I shall do what I must.
I shall do what I must.
They will be yours, my lord.
They will be yours, my lord.
They will soon be yours, my lord.
They will soon be yours, my lord.
Ambush! Look to your weapons and not the enemy! Make ready!
They will soon forget their allegiance.
They will soon forget their allegiance.
Ambush! Look to the enemy, men! Form up for battle!
A woman's words can be, persuasive…
A woman's words can be, persuasive…
Ambush! Form up, men! Form up, and face the enemy!
Ambush! Form up, men! Form up and face the enemy! Move or all is lost!
Over the side with their corpses!
Fight, you scum! There's nowhere to run.
That's true… Unless they can swim.
On my command: kill them all!
If they want a fight, they've come to the right people!
Well jump in the sea, then, you flaming fool!
I don't want to burn! Not that!
Shut up, you great, big, trouser-wearing, Greek,  girly, Gaul-fondling, nancy, fop!
A reward to any man who takes an officer's plume!
Best learn quick then, you fool!
Excellent! Destroying that artillery is no small victory!
Unleash Garm, the hound of hell. Let him loose, boys!
Do not anger Neverita! Act with respect! We need no storms!
Hold, men! Stand fast! They cannot beat us even by cowardly surprise!
Form up! Quickly! Move! It's an ambush! Wake up you fools!
Ambush! Be strong! Protect your brothers. Watch your flanks and stand firm!
Any man who flinches will feel my sword!
Arse! We're being attacked! Quickly form a defence! I will not die today!
I give my light, to dead men…
I give my light, to dead men…
Ambush! Don't panic! Whatever you do, don't panic! Aaaaahhh, they're coming for us!
Come my brothers, with the strength of Camulus, let us civilise these poor Greeks. Get them over your knee and spank them. On second thoughts they might enjoy that! Best just kill them!
Don't hold back! Any that do will feel my sword!
What cruelty do you wish, O Lord\?
By Jupiter, rarely have I felt so confident before a battle! With men such as you under my command, why should I feel any different\? Good luck, sons of Mars! Good hunting!
And the bloody horrible wine! Undrinkable muck!
Shhh! He's an officer, and better than us.
You are definitely mental, my lad…
By Jupiter, Mars and all the gods! Our foes are insolent, to stand against us, the might of Rome! Have they no sense\? Or do they crave death as the drunkard craves wine\?
Foreign scum! Why do they have to go to war against us\? Do they never realise that they will die, unloved by their gods\? That their wives and children will suffer in slavery\? Well, let's to it…

Do not think of anything today except your duty and your loyalty! The enemy are as nothing, a mere inconvenience! Pray to the gods, by all means, but pray for the strength to do your duty! Now, to arms!
A good cup of wine. In my villa. That's what I want.
What's going on, then\? You men\?
Bad place to die. Long way from home…
Horrible barbarian country. Horrible barbarian women. Horrible barbarian food…
I've been thinking. Would you strike a holy man\?
Did his mother repeatedly drop him on his head\?
You know, it's at times like this I quite miss home cooking…
Gods of our enemies! Listen to me! I pledge you my victory today! Turn your backs on your unworthy followers and support our efforts! Be honoured by us, and know what honour means!
See there! The admiral still stands! Now, let's make him proud!
Send them to Isis. May the fish knaw their nads!
Swords, my boys! Swords! They are upon us!
Charge! Kill them! Kill them all!
They're upon us! But do not fear! Form ranks, men! Form up and face them!
They have stolen a march on us! Form up, men! Form up for battle!
Move you, dogs! Move or all is lost! Make ready, and form up for battle!
Make haste! Look to the enemy, men! Form up to face them!
Hold! Do not panic! Form up and face the enemy! Move!
Hold you, dogs! Hold, and form ranks to face them! Move!
Form up, and keep order! Face the enemy, and be ready!
Fight! Take their ship or send them down.
Form up! Form up and face the enemy! Make ready, men!
Do not panic! Form up you, dogs! Form up and face the enemy!
Do not let fear take you! Form ranks, men! Face the enemy!
A reward to any man who takes an officer's plume!
Well, kiss my lobster's arse and call me Julia, we've won!
Thank you. Deal with it, there's a good man.
Sir! We're on fire. Thought you'd like to know, sir!
Enemies! Bah! The smell always upsets my digestion!
When we move, we do so at the trot!
Soldier, if you need to fear, FEAR ME!

By Jupiter, we are enough to stand and fight, like true Romans. If we must die today, then we will die like Romans, with defiance in our hearts! We will show these fools Roman virtue! Now, make ready!
If you can, swim for land!
I cannot feel my legs! Help!
On my command: kill them all!
If they want a fight, they've come to the right people!
Excellent! Destroying that artillery is no small victory!
Rome does not send its sons to sea so they can drown, man!
Tomorrow Sulis will bathe us in her warmth! Fight On!
Our honoured ancestors are watching today! We have a proud tradition of courage, honour and bravery to match and I know that you will not be found wanting! Now, the hour approaches! Make ready!
Someone bring me a fresh toga, I'm filthy.
Someone bring me a fresh toga, I'm filthy.
Our enemies fight today are on the defensive, on our terms, not theirs. This gives us the advantage, and I will use it to the full. Follow orders, and we will soon sweep them from the field!
I would sit and read my scrolls awhile.
I would sit and read my scrolls awhile.
I must bathe, for the road was long and dusty.
I must bathe, for the road was long and dusty.
They will learn to fear the shadows.
They will learn to fear the shadows.
Where can I get a good stuffed lark\?
Where can I get a good stuffed lark\?
No matter who we meet in battle we will triumph, for we honour the gods. Even if every foe had the strength of a thousand men, it would mean nothing! Remember that, are make ready!
I shall take a moment to rest.
I shall take a moment to rest.
The enemy must never know rest!
The enemy must never know rest!
They will learn to fear us!
They will learn to fear us!
Men, I ask no more of you today than I ask of myself. I ask you to fight! I may ask you to die! But you know I ask this for one, simple reason: victory!
I think I just stuck my elbow in something nasty…
Men! Pray to the gods, and ask for their help in battle! A strong heart and a prayer helps our cause as much as a sharp sword! Pray to the enemy gods too, for all aid is welcome!
All the way from our sacred shores to this putrid city. I am told there is much wealth inside so when we are done loot as much as you like! Onward and take Carthage!

Britons! We stand against the might of Parthia. Sent by demons of the underworld they strike fear in most armies. The sound of their horns make most warriors shake with terror. Are you afraid, my brothers\? Never!
Gut these wretches! Feed them their own guts!
Stop squeaking like a girl and help put it out!
Work quickly, men! Get those flames out!
Mark your targets when they come!
Do not rush! There's time to kill them properly!
Lift the standards high! Now, for glory!
Hold on tight, lads! And pray!
Hold on to your sword, there!
Sir, the enemy really do mean to kill us.
Hold on tight, lads! And pray!
Hold on to your sword, there!
The bastards! They are fighting back!
May Dagon grant them quick deaths.
Be ready, men, but rest while you can.
I think I've just found my sea legs, you know.
Nothing to report, sir. Everything is shipshape.
I need a drink. Several drinks. A skinful of good wine…
The sea is best left to fishermen. Warriors have no business there.
Bath the earth with their blood!
Now we can all calm down and stop worrying about that artillery.
My father was there! Damn them! Curse their cowardly blood!
You look like you've been at sea a long time. Want to suck on my sword\?
Did you just call his mother a haddock\?
Draw swords! Let us make ready!
They sail too well for my liking.
Draw swords! Let us make ready!
Make your final checks! Then say your final prayers.
Let's pray they're not too big a fish.
Brave Tyr! Guide my arm today!

Men! I have taken the advice of the seers and oracles, and brought you to this place for battle! I now give you over into the care of the gods, who will grant us victory against our vile foes! Make ready!
It may be beneath my dignity to say this, but gods above! Our foes are simpletons and bumpkins! Truly, the enemy have emptied many villages of their idiots and sent them to die at our hands!
I don't rest, but I will stop awhile.
I don't rest, but I will stop awhile.
If we are marked for death today, let us meet our fates with good humour trusting to the will of the gods. If we are marked for victory, then we shall celebrate in the same vein! To arms!
I thank my ancestors that they have given us an easy path to victory today! See: the enemy are weak, and we are strong. Do not cast aside this opportunity for an easy victory! Make ready!
Now: some food and good company!
Now: some food and good company!
Not like us to hide our faces.
I look around and I am proud to be your general. Any soldier would say the same! Courage is in every one of you! That, my friends, is why I am confident of victory!
I have prayed for a victory today. I have consulted oracles, and witnessed omens, and through them I know the gods have given me brave men to lead in battle! Now, forwards! Victory awaits!
You should try it more often.
I want silence amongst the men. It is vital we remain unseen.
For the people! And our gods!
Clear the dead! Over the side with them!
Help the wounded back to the surgeons! Look for gold after that!
Be happy! No more marching today!
Fight, you ship-rats! As the gods watch us... Fight!
Neptune's big pointy trident! We've won!
Oi! Your mother still working cemeteries\?
Wait! Wait until you can see their piggy little eyes!
Come on! Come on! You march like old women!
We still have a good wind!
Good fortune to you all, and all our comrades!
Sir! Take care, I beg you!
Good fortune to you all, and all our comrades!
I want to go back to the fields!
Swords, men, swords! Have at them!
Some say that makes you a lucky bugger.
Be ready, lads. Our waiting is almost done.
Aw… another bloody gull shat on my head!
Sir, we are ready for a weapon drill anytime.
Carpenter sends word, sir. His men are ready.
The Captain\? He's as caring and kind as a shark!
Soldiers should be on dry land. This is unnatural!
Bath the earth with their blood!
Aye, but he wins, the bugger!
We'll guts you for the birds, you bastards!
Bloody pointless anyway! We fight with our hands if we need to!
If I was you I'd start saying goodbye… Coz I'm gonna cut your bits off in a minute!
Can you lot fight, or do you just kiss starfish\?
You! Stop gaping like a fish and get working!
You! Stop gaping like a fish and get working!
Watch it men! They've tricked us!
Move, you dogs! Get ready to fight!
One day children will play out this great victory! They will remember us forever!
Take aim, fire on the shore!
For the love of Arwen, we have come to this last battle against this enemy holed up here. This is the end of the world, their final haven. Let us strike hard and true and finish the day victorious!
Attack! Give their guts to the fishes!
We stand, like our forefathers of old, to defend our people and our honour! There is much glory to be won today by brave deeds, not by foolish ones! Let the enemy come, for they will be beaten!

We will hold this position even if every night-spawned monster the gods ever put on earth comes against us. We will hold! But today we face only men, and not particularly dangerous men at that! Ready yourselves!
We stand on the defensive today, but that is not the same as cowering in fear! We are the shield of our people, but we are also the swords in their hands! We will prevail!

We stand today on the defensive. It is up to the enemy to come to us if he wishes for victory! But he shall not have it! And, in his attempts, our foe will leave many of his servants dead at our hands! Prepare!
You know, I'm not entirely convinced the admiral knows what's what…

To arms, brothers! Now, summon up all the fight left in you for you shall need it today! We fight not only their flesh but also these weak walls. Once inside, we shall clear their putrid streets of the vermin itself!
Today, my brothers, we make history! Today we sack these city walls and crush our enemy! This will be a great victory, my friends. One they will sing about for lifetimes to come!

Ravage these cowardly people. Storm these walls with violent hearts! Rip them from their homes and sate your desires on all that lies within! I want to smell death in these streets by the end of the day!
Their homes shall be ours in only a few hours, my brave warriors. Be not afeared because of these walls. What are they against the power in our hearts. Onward! For the glory of our ancestors!
Now is the day to make your mark, men! Take this place and in doing so carve your way into the great deeds of our ancestors. Be brutal in your action! Ruthless in your every deed!

Now, we take this settlement and fight through their streets with nothing but rage and hatred for these pathetic foes who cower and hide behind these walls! Show them no mercy, warriors, but kill all you come across!

I want this place torn to pieces! How dare they hide behind these walls and not face us in open battle. Take these walls, men! Then take their lives! Then take whatever you will! Their wives, their slaves, their booty!
Lay seige to this place, brothers! Once we have destroyed this settlement they shall always fear us knowing they are not safe even in their own homes! This will be a great victory!

My ancestor killed twenty Germans in a single battle. I shall go one better today and lead this army to the slaughter of all these bastards who stand before us! Britons! Make me proud, my artful warriors!
Tyr hears our cries and will help us!
We are come, once more, to battle, and not all of us will live to see tomorrow's dawn. However, I wish you good fortune for the day! May your names live in fame for a hundred years!
Today is the day of battle that we prayed would come. Take up your weapons and make your farewells. Some of you will die in what follows, but our people will have victory!
This is the kind of battle that I like: enemies ready to be trussed and stuffed like plump geese! Listen carefully to orders, lads, and we will feast well today! Good hunting!
By the gods, they won't be ready for us.
This is a good plan. Now conceal yourselves, men
This is a moment when fate calls to us! Let us cast aside caution! Let us prove that we are resolute and bold! And, as we win, let us offer thanks to the gods! Make our people proud!
This is a fine day for battle! Every day is a fine day for battle when you lead men of your stripe! So we shall have victory today, men! By the gods, I feel it in my water!
What they can't see, they can't plan for.
Take heart, men! Look to the men who stand with you! Seek to match their deeds and their war-birthed nobility! What enemy will then stand against us, if every man is a hero\? Prepare for action!
By Jupiter! And Neptune! And Mars! We have victory.
Better than giving them a fair chance, boy!
Stop fannying about and put the fire out, you numbskulls!
Where's the honour in shooting someone, eh\?
Any man who runs will answer to my rage!
I've seen corpses with more life than you! Move!
We still have a good wind!

I have witnessed an omen. Five birds circling our camp, chasing off a sixth. It is a clear sign. Victory will be ours! We must split into five divisions and form a great circle! And feathers, we must wear feathers!
We are fortunate, men! The Moon King has sent his celestial peltasts to fight with us! But do not look for them! They are smaller than our eyes can perceive for how else would they fit on the Moon\?
Get ready! I think, it's time to--AAARRRGGGHHH!
Cold steel, men, cold steel! Our one true ally today!
I'll tell you a secret: everyone's scared.

I have been granted a vision. In my dream a great wind extinguished all the flames of our camp! All apart from those burning in my tent. Is it not clear\? The gods favour me with victory. You, on the other hand, are all going to die.
Get ready! I think, it's time to--AAARRRGGGHHH!
I'll tell you a secret: everyone's scared.
Stop that screaming! You peasant nancy!

I have spoken with the gods. We shall have victory: they promised! But we must not spill a single drop of blood! Is our course not clear\? Put aside your weapons, men. We must wrestle our foes into submission! Wrestle!
I come before you as a God! Fear not! I am garbed in this mortal disguise so as not to blind you. But I shall ride out and unveil myself to the enemy! And my divine nakedness shall unman them!
Indeed, sir. That's barbarians for you!
We will walk on your corpses!
Men should know when they're conquered!
Our children fight better than you!
What\? Don't mumble, boy... What did he say\?
If that's true, how come you avoided the Siren's song\?
Wine warms a sailor's heart, man!
Water, water, everywhere. Give me land!
Bath the earth with their blood!
Praise the gods we are protected today!
And eases his joints after rowing…
Taunt these curs. Lets see what they're made of.
In the name of the gods! What do we do now!
By the gods, are you the best your leader has to offer\?
You heard him... Let's say hello to the fish-faced bastards!
I do not know which smells worse: crab farts, or them!
When the times comes, you will make Rome proud!
Bastards! Quickly, boys, have at them!
They seem a little… Confident. Too confident for my liking.
Now make your families proud. Fight fast, fight well!
All-Father be praised! How can I help\?
All-Father be praised! How can I help\?
All-Father be praised! How can I help\?
All-Father be praised! How can I help\?
We are a proud people. We have a proud heritage. We have honoured the gods and, by those same gods, we can fight! Come all the world against us, we will stand and beat them!

Many of us carry scars honourably gained in defence of our people. Today, we stand ready again in their defence. If necessary, we will die for our cause. Better yet, we will help our enemies die! Stand ready, men!
The enemy cannot be allowed within these walls! Our banners must remain flying even if every man here dies in making it so! The gods will permit no other outcome! Stand ready!
Make yourselves ready, men, for the storm is upon us! Our enemies are as cold-hearted as a winter wind from the mountains, and about as friendly. But we will not yield! For our people!
To the victors go the spoils, yes\?
I look around me and I see fear in some faces, and hope in others. But in all I see resolution, and duty, and a belief in honour! That is why we will hold here! Make ready!
What can I do for Egypt\?
What can I do for Egypt\?
What can I do for Egypt\?
What can I do for Egypt\?
I would not have chosen to fight here, but fortune rarely respects the will of one man. Here we are, and here we fight! And here we do our best to win!
Not if those fools sink the bloody ship!

Hold, you noble soldiers, hold! We may stand, surrounded and imperilled, but I would not have it any other way! Here, today, we have a chance to seize our destinies and do mighty deeds! Who, then, is with me\?
The admiral's seen it all before, men. Trust in him now!
There's more of them come to join the party! Praise Camalus!
Stand ready, you sons of fury! We will be as merciless as the storm today, wreck all before us! May the gods guide our hands today, and make sure our blows are true!

Soldiers! Remember your ancestors as you go into battle! Make sure they witness no cowardice today! They were mighty men, and sired mighty sons! Be worthy of them! Now, stand your ground and make ready!
Soldiers! Attention! Today we fight! Today we kill as many of them as we can! That is all! I have no grand strategy to speak of beyond that simple idea! Now: to victory!
Stay awake, lads! This isn't a break, you know.

And so we come to the enemy's home. We stand before these walls knowing this will be a great victory and once we have taken the fight to their very hearths we shall vanquish any defence they have left!
Good plan. If we can't be seen, we can't be attacked.

Over there is an army of fools, brought to the field of death by lies and falsehoods. Our swords, spears and arrows will kill them, but the true cause of their defeat and deaths is idiocy. Make ready!
As you gaze upon these walls, think of our own homes. The sooner we trounce this lot and rout this settlement the sooner you shall feel the warmth of your own hearths!
My word what a smelly cackle of women we have over there. They have dolled themselves up especially for us, men! I'm getting all, well... just looking at them! Make ready to ravage them!

I cannot promise you a great feast after this army of Sallykids are defeated. They eat the most disgusting beetles of the desert flavoured with snake venom and spider's legs. They insult the gods by taking us on!
With me! Charge! Cut these dogs down!
These Seloys, Sell, Seloowies or whatever they are called think they take after the great Alexander. Ha, ha! I could eat Alexander for breakfast and kill ten of these lads before lunch!

These Seleucids are dirty buggers. If you find yourself taken prisoner, better kill yourself than be subject to their vile tortures. It is beyond our worst nightmares! Be victorious today, for your honour's sake!
