Related to Alexander are they\? These great Savaloys! One piece of advice, men! Never bow down in front of them or they'll have you! Just like young Alexander. He'd have done a plank with a knothole, that one!
Now it is often said that I am arrogant. Oh,yes, it is. A little bit cocky. But these Selly Ucids are the cockiest bastards there have ever been. They mean to out-cock even me! Make ready!
What do they call themselves\? Solly who\? Solihull\? Sally what\? Why do we have to fight these people! I became a warrior to fight real men, to test myself against the best. Not this vermin!
Aye. Some of us noticed that!
Any man who leaves his place will be cut down!
Ignore those fools! They only want to kill you!
Now we show them courage, men! Stand by!
I think, sir, we should make ready!
Now we show them courage, men! Stand by!
No! No! I have yet to do great things…
That man is annoying! Gold for anyone who kills him!
We will walk on your corpses!
Our children fight better than you!
Men should know when they're conquered!
Well don't hit them so hard then!
Glory and loot, men. I promise you both this day.
Oh! Look at that! I've broken a nail.
I can't wait to go home. I miss my family so much.
By the bears' bollocks, I cannot believe they land and take us on. We shall sea the seas run red tonight! Let them come and join us in the dance of death! May Garm feast on them tonight!
Legionary! Put that down! RIGHT NOW!
Do not flop about like a landed fish!
The enemy\? Pay them no mind! You do your work!
I once took a fish here that were bigger than you, sir.
The enemy\? Pay them no mind! You do your work!
The next man to touch a rope without orders will feel my sword!
Bath the earth with their blood!
See them die! Oh that is sweet!
Oi! You sons of bitches, your mother was a dog-fish!
It's gone! The seige gear is lost!
See this sword, you unwashed varmint\? It's going to slice your balls off.
You barnacled bastards! We're gonna cut you limb from limb!
Right, you lot. I know you can swear like sailors, so give it some!
Up your bums, you bench-sniffing bastards!
Ha! Now we begin to fight!
Did you see them coming\? By the gods they're crafty ones!
Secure the deck, and make ready to fight!
All-Father be praised! How can I help\?
All-Father be praised! How can I help\?
All-Father be praised! How can I help\?
All-Father be praised! How can I help\?
Rome is mother to us all!

Deliver this place and I promise you shall be rewarded! Drive the enemy from the walls, hunt them in the streets, houses and temples! Any that resist put to the sword! Do this, and you may claim your choice of the spoils.

By all that's good and all that the Druids preach I want a victory today more than ever before! Cut these bastards of Pontus down! They like to torture and maim their prisoners. Let them know the cruelty of our blades!

Behind these walls, our enemies cower in fear, frightened to face you in the open! But these walls will not shelter them! We shall overrun their defences and, in their streets and houses, show them what it means to be afraid!
I will not pretend that this will be easy. Even vermin can find their courage when defending a wall, and a cornered rat fights fiercely! But we have the strength and skill to take this place!

First over the wall: they shall receive the greatest reward. They and their company will have the choice of spoils, be granted the honours of conquerors, and be celebrated above all others. Make ready!
I'm getting cold just hanging about.
Stop talking at the back! Listen to me, will you! I'm speaking now! What's that\? Oh, you can't hear! Great Garm! Someone kill that man then. I want no deaf warriors in my army!
What's that smell\? You there, at the back! Did you just fart\? I shall find whoever did it! Sniff him out! And burn him in sacrifice to Wodan! I swear I will!
Attack! Kill them! Kill! No, you hang back a bit, lad.
Kill them all! Kill those sons of whores!
Last one there is a twat!
Oh, for the old days of honour!
Oi! Crab-face! Your mum does gravediggers! For money!
Deckmasters! Get your men moving to douse the flames!
Any man who falls behind will answer to me! So, steady!
If the man alongside falls, so be it! Keep to your place!
Told you, lad! Just like a nice parade!
Form on me! Steady now! Draw swords!
Fortuna save us! What a bunch of piss-swilling bastards!
That man is annoying! Gold for anyone who kills him!
We will walk on your corpses!
Men should know when they're conquered!
Our children fight better than you!
All seas look familiar at my age.
I'm getting bored of this view.
Did anyone smuggle any women on board\?
Do NOT flinch! I will beat any man who is weak!
I have a powerful fear of fish!
Do NOT flinch! I will beat any man who is weak!
I have a powerful fear of fish!
Bath the earth with their blood!
That makes things a bit fairer.
Only if I don't do it first…
I've heard they don't like you either, you girl!
Only if I don't do it first…
You just like worrying honest folk, don't you\?
I've heard they don't like you either, you girl!
Come here, you fish-breathed, gutless whores!
Crush them, boys! Double your efforts, my lads!
We can smell you from here!
Make your peace with your gods! You die today!
You're never that nice to us!
By Ba'al' balls it's good to feel land under my feet again!
gods in the deeps! I can smell them from here!
Get ready! We'll gut these whoresons like fish!
Good luck, son. You'll be fine.
Be Angra Mainyu's wrath! Destroy them all!
That's just what your mother calls me.

Pray to the gods for victory, men, for it will bring us great renown and reward! Both are here for the taking, just beyond those walls! Renown for our achievement, and the choicest treasures as our reward.

Patience, men, they will not look so arrogant when the day is out! When we throw them from their walls, when the streets run red with their blood, and we loot their homes and temples. Then they will quake!
Their walls may be high and their gates thick, but no place is impregnable! We will scale their heights and smash down their barricades, and any who resist shall be put to death or enslaved.
Their defences will not look as daunting when the we breach them. We will flood into the gap and claim what is ours! To the victor goes the spoils, as the Roman dogs would say.

We will raze their defences, bring their walls, gates and barricades crashing to the ground, and put any that resist to the sword! They will bend the knee to us, or this place will become as ash and dust.
These walls will not stop us, men! Once their defences have fallen and their warriors put to the sword, you may claim what you will as your choice of spoils! This is my gift!

Any that stand with me this day, all those who hold against our enemies, will be counted above all others. They will earn their honour, earn it in victory or in death! No matter the odds, we will not yield!
How long do we have to wait here\?
Not a word now. Keep silent, till I give the order.
Anyone falls behind I shall kill them myself!
I rather like the smell of blood!
Don't take this the wrong way, but you're a loony!
Better than giving them a fair chance, boy!
You men! Do not gawp like children! Put out the fire!
Where's the honour in shooting someone, eh\?
Any man who falls back will lose his head!
Hmmm. You people try my patience.
Forget the enemy! Be afraid of ME!
I told you, just like a nice parade!
Hold to your duty, no matter what!
Stop that screaming! You peasant nancy!
Forget the enemy! Be afraid of ME!
The Greeks think of themselves as poets. Today I want you to show them some Germanic poetry in motion as you slice off their heads and spear their hearts! Send these verse lovers to their graves!
We will walk on your corpses!
Our children fight better than you!
Men should know when they're conquered!
Here have my flask. You only had to ask.
Water, water everywhere. Not a drop to drink…
Did you see that\? A whole horde of sea monsters!
I do not like these waters. They are troubled.
That's a huge boost for our chances today!
Well, there's enemy ships all over them.
Come and fight! Come on, you spineless squid! Face us!
Curse them! They've destroyed the seige equipment!
What are you waiting for\? Need some help, do ya\?
Don't worry those fish-faced gits, you land-fool! Worry about me!
Does this part get any easier\?
May Ba'al be with us. And may we homour Carthage today!
The waiting\? For them to attack\? No.
Caught them with their pants down! Let's get to work, men! Kill them all!
Caught them napping, did we\? Now, that's what I call an ambush!
Attack! Attack! You lovely boys! We shall feast well after this!
It worked you glorious, hairy arsed bandits! Now make them pay!
Not quite all the jar, sir!
Wasps are really awesome at staring contests.
Not in my unit there isn't!
I'm not a lord. Sir" will do."
Haha! They weren't expecting that! Excellent, my brave warriors! Now, cut them to pieces!
Drive in, lads! No stopping now! We have the upper hand! Use it!
Don't let them form a defence! At them quickly now! No mercy!
Stand up straight! You are warriors, not sacks of barley!
O, gods! Grant me quiet! How much did I have last night\?
Are we having a staring contest, or a fight\?
Enemies\? Bah! Townsmen with a nasty temper!
Who's for a drink\? There's time!
Kill them before they form up! Take their leader out. Cut his bloody head off!
Keep moving! Don't give them a chance to regroup! Onward, brothers!
No, boy! We're the hard cases here!
I am not known for offering the enemy much. But I offer them this: run now, and I will spare your lives. Stay to fight, and you will have only death and defeat! Now, to work, men!
Stand to! Prepare! Remember your training!
I don't like the look of 'em!
By all the gods, I trust we have an easy fight today, men! But we know that the gods also love their little jokes! So make ready! Keep your wits about you and your swords to hand!
By all the gods, I think I am the luckiest man alive! I have you to command, and prospect of a glorious victory! I thank the gods for these gifts! Now, the victory awaits our efforts!

Battles are rarely won by cowards or timid old women! Men with hard hearts win battles! And today I see such under my command! All that remains, then, is to listen for your orders, and obey! Prepare yourselves!
If I hear another word, I'll have your tongue cut out.
As I see it, and as the omens confirm, our enemies are well supplied with farmers and peasants. They lack warriors but that is entirely to our benefit! Brave soldiers, to arms!
For the love of the magnificent Pharaoh! DUCK!
I am blessed with luck it would seem.
I am blessed with luck it would seem.
There is still time, my lord.
There is still time, my lord.
All is not lost, my lord.
All is not lost, my lord.
I have not failed you, my lord.
I have not failed you, my lord.
Come on, heroes, do you want to live forever\?
Fate has granted me another chance.
Fate has granted me another chance.
I want blood! I want BLOOD! For Taranis!
By Toutatis! Send these whelps to the depths.
Oh, for a bed and a warm woman!
We are undone! To arms! To arms! Form up and face the enemy!
Everyone's scared! The trick is not to show it!
Any man who dies will answer for his weakness!
File leaders! Look to your men now!
Hold steady, lads, not much longer!
The enemy\? What are they\? Goats and little girls!
Hold steady, lads, not much longer!
The enemy\? What are they\? Goats and little girls!
Swords, men, swords! Have at them!
Storm and tempest! What a bunch of girls!
Cut your armour free! Then swim!
Do not let the crabs near me.
Ancestors! Protect me now, if you don't mind…
Our children fight better than you!
Ahh... I will owe the captain coin...
I like a good, strong sailor.
To the ocean, as you say.
I can. Rather fight on land any day.
I would sail beyond the known world at your request.
Always the worst part, the calm before the next storm.
I can't wait to see a good old sea battle.
I wish we had some wine with us. I could kill a drink.
Ahh... I will owe the captain coin...
The crabs will bless their gods for their feasting today!
Making my way to the ships.
Sea air. Very bad for the armour.
Of course it's wet, you idiot!
The crabs will bless their gods for their feasting today!
Bath the earth with their blood!
That's the end of the artillery!
I would sail beyond the known world at your request.
Making my way to the ships.
I like a good, strong sailor.
To the ocean, as you say.
Call yourselves sailors\? My mother can swear better…
Camulus, give us strength to repel these curs!
What\? I can't hear you\? Turn around if you're gonna talk out of your arse all day!
Then we'll just have to stick it where the sun don't shine!
But your mother's known more sailors than us!
Oi! You lot! Come and kiss my bony rower's arse!
Make ready, men! We’ll show these fools who they face!
They will make murals of this victory, men! Go and make history!
By Ba'al's oiled beard, what a noise!
Drown these dogs! Let Ran take them in her nets!
That's why you're not in charge.
The dogs of war, eh\? Let's send them to Ankou!
What cruelty do you wish, O Lord\?
What cruelty do you wish, O Lord\?
What cruelty do you wish, O Lord\?
What cruelty do you wish, O Lord\?
That'll teach them to drop their guard! A perfect ambush! My blood is up!
Tear them apart, men! What a bunch of idiots! Let's cleave a few heads!
Surprise, surprise, you fools! Welcome to our little party! Prepare to die! Ha, ha!
No more than they deserve! Run them through! I want their blood! Now!

Too long has Egypt been a poor neighbour! Too long has the Pharaoh's arrogance been heeded! Today, we do some way towards righting wrongs! Ba'al watches over us, and we will be triumphant in his name! Make ready!
Delightful, sir. Your taste is… wonderful.
Nonsense! No commander of ours would do that with a goat!
My thanks, but I relish only wine from my own estates.
O! No, no, no. You look well in it!
Yes! The stupid, weak bastards don't know what has hit them! Finish them off!
That's worth a mug of mead! Well done, my beauties! Now kill the idiots!
That's it, men! The gods rejoice in your skill and cunning! Attack!
Check your weapons! And then check again!
Do you think this colour goes with my eyes\?
Anyway, I heard this story that…
Drink, sir\? Only the local wine.
This bloody helmet's given me a blister!
Look, I stole the armour. Really, I did! I'm not in the army…
Right, my lucky lads! Give them a taste of iron!
Another day dawns, and another battle beckons! Well, men, this is nothing new to us! One day, when all our enemies are crushed, we will go home with honour. Until then: prepare for battle!
When we take this place, it will be a heavy blow to our enemies and their ambitions. The glory and loot we gain are just added delights! Once we are within the walls, do as you will! Now, to arms!
Fear is as powerful as a sword!
Fear is as powerful as a sword!
When we have taken this place and our enemies kneel in chains before us, when their women and children beg for the mercy of slavery, then we will have done a good day's work! Now, to arms!
I'll pick off a couple of weak ones!
I'll pick off a couple of weak ones!
What of it\? Meant we had a good night's sleep.
Their general believes he can take us here. He thinks we are not ready. His army thinks we are barbarian scum! Shall we teach them a lesson\? Make ready! Let's send these children to their deaths!

Today, as your leader, I command you to stand fast and defend this settlement! The gods favour strong men. You shall need to be strong today. Offer them thanks and sacrifice the enemy's in their name!
They will learn to fear me!
They will learn to fear me!
They will learn to fear me!
They will learn to fear me!
Pray to the gods we may hold these walls today for if the enemy scales them then it will make our task almost impossible. Stand fast and brave, men! The gods are watching!
It's like you making us hide when watch duty was handed out.
Right men! Listen to me! In the coming defence, remember block and counter. I don't want any gratuitous disembowelling or limb ripping or looting. Is that understood\? Just defend these bloody walls!
Race you then, you old bastard!
Come on! Either hurry up or get out of my way!
Remember, first one to rip a heart out wins the boar's teeth!
After this we deserve to drown in wine!
I wish you good luck, my brothers!
Ancestors! Protect me now, if you don't mind…
Mark your targets when they come!
For Carthage! For the glory of our great city!
The enemy\? The enemy\? Keep your eyes on me, damn you!
Hold the men in check! Some of them may run mad!
Sir! Gods! Sir! They really don't like us!
Hold the men in check! Some of them may run mad!
Smells like roast pork tonight, then!
This lot bring shame on the name of Baduhunna and those who serve her! We must wipe them from the face of this world as vermin not fit to bleed on our blades! Terminate them!
The bastards! They are fighting back!
I will have order! Keep your spacing!
We will walk on your corpses!
Men should know when they're conquered!
And… And they hunt in these waters you say\?
Maybe, if you're nice to me.
…next moment, snap! And it dragged him straight to the bottom.
When we do get to fight can I have a go with your new sword\?
I long for some fresh fruit.
Quiet! Do you want to be fish food\?
Still, nice day for a bit of rowing.
Bath the earth with their blood!
I hate those bastards! May they rot in hell.
We can concentrate on what's in front of us now.
Your mother was a fish! And she smelt!
You look scared. Don't worry it'll all be over soon.
Steady, boy! Don't cut yourself on your razor wit.
The gods must have a sense of humour!
The gods must have a sense of humour!
The Gods are watching over their son!
The Gods are watching over their son!
Aye, lad, but they sail like little girls!
Gods of wind and tide preserve us! The foe look fierce!
Quick, lads! Show 'em what we're made of!
It's knowing when to fight, and when to-
Remember your training! This is it!
Quiet now... Or I'll take that flapping tongue of yours!
Is it too late to say I haven't had any training\?
I have carried out your orders.
With Ran's blessing, we'll drive these curs into her nets.
I was the instrument of your will.
They're running! Those gutless fish are swimming for home.
They're running! Cut them down like dogs!
Cowardice! This is a cowardly way to fight a battle!
Like the scared little babies they are! They're routing!
My mission was a success, my lord.
I have carried out your orders.
I have done all you asked and more.
We did it! She's going down!
Succeeding is what I do best!
I have done all you asked, my lord.

Stand by! This will be close!
We'll kill these dogs! Or drag them down with us!
Hold her together! Make sure the hull doesn't break!
Only if you want it, sir.
Keep to your tasks! We are not going down!
May the gods be merciful and make this quick!
Belenos, deliver us from the dark depths!
Yes, we are you bloody fool!
Well, don't look down then, you stupid…
Neptune! Send us a gentle breeze and good fortune!
Neptune! I beg you: do not let the fish eat me!
Only cowards will stay and die in this thing! Now, get ready!
It was only a bloody boat…
Dry! Land! O! Thanks be to Jupiter!
Defend the ship, my brothers! Kill the defilers!
You march. Your feet bleed. You march again!
I don't care how tired you are!
Down lads, down! They make a nasty noise but---arrrrgghhghghh!
Duck you foo-- Ah, too late!
Come on, stand like a man!
They seem damned hostile today, the buggers!
I'm bored. Will anything ever hap-arrrghghg!
Can't I cower like a girl for a bit\?
Fight or swim, lad! That's your only choice.
Oooh! Have we got any real men with us\?
I will cut down any man who flinches!
Show them how real men fight!
Which one of you peasants did that\?
Anyman who drops is left behind!
When this is done, I'm going to worship Bacchus for a week!
If those elephants charge… Well, it's been nice knowing you, lad.
I've never seen an elephant before. They're beautiful!
Put your backs in to it!
Put your backs in to it!
Put your backs in to it!
Put your backs in to it!

I would journey to the ends of the world for Makedon!

I think I just crapped myself.
Hold fire, you idiots, until you have a good target!
To arms, men! We will crush them here and wipe them from the face of this world like the petty vermin they are! I am sick of the sight of this place. Finish this quickly!
They will fight  to the last today, brothers! At last an enemy forced to face us and try to match our courage. But they know in their hearts this will be their final day in this world! Crush them!
Parthians love one thing more than any other: gold! Bear this in mind, my friends, as you drive them before you! They are always worth killing for the golden fruit their corpses bear! Now, to arms!
Our Parthian foes are perfumed fops and unwashed brigands, in roughly equal numbers. The fops are worried about their nice clothes, the brigands about their loot. We have come for victory. Prepare!

Come, warriors, they await us inside. They prepare, as I speak, to welcome you with arrow and blade and all sorts of hot surprises! Ha, ha! We shall enter as uninvited guests and take all their offerings with great glee!
Is there anything more laughable than a Parthian army\? Do they not realise they look ridiculous, in all their finery\? Are they soliciting for customers on the docks, or here to fight\? Bah!
At last! We come to the final verses of our enemy's tale! Go in there! Storm these walls and wipe this lot out! They should give us a good fight so enjoy yourselves!

I'm quite surprised to see the Parthian army today! I half expected them to be still a-bed with their concubines and catamites! No matter, awake or lolling in a drunken stupor, they can still be killed! Make ready!

And so we come to the final moments in our enemy's story! Pity them as you scale these walls, their final stronghold. Be wary of their desperate defence. And then bless them as you send them to their deaths!

I do not like fighting Parthians! They have little concept of honour, and no concept at all of bravery! They value trickery, lies and cunning. I have heard that rats do much the same! Ha! Make sure they do not bite you!

Do not feel any fear of the Parthian army over there. Oh, they look pretty enough, and they can ride around on their silly little horses, but they do not fight like men! No, they fight like old women! To arms!
There's more of them, over there… See\?
They have no choice now! They have nowhere else to run! Here they will fight and here they will die! Celebrate your work so far and now end it with this great victory!
By all the gods! I almost thought we faced a challenge here, then I remembered we are fighting Parthians! The only problem is trying to find one who isn't running away! Anyway, to arms!

Praise the gods, we have got the bastards cornered at last! Can you hear them shake behind these walls\? Soon you will be among them. They shall fight hard for this last outpost. But we will trounce these feeble foes!
Get in there and trounce these cowardly bastards! This is the last of them, holed up in this rats' haven. I want them dispatched and this whole place levelled. Not one of them gets out alive!

Expect a hard battle, boys! They will not let us take their last refuge without giving as good as they get! But we love a good fight! Let us strike fear in their hearts! Give them the deaths they deserve!
I hate the Greeks! They make me sick with all the money and slaves they have. All that wealth and not a decent drop of mead in the whole of their empire! Let's exterminate them!
Have you ever done it the Greek way, men\? Eh\? Assaults from the rear… They call it flanking! They like it like that, you know! What a bunch of flankers! Let's give them some of their own medicine!

See these Greek bastards! They think they are so civilised. So superior to us who are just barbarians in their eyes. Well, I want those eyes plucked out. And roasted for our feast! Is that barbaric enough for them, I wonder!
Once upon a time, a general made a rhyme! He started a fight, with all of his might, even though his army was tight! Come, men, put away the mead we have to kill this bunch of girly Greeks.
Dehh hett dahhh haa dahh whoo daaah!
Dehh hett dahhh haa dahh whoo daaah!
Dehh hett dahhh haa dahh whoo daaah!
Dehh hett dahhh haa dahh whoo daaah!
Dehh hett dahhh haa dahh whoo daaah!

Erghh! Greeks! Smell them from here! I can't stand them! Pretentious bastards! They dance and do plays and build fancy columns! Bollocks! They can't drink mead! They can't feast until they puke! And they can't fight!
All my life I have longed to share a field with the Greek army. To take on their hoplites and test my minds against their generals. They are so… beautiful! Let's show them some real barbaric moves!
Gods bless us now! There's more of them!
I can't wait to cut some throats.
See you in there. Last one out's a boar's arse.

Today we fight one of the oldest civilisations in the world. They used to dominate the Mediterranean, I'm told! Now look at them, pathetically shaking at the sight of real men! Let's run them through!
They're mettle is weak and brittle. They break and run!
We have prevailed, men! See how they run!
Fight, you buggers, fight! This is not some children's game!
They're running, by the gods! Excellent!
We just leaving them to drown\?
To drown like that. A sailor's worst nightmare.
They're running, by the gods! Excellent!
Don't come between the gods and their catch, boy.
They're ramming us! Be ready to fight, men!
Here they come! Ram away you unwashed vermin!
Sir, with all due respect I don't like this one Jupiter-be-cursed bit.
At them! Keep at them! They're weaklings!
They're running! Cut them down like dogs!
Cowardice! This is a cowardly way to fight a battle!
We thank the gods of the sea for our safe voyage. Now we call on Camulus to be with us today. May he guide our sword arm and bless us with victory! To arms, men! We go ashore in Andarta's name!
So many shots! How many men do we face\?
Let go of your bloody sword!
Fifteen years! I've never lost a ship 'til now!
Look to yourselves, men! Abandon the ship.
Let's make sure we bloody win before we get all glorious, eh\?
I give thanks, Neptune, for glory to come!
Get onto the wall and kill the first bastard you see!
When your feet bleed you can moan!
Choose your ground carefully. You only die once.
I don't care how tired you are!
Choose your ground carefully. You only die once.
Gods above! They are creditable shots, at least!
With respect, sir, I think you are allowed to duck.
Don't let the others see you like this!
Watch out! Arrows and stones do not care about courage!
I will kill any man with fear in his heart!
Honour! Honour\? We fight for our lives as well!
If any of you men run, you will answer with your heads!
I do not want a grave here, of all places.
Earn your pay! Kill those bastards!
Show them how real men fight!
You lazy goat-sucking farmboys! Kill them!
For the Pharaoh, strength onto him!
For the Pharaoh, strength onto him!
For the Pharaoh, strength onto him!

For the Pharaoh, strength onto him!

For the Pharaoh, strength onto him!
For the Pharaoh, strength onto him!
Them elephants look horrible... And smell hideous too!
I've seen a few things in my time but that is just wrong.
They do… Reminds me of your mother.
I have come from talking with the druids. What a rightly sober lot they are! They say we will have a great victory today! Tonight I trust we will all drink and get royally drunk! Get ready, men!
By the gods! What a city! Beyond even my wildest, wettest dreams… I have imagined this moment many times but still… Come, men! Let us see if her streets are really paved with gold!
Sons of Briton, I have decided to attack! Having consulted the druids this is our time! The gods are watching, waiting, expecting. Now we show our mettle and let us dispatch this foe! Onwards!
The gods have shown me we must attack. Andraste has granted me the strength to lead you and I pray you shall not disappoint me. Draw your weapons, men and make your peace with the gods.
I have spoken with the druids and they have shown me the way to win this day. The omens are good, the sacrifice has been made. Now we must seize the day, and crush these bastards! For the gods!

Our beloved Arwen's lips smile wide as she looks down on us. Her breasts are firm and her body perfect! If you feel her embrace today, you're a lucky bastard! Your fighting will be over and you will be dead!
Jupiter and Mars, give us your strength and your blessing for what we must do today! This will not be a pleasant day, men, but we must be strong and destroy this place! That is what Rome expects!
I will watch them, my lord.
I will watch them, my lord.
My eyes are yours, my lord.
My eyes are yours, my lord.
I hear that the wine round here is very fine.
And I hear blood is very good for the soil, sir!
I live to serve the mighty Carthage!
I live to serve the mighty Carthage!
I live to serve the mighty Carthage!
I live to serve the mighty Carthage!
And this, grandmother, is how you…
Aim low! Aim low! Give them death!
See this place\? It is their last outpost. All their hopes live or die today within these walls. In Andarta's name you shall ransack it and lay waste once you are inside!

When I was young bards sang about days such as these when, before the enemy's final stronghold, the leaders spoke to encourage his warriors. Well, you need no bluster from me. Simply enter and do your worst!
Well, that worked out mostly not wrong.
Well, that worked out mostly not wrong.

Today shall be one of the hardest days of your lives! Today we extinguish this enemy's last hope. They will fight tooth and nail against us. And we shall show our ancestors why we are worthy to carry their blood!
The Gods have granted me another chance.
The Gods have granted me another chance.
There! Look! There's more of them... See\?
Are you done\? Then get back in line!
Don't worry you'll see a lot of bloody things in a minute.
Here, lads, more heads to cut off!
I can't see a bloody thing.
My good men, my true warriors of Gaul, my fearless fighters! Know today I will spill my last drop for you. Today the ancestors fight alongside you. Today we fight to the death!
Give a cheer, lads! The wretches flee from us!
Go and poison the fish, you bastards!
Keep at them! Do not help the wounded yet!
That's it! Well done! Now, kill the cowards as they run!
After them! Don't let them rally!
The dirty scum run like children!
I hate them. They are worse than merchants!
By the gods! They are not brave then.
A fine feast for fish and birds… It's making me hungry.
Give them no quarter! Cut them down.
By the gods! They are not brave then.
Brace yourself! They're going to ram us!
Bugger me! They're coming straight for us!
I say, this is a good day! There's the admiral! Hurrah!
The enemy\? Pigs! Worse than Greek oarsmen on shore leave!
Now, at them again! Don't let them live!
There he is men! The bastard who got us into this!
And the bastard who'll get us through it!
Hard to say, but there's enough of them.
You've got better eyes than me, what are they doing\?
There's too much water coming in!
Swim clear! Find what you can to stay afloat!
Put your backs into it, men!
Do not invite ill-fortune by saying such things!
I heard the sacred chickens drowned yesterday…
Warriors! Stop gaping like fish and start working! Haul!
Keep firing, you fish-faced old women! Keep firing!
When your feet bleed you can moan!
I don't care how tired you are!
You are BLEEDING on your armour! Did you ask permission\?
I say, all this shooting is ruining my day!
Duck you foo-- Ah, too late!
She's not here, so shut it!
Oh shut up, you big wendy showoff!
I think I hit their captain!
Keep going, men! Take them one by one!
The enemy are remarkably dirty. Mars protect us from their stench!
Put your backs in to it!
Put your backs in to it!
Put your backs in to it!
Put your backs in to it!
Try to kill their riders if you can. Then drive them off!
Yeah, I heard you're wife was a tough one.
Last time I faced an elephant it was not good.
