I say to you we will hold, and that every single one of us will be a Hercules reborn! Even if the enemy are as savage as the Stymphalian Birds, we will resist them to our last breath! Now, make yourselves ready!

Would you have Parthia under the yoke of the Seleucids\? Would you let our people be enslaved\? No! We will fight! We will battle to the last! Draw your weapons, men! Let us show these Seleucid scorpions how free men fight!
Fight, and die well, lads. Let's make these bastards pay!
I can't see the point in this. We've had it!

Do you hear that, men\? That sound that whispers in the wind\? That is the sound of their gods crying at how pathetic these people are. This is the last of them. Let's put their gods out of their misery.
Men, I am tired of this foe. Sick of the sight of them! This is their last army so dispatch them with speed and ruthlessness. I want them obliterated and forgotten. Forever!
They shall fight hard. Be very wary out there. This is the last of them and so they will battle until all is lost. Make sure of your every move. Do not tire. For they shall not!
We have the chance to wipe these fools from the face of the world. They should have stayed farmers or shopkeepers as they are terrible soldiers. Let us show them how it is done!
Once we have dispatched this enemy there are no more of them. Their last army! Well, I want this to be their last day! Show the bastards no respect and kill them all. No prisoners.
So this is all they have left! They must be rubbish to have lost so many. We shall take them and destroy them. Their gods obviously do not care for them so why should we\?
May Taranis strike you down if you run off!
Why should we bother with this lot\? Aren't they the last of their kind\? I suppose somone has to take care of them. So let us clean up quickly and then get to drinking. I have a great thirst coming!
That changes things… Where are that lot going\?
A noble cause requires noble men!
Fight with us! It’s a good life!
To arms! Attack! To the fight, men!
Fight with us! It’s a good life!
A noble cause requires noble men!
Death in battle, there is no finer ending!
Are you ready to do your duty to the tribe\?
It is a great and glorious thing to fight for our cause!
It is a great and glorious thing to fight for our cause!
Are you ready to do your duty to the tribe\?
Death in battle, there is no finer ending!
These Germans vex me! By the spirits of my ancestors, they truly vex me! How can a folk so ignorant, hairy and crude think that they have any right to walk abroad\? Time for them to die!

These Germans have no idea of decency or honour. They believe only in murder and theft. Fortunately, we are men of a different strain: honour, glory and duty are mother's milk to us! Guard yourselves, and get ready!
And there goes our chance at loot!
Now, at them again! Don't let them live!
Run you bastards! You bring dishonour on your families!
I feel strangely happy, watching them drown…
Ah! This will be a sea of widows' tears when we are done!
But better them than us, boy.
Run down these curs! Kill the filthy sons of whores!
Yeah! That'll teach them to take us on!
Be ready to fight… Now brace!
We are lucky, my boy, that we sail with such a good admiral…
I've seen the admiral! And we're winning!
Keep at them! Do not help the wounded yet!
That's it! Well done! Now, kill the cowards as they run!
After them! Don't let them rally!
The ancestors are pleased. They like courage!
Where did that lot spring from\?
Save yourselves! Jump while you can!
A quick, clean death is preferable to this… Agreed\?
My mother warned me there would be days like this!
If it comes to it, yes.
Move the thing… And that other thing… And sort that there…
By sea or by mountain, sire\?
By sea or by mountain, sire\?
Neptune be thanked! A fine day for a battle!
What did the omens say of today\? What of the chickens\?
By sea or by mountain, sire\?
Clear away! Move those ropes! Clear those buckets!
Move, you miserable wretches, and haul away!
Steersman! Make sure they can see our banners!
By sea or by mountain, sire\?
Jump to it! Keep the arrows coming!
I think I hit their captain!
Oh shut up, you big wendy showoff!
Lady Tanit's incredibly holy tits, that feels good!
May Seth bring a storm to help us. There's more!
You march. Your feet bleed. You march again!
Our enemies love black wickedness, it seems.
I don't care how tired you are!
Well done! Fine work there, men!
It's SUPPOSED TO HURT, you idiot!
I am not moving from this spot, not for any-AARGGHGH!
Tell my mother her cooking was awful!
Tell her yourself when you get home, you fool!
Yeah, we get it. Just pull will you!
I do not want to be ashamed when I join my ancestors!
Anyman who drops is left behind!
My father was an oarsman, and his father before him and his father's father-
Keep firing, you fish-faced old women! Keep firing!
Try and spare the ship. We could use it ourselves.
These bastards are a cruel bunch. If you are not cut by their curved blades they will capture you and cut your balls off. Make sure that doesn't happen! Get in amongst them and deal with them first.

Never trust these foreigners! If they surrender, don't believe it. They are liars and have no honour. They dress as women and have dogs and cats as gods! No, I do not like fighting them. So get it done fast!
See them pray to their animal gods! These freaks are blasphemous and insult our deities by daring to take us on! I give you permission to defile them as you will. For the glory of our gods!
We'll kill these elephants, if you hold!
Do you think we'll be remembered\?
You shouldn't have profaned that tomb… Gods always have their revenge.
That whore'll be telling funny stories about you forever, lad.
My fault\? It was your idea to go looting!
No fear! Show them no fear!
More fools have come to die. All the more glory for us!
Charge home! No quarter! No mercy!
For the honour of our families!
Fight, O my brothers, fight! Glory and honour!
Enemy reinforcements! Let's show them what we got!
At them, by Ares! For Glory!
By Hera's saggy tits! I've had enough of this!
Cowards flee, and they die a little death each day.
Look at them run, desperate to escape their fate.
Now lads! They're on the run!
Great work, men! Now, keep at them!
Food for fish and birds… It's what I'd want for those bastards!
Brace yourselves, men! Prepare to fight!
Unclean bastards! They're going to ram us!
I've seen the admiral! And we're winning!
What did that skinny one say\?
Press them, you bastards! Give them no space!
Harry them! Give them no escape!
There's the cunning bastard behind our victory…
He was just asking who ate all the pies\?
What\? You mean the admiral is here\?
Get rid of that water! Quickly!
Don't let the ship drag you down! Swim for it, men!
He looks like he needs it!
May Mithra bless the admiral today!
Take that man's name! His armour is a disgrace!
This is not a good place for a battle.
This is not a good place for a battle.
How do you hear these things\?
You always say that. Misery guts.
This morning a sea eagle dropped a snake on the admiral's deck…
You! What's your bloody name and number\?
You always say that. Misery guts.
Fine work, my brave lads! Fine work!
Men! They've loosed the dogs on us, the cowards!
The general is right to be proud of you men! That was hot work!
Be brave! We're only facing a few girls today!
Of course it hurts, you idiot!
Arrrchhh. My blood. But I will not end like this!
I do not believe in cowardly ways such as duck-arrrrgghghghgh!
Girls with bloody big choppers, mind…
Look out, men! Beware the dogs!
Better one to live and have a Roman victory!
This is a good day to die!
Hold, damn you! Elephants aren't dangerous!
Aim for the riders if you can reach them.
They are going to shit everywhere!
In the name of Carthage, I will hack you to pieces!
There's no shame in this at least… We can die well.
Bloody hell there's a lot of them!
Hold these barbarian scum! A dikhakloi for each one you slay.
So he is human after all.
Let the officers worry about these new bastards.
I know we're few in number, but we must fight on!
See where those extra men go!
Ha! You can smell their fear on the wind!
Best thing for them: a good wash!
Press them, you bastards! Give them no space!
Harry them! Give them no escape!
Cowards! They're trying to make off!
Ha! The enemy captain is taking orders from his mum!
Food for the fish! They'll eat well today.
Calm down, man, or I'll gut you myself!
Brace yourselves! We'll go down fighting!
By Ba'al's hairy parts, this is going to hurt!
Come on, girl, you can take it.
Dis Pater! They're making a noise!
I can't understand what they're saying.
Now lads! They're on the run!
Great work, men! Now, keep at them!
Raise a cheer, men. For our glorious admiral!
Just something about your mother and a donkey.
gods of the deep! This is ill-luck, to die in such a fashion!
Carpenter! Look to your work! Make us watertight!
Plug that hole! Stick anything in it!
Swim for it! Get clear of the ship!
This is an evil day to die. Evil.
This is an evil day to die. Evil.
Look out, men! Beware the dogs!
May Hera be merciful and cradle us in her arms.
Fine work, my brave lads! Fine work!
Can I have a breather now they're gone, boss\?
Be still, man! Do you want to be killed\?
Battle\? Battle\? This is murder, not battle!
Look out! Duck! Duck, man, duck!
Rest when you're dead, you lazy bugger!
Honour is all I have left!
Men! They've loosed the dogs on us, the cowards!
Crucifixion, or eaten by fish. Mark my words. Fish.
You have a dishonest face, lad! You won't die in battle!
Our enemies are so unmanly and weak that the only way they think to win is to outnumber us! Ha! As if numbers matter to Roman courage and virtue. Ignore their count, and strike hard!
That, my boy, is an elephant.
For the Pharaoh, strength onto him!
For the Pharaoh, strength onto him!
For the Pharaoh, strength onto him!
For the Pharaoh, strength onto him!
For the Pharaoh, strength onto him!
These easterners trouble my digestion- as do all foreigners come to think of it! But there is something about this lot and their shifty ways that makes my sword arm itch too! We'd best be at them!

Make ready, men! Our eastern foes are not used to proper battles, and it would be rude to keep them waiting! The seem strangely eager to reach their benighted and wicked afterlife, so let's oblige them! To arms!

It is a brave sight, an eastern army. But it is brave only in appearance. In reality, their generals are fops and merchants, more suited to arguing over figs than fighting battles! So, prepare to give them a fight!
I am sure that we will find plenty to loot among those dandies and fops over there! All we have to do first is kill enough of them! Given their cowardice, that should not be too hard! To arms!
You can always smell an eastern army! The stench of camels goes before them, even when they have no camels! I am sure their odd ways… Well, that alone is reason to kill them! To arms!
What a shiny, polished, well-dress collection of corpses! How noble in aspect, how splendid in attire! It will do them no good if you shove a good length of iron into their bellies! To arms!
Those easterners trouble me! I do not hold with men who think of wearing silks and perfumes! I do not care for insolent cowards! I do not care for THEM! It is time! To arms!
Make your peace with each other!

Those eastern sandflies are interested only in gold, not honour! To achieve wealth, they will do anything to anyone! Do not fall into their hands: they will seek out gold in your bowels, given the chance!

Britons! We stand at the gates of this lot's capital city! We must scale these walls and break their hearts as we rampage through their beloved streets! Show no mercy! Pillage whatever you want, it is ours for the taking!
For Rome, and our glorious commander!
Teach them never to take on Carthage again!
Gather yourselves, men! By the gods, I am sick of the sight and smells of the sea and glad that we are again to fight with land beneath our feet. To arms, men, and let's butcher our way inland!
I've spent enough time on that boat with you stinking bastards! You're a bunch of hairy arses and I have never been prouder to lead an army in all my life. Now, let's fight!
We go to shore, men, to do our work. See the enemy. Mark them well. May your blades strike true and your shields be strong. We fight for glory, honour and our homeland!
We made it, men. The gods have granted us safe passage to these shores. Now we go about our work with fire in our hearts and the enemy's blood on our swords. Now we fight!
Keep one eye on that lot.

We now leave the sea to claim our rightful place in our people's history. May the ancestors fight with us today for we carry with us their honour and heritage. Forward, men, and destroy this pathetic gaggle of girls!
By Andarta there's more of them!
Bloody bastards are breeding like flies!
I feel so much better, hearing that.
I feel so much better, hearing that.
The curs are turning tail, and running! Well done, men!
Wind and waves! This is a fine day!
The yellow bellied landlubbers! Can't take a proper sea battle!
Wind and waves! This is a fine day!
Leave any survivors. Let the gods of the sea take what they will.
Boarding masters! Keep your men at it!
This will put an end to it one way or another.
You know me, sir, I'm always ready for that!
A wise man does not expose himself needlessly to danger.
We make war so we may live in peace.
Aries and Athena watch over our warriors.
We make war so we may live in peace.
An army without faith is no army at all.
Aries, give strength to our brave warriors!
A wise man does not expose himself needlessly to danger.
Surely bravery alone is enough for our warriors\?
Surely bravery alone is enough for our warriors\?
Give them no mercy! Kill the cowards!
A thousand curses on their heads! Cowards!
War is old men talking and young men dying.
Aries, give strength to our brave warriors!
An army without faith is no army at all.
Neptune's scaley buttocks! Get ready for impact!
War is old men talking and young men dying.
Aries and Athena watch over our warriors.
So many shots! How many men do we face\?
Now, show them how soldiers fight!
They just want to live, lad, same as us…
No lad, we float here 'til it's done…
This will shame our glorious Pharaoh! Save her if you can!
Here, hang onto this… Will they pick us up\?
Maybe… But only when the battle's done.
Let loose the fury of Anath! Fire the artillery!
Neptune be thanked! Dry land again!
You can stop that now! They're all dead!
Excellent! They will not trouble any more farm animals!
Right now, I wish artillery had never been invented!
Look sharp, lads! They're dead but there's more to do!
Did you practice being stupid and cowardly, or does it come naturally\?
Right now, I wish artillery had never been invented!
Senior men! I think, it's time to--AAARRRGGGHHH!
Sir! Get yourself to a surgeon, sir!
Curse them ten thousand times! That was my best cloak!
Sir, NOW they're trying to kill us!
Anyone! Please! Bind my eyes and point me at the foe!
If any of you men run, you will answer with your heads!
I will kill any man with fear in his heart!
Honour! Honour\? We fight for our lives as well!
I think I'm going to throw up!
I think I'm going to throw up!
I hate it when you make cheap jokes…
Not on my time you don't!
This battle's going to the dogs, then!
Not on my time you don't!
Send them to Barinthus' kingdom, to drown amongst the fish!
If them elephants charge, don't forget to scream.
I don't think elephants tell jokes.
You have got to be joking!
By Zeus and Ares, I swear that I will defend this place to my last breath and the last beat of my defiant heart! I expect no less of you! Make your farewells, and fight!
Will that scare them off- Right! Very funny…
By Sulis! It's warm in here.

O gods! Give us the strength to cut down these Egyptian jackals! Their foul mishapen gods offend all men and the heavens too! Let us be your wrath! Strengthen our sword arms, fill our hearts with courage, and we will claim victory!
Let us drive back these desert hounds of Pharaoh! Outcast Greeks and the sons of slaves, they are not worthy! We will show them what it means to be true soldiers. Make ready, men!

You will have heard talk of the Pharaohs, our enemies' living gods. Gods\? Bah! It is a lie! Our enemies are lead by liars and falsehoods! They fight for lies and falsehoods! We shall cast them down! To arms!

We face the dogs of Egypt! Slaves of the so-called Pharaoh and of the line of Ptolemy. We'll drive these whelps, this property of inbred rulers, before us! Or kill them where they stand! To arms, men!
And the fire in your hearts!
On the bright side… Don't have to worry about them debts now.
Let them feel the strength of your blade!
This is it, lads! See you on the other side!
At last! Land once again! Now we destroy this bunch of women who dare stand in our way. After that voyage I'm bursting to crack heads. Follow me, boys, and we shall feast tonight!
I live to serve the mighty Carthage!
I live to serve the mighty Carthage!
From sea to land we are delivered! Praise the gods and give thanks so that we may prevail here today. Fight with me, men. I long for the sight and smell of death! Onward!
By Taranis, I am worried. For today we go forward as the last of our great warriors. The gods have not been kind to us. They have to give us strength today. Pray to them, men! Pray for victory!
It is a great and glorious thing to serve your people!
It is a great and glorious thing to serve your people!
Great. Where did that lot come from\?
Do not let the cowards live, by Ares!
This isn't going to end well, is it\?
After that voyage I've had enough of the sea. I look forward to smashing heads on land again. Let's get this done, men, and then we can drink and feast to our hearts content.
Every time! aim low, Jupiter and Mars curse you!
If anyone hangs back, I'll throw them over the wall myself!
I want to sacrifice to our gods in this place tonight! I want to show this pathetic enemy they are not safe anywhere! Kill them then pillage their homes! Assault these walls, in Camulus' name!
They just want to live, lad, same as us…
I knew they were a bunch of cowards.
Look! The gods have filled their bones with ice and fear!
The gulls will grow fat today!
Give them no mercy! Kill the cowards!
A thousand curses on their heads! Cowards!
Ha, ha! They're running for their lives!
Off you go, you useless tossers! And don't come back!
May the gods make us content with our lot this day.
Men, if you would be so kind: kill them!
There she goes! And those filthy bastards with her!
Men, if you would be so kind: kill them!
They've outmanoeuvred us! Standby for a bloody big jolt!
Kill them all! Let their widows weep for a thousand years!
Only if you want it, sir.
Grab any flotsam you can, men!
No! No! Not a watery grave!
Has anyone got a child to sacrifice. The gods seem to hate us today.
Get rid of your gear! Anything that will weigh you down.
I have just had a thought: I think they are trying to kill us.
This battle's going to the dogs, then!
I hate it when you make cheap jokes…
You can stop that now! They're all dead!
Come on, stand up like a man!
Those bastards are altogether too keen on shooting at us, I think.
Gods bless you! Enjoy your next life!
Standing here like this is a bit too honourable, in my opinion!
But have too much good sense!
I told you that was sharp, you twat!
But have too much good sense!
I will cut down any man who flinches!
Thank the gods! I didn't drown!
Dry land! Excellent! I never did like fish!
Thank the gods! I didn't drown!
Yes, sir. But is it sharp\?
This blade has always been in our family. It is a heavy burden.
If they charge, surround them, men. Bring those elephants down!
Elephants! What are we meant to fight them with\?
I would journey to the ends of the world for Makedon!
I would journey to the ends of the world for Makedon!
Would that I were as swift as Hermes!
Would that I were as swift as Hermes!
Homeless Greeks and their slaves: that is who we face! Do not misjudge them, for even a whipped mongrel can muster some courage! But if we stand firm they will break and run in fear! Make ready!

Egypt has been brought low by the Pharaoh and his court of disgusting minions if that is the best army that can oppose us! Stateless Greek vagabonds and slaves are not soldiers! They are easy meat! Make ready!

Do not fear Egyptians, men! They are shadow-men, and have none of the former glory of their land! They play at war, and I do not! Put your faith in me: I I speak the truth. We shall have victory today! To arms!
If I die today you better all come with me!
They're may be more of them but we are stronger!

Do not be disheartened, men! We should not fear these dung beetles of Egypt! They lack your courage and discipline! They are a rabble, of low-born Greeks and the spawn of scorpions. They will not stand! To arms!
Good, reinforcements. What banner do they march under\?
Make ready! When that ramp drops… We charge.
May Tyr put blood on your blades today!
Don't be too eager for them to find their courage!
They take flight, the cowards! Come back!
No better sight than the enemy sent to the depths.
Apart from ones we've looted first.
Cut the cowards down as they run!
Men! Prepare to fight for your lives and your honour!
Men! Prepare to fight for your lives and your honour!
Let's pray they're like you and that whore. Limp but keen!
Reminds me of a night in Athens... Couldn't walk for a week.
My father taunted me like that once. I killed him for it.
Look alert at your posts, men. Our admiral is watching.
It's the admiral! There! Hello! Sir! We love you!
He brings glory and honour to Egypt, our admiral does.
Steady on, boy! Stop waving at him!
We still have a wind, my lord!
Either that, or they've a cargo of dung, sir!
Mars curse them! They are fighting back!
Leave me! I will go down with the ship.
That lot, over there, don't look too friendly.
Neptune send us a breeze! Our enemies are scared, then!
Better to be moving at least, than a sitting target.
My finest wine for the first kill!
This is my day of glory!
There's enough killing today for everyone!
Would you like a last morsel\?
This is my day of glory!
There's enough killing today for everyone!
They're just a load of stinking, pig-fondling peasants!
Peasants\? I don't think the enemy are quite that noble!
I have chosen where I will die. You should do the same.
Right lads! If you get lost, take the nearest tavern and hold it against all comers!
Elephants\? More trouble than they're worth, lad!
Do you think you are going to live for long against a giant sodding elephant if you run, you useless TWAT\?
Watch out! It's those big bastard elephants!
Feel free to cut them open! Stick it where the sun don't shine!
Drive them from the deck! Repel these dogs!
We fight or we die, lads… Kill 'em all!
Who said you could be seasick\? Clean it up!
Has anybody seen the standard recently\?
Soldier! Put that down! RIGHT NOW!
You lazy, horrible litte soldiers! Kill them!
Can't take anymore, eh\? Then it's over the side with you!

There is a streak of cruelty in those Greeks yonder that allows them to treat other peoples with vicious contempt! Their ill-judged superiority lets them lie, kill, cheat and steal as they will! Well, today we end their foulness!
That Greek army looks rather handsome. Perhaps, if they fight as well as they look, then this might be a challenge. But I doubt it. They will be writing girly poems to each other, I'm sure! Stand to!

Prepare yourselves, good sons of Rome, to fight treacherous and unmanly Greeks! Unmanly, I say, but not to be underestimated: they can bite and scratch like any other backstreet floozies! Give them the sword!
Do not puke over the side! It upsets the tritons!
I should have worn different sandals…
I should have worn different sandals…
Make your shots count! They bloody well will!
Attack! Defend! Attack! HA! Attack is best!
Can't anyone see we are losing here.
We are losing too many men here!
I had a dream that one day a great army of ours would rise up and destroy all the Britons. That may be in years to come but today we shall start by sweeping away this lot.
No, but we can die well.
Death! Or glory! And where's my sword\?
This is madness! We can't win!
Quiet! Next man to speak, I will kill him!
Don't worry, sir. We'll make sure it was.
Hesitate and you're dead. Kill them quick, and we can take this wall.
Last one in's a Roman bastard!
Last one in's a Roman bastard!
Last one in's a Roman bastard!
Last one in's a Roman bastard!
Last one in's a Roman bastard!
I trust this was the right thing to do.
When we get in there I want them to beg for death.
They flee, lads! Like the spineless slugs they are!
You've had your fun! Let them drown peaceful like!
Praise the gods, what a glorious sight!
Another notch on the mast, sir.
Come on, boy! There's spoil to be harvested.
You've done well, all of you.
gods be merciful, they're ramming us!
Hold onto something. This is going get rough.
They insult our honour, men. Make them pay!
It's the admiral! He must smell victory!
He's the best I've ever served under, that admiral.
Quit your whining. We know they're there now.
If we can find some wreckage, we may still have a chance.
The enemy\? Not worth a fart, the lot of them!
The enemy\? Not worth a fart, the lot of them!
The ancestors are watching, my brothers! Show them mortal courage!
Show them a mortal arse, more like…
What shame is there in death\?
Don't you worry about them elephants. Stick by me!
Look! Over there! Grey. Big. Tusks. Long nose. Umm…
They've come to say hello, men! Let them have it!
By Hera's tits, the admiral looks good enough to-
Done! It's more likely to hit us than them.
Bet you my next shot will be closer.
Shezmu curses us! Anhur curses us! They send us more enemies!
Vulcan's brazen buttocks! Where'd they get those\?
Drive them back! Take the fight to them!
Then throw him overboard and pull twice as hard.
How dare you start bloody weeping!
Stop bleeding now, sir! Upsets the lads.
You there! THAT is a weapon, not a pitchfork!
There's nothing like the freedom of the sea. The wind in your hair!
Fire! By Hathor's horns fire, will you!

Their reputation and appearance are fearsome but hear me, men, when I say these Gauls are worthless! They are like flea-ridden dogs and dangerous only in a pack! Like dogs, we need only kill their leaders to cow the rest!

Pay these Gauls no mind! Ignore their shouts and insults for they are trying to find their courage! We need take no such action: we know our duty! So, make ready. Today we slay some filthy swineherds!

Our foes are mostly Greek and given to worrying about poetry or some similar womanly nonsense! This gives them little time for manly pursuits useful in war! So, prepare yourselves, Romans, and good luck!

These Gaulish pigs will regret the day they took arms against us! Men of the east, we will show them true courage and true honour! We will drive them from here in disgrace! Victory! Victory will be ours!
O! My heart is a-flutter. No, hang on, it's wind! Greeks do that to me. I see a living Greek and my mouth fills with vomit… So, let's kill them all, and having done that, we'll rob their corpses!

These Gallic pigs know how to fight, but only as a rabid dog bites and claws at any who come near! Their courage is mead-granted. They are unruly and unpredictable, not true soldiers! We will use that, and defeat them!

Is there anything more pathetic than a warlike Greek\? Anything\? A second warlike Greek, perhaps. Over there, awaiting death at your hands, are many of those creatures. Prepare yourselves for battle!
I have yet to meet a Greek I liked, other than at his funeral! Let us be a plague, then, upon our enemies and make sure Hades is busy welcoming Greek souls today! Take up your arms!

I have heard it said that Greeks like a good argument. They also like good food, fine wine, talking, learning and generally being civilized. That's very nice, but war is not a nice business. Why are they here\?

I do not like these Greeks. They hide their womanly ways behind witty manners and clever remarks, while disdaining honest Roman virtues. Will they still be witty when they are dying, I wonder\? To arms!

Greeks are not made for war. They are made for growing olives, writing poetry, and banging on about their bloody boring ideas. Today we are going to show them an idea called fighting". They won't like it!"

Bloody Greek fops! Look at them over there! Polishing their armour, dressing their hair and generally mincing about like great bearded schoolgirls! Bah! Would that the gods would poison the lot! Well, get yourselves ready!

I would not presume on Zeus or Ares for help today! We will be worthy of their praise instead, by crushing those who defend this place utterly! Let us show the world that we are true soldiers! Stand ready!
Keep your aim low! Hit them in their fat bellies!
Come men, once more unto the breach, once more!
We will fight or die right here!

Those Partians over there are no better than goat-stealing desert bandits. I hope they steal the goats to eat but... with Parthians, who can say\? Ha! The god of goats will thank us for saving his flock! Make ready!

That collection of perfumed fools is a Parthian army. They look impressive, don't they\? Well, they are not warriors, only painted catamites in pretty uniforms! They will run, soon enough! Now, to arms!
Parthians, Parthians, Parthians… They are the rats of the world, men, nibbling at the crumbs others drop from their tables. Even their cities resemble nothing as much as open air sewers! Kill them!
Careful with that! You'll hurt someone!
I can do this... Don't look down. I won't look down.
I don't know which is worse, stuck in here with you lot or out there with them.
The girls in engineering have done their work. Now it's our turn.
Gaul is mother to us all!
Gaul is mother to us all!
Gaul is mother to us all!
Honour the gods and your ancestors!
Honour the gods and your ancestors!
Honour the gods and your ancestors!
Merciful gods, you have carried us whole to these shores and in return we pledge you victory! In the name of blessed Pharaoh, we will put these dogs to the sword or take our places in the underworld!
I live to serve the people of Gaul!
I live to serve the people of Gaul!
I live to serve the people of Gaul!
What about us having a breather\?
Don't let them rest! Kill! Kill the buggers!
Push them back! Push them back!
Keep at them! Don't let them rally!
Come on! Gut these bastards as they run!
Keep a weather eye open, men!
Keep a weather eye open, men!
Come on then, if you think you're hard enough!
They will have to pay for that!
Stab the bastards in the back, if that's what it takes!
Keep going! They're running! They're running!
Our admiral is a sly one, is he not\?
I want their banner! To me, men, to me!
Eyes on your work, men! The admiral wants this finished.
The gods do seem to have granted him another victory.
What are you lot doing\? Get to work, you curs!
Straighten those lines, if you please! No untidiness!
You know, I think I've seen more threatening whores!
Sounds right. You have poor taste in whores.
We will not give up! Death will take our foes!
Make ready! Won't be long now!
May their false gods help them if they think we will stand for this!
Fight! Drive back these gutless worms!
Kill! Kill! Kill! Kill! How many more times\?
Pull away, men! Let's get out of here!
I love the sea. It reminds me of my mother's -
Aim at the men, not the woodwork, you lump of gull-shit!
Make sure it hurts, by all the gods!
True, but your average Pompeian biddy is pretty nasty too!
You know, there are old women in Capua more dangerous than them!
I wouldn't show off about it, boy.

An army of merchants, desert hoppers and farmers. Look to your water, boys, they'll be after it! Not much where they come from. Be merciful! Cut them open and they'll be able to drink their own blood!
Do not be afraid! These Gauls are little more than savages. We will show them what true courage is, men! We will put them to flight and send them scurrying back to their hovels! To arms!

An unwashed and unpleasant folk, these Gauls find their courage in strong drink! We need no such draught of bravery! We are men, not reeking drunks! We will send these filthy whoresons to their dark afterlife! Make ready!

Have no mercy in your hearts today! The barbarian hordes over there have no mercy! They do not even have a word for mercy in their pig-grunting of a language! Any man with mercy in his heart will answer to me! Make ready!
By the gods, that smell! They must be from the east with their spicy foods and camel shit! They never wash and they wipe their arses with sand. Be sure not to shake hands! Just cut them off!
Barbarians threaten everything that we as a people believe! Good order, honesty, justice, freedom, prosperity and piety would be swept away in an instant by those fiends! That is why we fight them!

Call me superstitious but these men of the East worry me. They mutter prayers in battle in their strange tongues. They may be summoning demons. Send them to their afterlife before they use their magic! Kill them quickly!
Bloody foreigners and their ways. Cowards and cheats the lot of them. I want you to show no mercy today, men! This pagan army is to be cut down by divine order! Take no prisoners! Leave no one alive!
By my bowels! This will be a good day, brothers! They love their gold in the East and wear a lot of jewellery and even decorate their beasts. Yes, we shall be rich by the end of the day!
May Seker greet them with open arms.

Ha, ha! Yes the good old sun-worshipping, camel-loving, beetle-shitting fol! Oh, my friends, we are in for a treat. Their soldiers are slaves and useless. Their leaders fat and rich! Let's get amongst them!
I hate the Easterners! They are shifty and cunning and will do anything to stab you in the back. They are not honest fighters. They make me nervous! We must win today, brothers. Prepare yourselves!
When we have thrown these invaders back into the sea, I hope that Neptune will drown them all! I want these bastards dead, by sword or sea matters not, but dead! Stand ready!

Mead-drunk, blood-drunk fools! You need more than strength to win battles, you stupid Gauls! We match the strength of any Gauls with our own, but it will be our discipline and my tactics that will grant us victory!

Do not let these Gallic swines rob you of your bravery! We are worth ten times their number! They lack discipline and skill, and their courage is not their own! A taste of our steel, and they will run!

I pray now to Ares and Haephestus, that they will send us aid on this blackest of days, in this most perilous of battles! None will stand for our people if we fall, so gods of our fathers, aid us now!
Camels and dung beetles! What do we have here\? I see an army, of sorts, lead by a general, of sorts! But they would surely be happier counting coins or whores than fighting! Let's be at them, then!

By all the gods, what a collection of brigands, thieves and desert scorpions! And they call themselves an army! Well, men, we shall soon show these eastern imposters what a real army does! Stand ready!

This is the last rat-hole, my lads! The last filthy, stinking heap of dung to be cleared away… It is not a job for soldiers, but it is a job we must do. Now, attack swiftly and live to celebrate victory!

This is the last task, men. This is the final bolt-hole for our enemies. They have nothing left. Remember, as we go forwards, that the trapped beast is always dangerous and can bite one last time. To arms!

This settlement, this collection of dungheaps, this sink of depravity and unmanly vice, is the last hiding place for our enemies! Men: make it their final tomb! To the walls! For our glorious victory!
When we are done here, only the dead will remain within these walls! Any who survive will soon long for death rather than servitude! Their lives and wealth are ours for the taking! Make ready!
My great warriors of Andraste! For the glory of the god of war, who knows well enough that defence is as noble an action as attack, we will hold our ground! Let them come!

Friends, you know me and how hard I will try to spare even a single drop of my fellow warrior's blood. But some will die today as our brothers have fallen before. Today we fight for them and the glory of Tuisto!
We can take these curs with us!
The Old Ones will watch and smile with pride as they look down on this fight. As wave after wave of the enemy are repelled by our defence they shall feast in our honour!
I ask you once again to prepare for battle, my loyal warriors. Once again into the fray we go and once again we shall fight side by side. And I thank you, once again, for this honour! In Tyr's name!
Centurions! Get them moving, if you please!
I am sick of all this!
In Rome's service I never tire.
Come on, heroes, do you want to live forever\?
We must not retreat. Keep fighting to the last!
Be ready, men. When the ramp drops, we charge.
Stab the bastards in the back, if that's what it takes!
Keep going! They're running! They're running!
Kill them all, lad, especially the ones who run!
I want their banner! To me, men, to me!
Come back and fight, you bastards!
Gods above, watch over your servant.
That's our admiral, lad. He's a fine figure of a man.
He's a cunning bugger, our admiral. I like him.
Gods above, watch over your servant.
We will just have to cut out their tongues then.
Don't let them rest! Kill! Kill the buggers!
Push them back! Push them back!
Keep at them! Don't let them rally!
Look sharp, lads, it's the admiral!
The admiral is crushing them! He fights like a god!
We still have a wind, my lord!
What about us having a breather\?
The Gods have revealed their will.
I have failed my mission, my lord.
The Gods have revealed their will.
I have failed my mission, my lord.
I swear I will not fail again!
My soul has been found wanting!
The Goddess has revealed her will.
Seth has cursed me with failure!
Keep an eye on that lot.
There is no greater enemy than pride.
The Goddess has revealed her will.
Seth has cursed me with failure!
My soul has been found wanting!
I swear I will not fail again!
There is no greater enemy than pride.
Hail to the Mother! How can I help\?
So, brave warriors, to our work!
This was my father's sword. I will not dishonour him.
This is a good place to die!
So, brave warriors, to our work!
This was my father's sword. I will not dishonour him.
This is a good place to die!
I live to serve the people of Briton!
Mutilate the dead! Leave them with nothing for the next life!
I live to serve the people of Briton!
Sir, no, sir. Not a bit, sir.
Hail to the Mother! How can I help\?
I live to serve the people of Briton!
Do I look like I care that you are seasick, oarsman\?
Clear for action! Quickly now! Last man in place will be punished!
Who gave you permission to be sick\?
I live to serve the people of Briton!
Hail to the Mother! How can I help\?
Hail to the Mother! How can I help\?
To your posts! Defend them with your lives!
I hope Arwen will be there to kiss my brow when I die.
May Menthi protect the admiral now.
Make sure it hurts, by all the gods!
Stop waving that sword, you utter fool!
I don't care if it hurst, you bunch of girls!
Put some effort in! I'll whip anyone who slackens!
Bloody gulls keep getting in the way!
We hunger for blood and battle!

It is hard, I know, to understand that we have an honourable duty here! It is not just to kill those unwashed fools, although that is a worthy thing! No, we come to bring civilization! It seems a waste! To arms!
I fear there may be little loot to be found among the barbarians yonder when they are decent, honest corpses! They do not look rich enough to buy a goblet of piss! However, we must kill them!

Well, our enemies have some impressive beards and moustaches! What a pity that their wits are so completely lacking! If they had any understanding of our might, they would run back to their hovels! Make ready!

Those wild creatures over there are not true men, but pig-spawned beasts of the forests and wastes. They make walk as men, and even talk like men after a fashion but do not be fooled! Be wary, and be prepared!

I am sure that when our foes have stopped worshipping their sacred pig, or whatever foulness the animal endures at their hands, we shall have a battle! When the time comes, kill your barbarian cleanly and move on!

Have you ever seen a bigger collection of moon-faced, slack-jawed, dribbling, piss-stained peasants than that lot\? It is easy to see why we call them barbarians! Well, make ready, men! They need killing!
I despise barbarians! They are monsters, spawned in darkness and filth, ignorant of all that is good and true! That is why we must fight them! That is why we must win!

I can smell our enemies from here, men! Fear does that to barbarians! Fear, and strong drink! They would not stand to fight unless their bellies were swollen with booze! We will empty them presently! Make ready!
The long road of war has lead us, at last, to this final gateway! Beyond lies the last refuge of our cowardly and hated enemies! All who resist face the sword! All who yield face slavery! Forward!

This ants' nest of villainy is the last hiding place of our enemies. Beyond the hovels within those walls they have nothing. After today, they will be forgotten, except in the monuments to our victory! Onwards!
I will speak plainly. Men, our enemy stand upon the edge of an abyss. One small push, and they plunge to their doom! It is up to us to escort" them to their well-deserved deaths! Prepare!"

Our enemies cannot afford to let this place fall! There are no more bolt-holes for them. That means hard fighting, as you know. But think of our glory when it falls! It will be a triumph worthy of our arms!

Our foes must make this last stand, no matter how foolish, or the gods themselves will not remember them! One day, possibly, a bored poet will compose a tedious verse about their fate. But today, we attack!
May the gods be with you, men!
Our forefathers were mighty men, and we must be the same today! This is the last place the enemy can call their own and, by dawn tomorrow, it must be utterly cast down. Leave nothing!
I could do more in service to the people.
I never tire in the peoples service.
There is more I could do.
The gods inform me there is more I could do.
I can't go on! They're too many of them.
In your service I never tire.
I want them dead! DEAD! Do you hear me\?
We are few, but all the more glory for us… Keep fighting!
Get across quickly, lad. Better to fight on the wall than fall.
By sea or by mountain, sire\?
By sea or by mountain, sire\?
Is that meant to be a choice\?
Just a wound my lord, fear not.
I am not ready to die.
It is just a wound, I shall live.
This wound will heal, in time.
It is just a wound, I shall live.
It's just a wound, I'll tend to it.
Fight, curse your entrails with maggots! Fight!
Just a wound my lord, fear not.
Fear not, my lord, I will survive.
This wound will heal, in time.
I have survived greater wounds than these.
Fear not, my lord, I will survive.
I have suffered far worse, my lord.
It's just a wound, I'll tend to it.
I have suffered far worse, my lord.
This wound will heal, in time.
Order the men to pursue, cut them down.
This wound will heal, in time.
I have survived greater wounds than these.
I am not ready to die.
I'm glad they're in good voice! Means they'll scream louder later!
Cheer you, curs. Raise your voices for our admiral!
Go on admiral! Let's finish them off!
This lot don't look too bad. If anymore turn up…
Look to the ship, men, and be ready with your weapons.
Why does everyone we meet always want to kill us\?
This weather. It's not good for my knees.
Why does everyone we meet always want to kill us\?
Prepare! Make ready, and cheer, you miserable sods!
Nothing fancy today! Just kill the buggers!
Dagon's wrath! They're firing at us!
Don't hold with elephants! Nasty things!
Steersman! Get those sailors working as if they mean it!
How dare they! Cut them down, men!
Praise Anath! She smiles on us today!
I think I'll stay in bed next time someone says battle!""
Ten thousand curses! And ten thousand more!
Don't call me sir! I work for my money!
Come on! They are supposed to fight us!
Strike low! Strike low! Into their bellies!
Oarsmen! On my order! Keep in time!

They outnumber us, but each of us is worth ten of those dogs and, should we fall, we will have cost them blood and treasure! We will spit defiance at these aggressors! For our people! That is a glorious death!

We face many foes this day, but what of it\? It will be bloody work, but the rewards: think of the honour, the glory, and the spoils that will be yours when we are victorious! All that can be gained, if you but find your courage!

Their numbers make them arrogant, but their army is a lumbering beast, slow and easy to outwit. Today, we become the agile hunter. Quick and daring will be our watchwords, and we will goad them into folly and wear them down!

Their presence here is insulting, and it will be their downfall! I'd be nowhere else this day, nowhere but here, standing alongside my soldiers. For, if we stand together, their numbers mean little when counted against our courage!

Gods, hear our prayers! We are outnumbered but with your aid we would throw back these alien rabble. Grant us victory or be merciful on us in death, for we fight in your names! Make your peace, men, and make ready!
What can we do against elephants\?

I will not lie to you, today will be bloody, and many will die. But if you can find your courage and sharpen your will to a grim purpose, we will fill the field with their dead! if we hold, our victory will be glorious!
Stand tall, men. We will defy these beasts!

Arrogance and overconfidence are a heavy meal before battle, and our enemy has gorged on both! Our action will be swift, we will cut off this beast's head, cut out its heart as it still slumbers, and the body will fall!
Die. Kill them as we do.
Today will add another triumph to the history of our people's greatness! Yes, we are outnumbered but so what\? All we need to do is keep our heads, and we will have victory! Make ready for the fight!
We face many foes here today. So what\? Fortune is the companion of courage. If we have bravery in our hearts, the gods will favour us with victory. This I firmly believe! To arms!

Would you be remembered as cowards\? Our gods, ancestors and people watch us! Would you dishonour them\? If we are destined to die this day, let us take these filth with us, and drag them with us to the underworld! For we will not go meekly!
So then, the gods test us once more. Will we be worthy of the challenge\? I look around me, and I have hope. I look at the enemy and I have certainty! Now, to arms!
Today we will fight as our forefathers did: against dreadful odds! And, like them, we will triumph and add further glory to the name of our people! The hour approaches! Make ready!
Put your backs in to it!
Put your backs in to it!

Be thankful, men! The sea gods did not drag them into the depths and the dogs have managed to get ashore! We now get to show our courage instead, and drive these whelps back to their ships! Send them home, their tails between their legs!
Put your backs in to it!

Gods! Why did you not drown these curs when you had the chance\? If it is battle you want to see, do us some honour and throw us more than sprats to fight! The greater our victory, the greater your glory in granting it.
Put your backs in to it!
Here and no farther! This sea-rabble will not gain a foothold! We will cut them down or drive them back to the sea, men! They will not gain so much as a toehold here, not while we guard these shores!
Put your backs in to it!
Let us drive these whelps back into the sea, men! We will cut them down before they get a foothold, and throw their carcases back for the fish and crabs to feast on! They will not take this land!

We have landed ourselves a poor catch, men! Look at the motley haul of fish the sea has spewed up upon our shores! When we're done, we will leave what's left for the crabs and for the seabirds. Make ready, men!
Put your backs in to it!

We make our stand here, and we will drive them from these shores! These dogs will not get a foothold, we will drive them back into the shallows! Drive them back into the depths, to die amongst the fishes!
Put your backs in to it!

We will gut these invaders like fishes: gut them and leave their entrails for the birds! After today they will think twice about threatening these shores, for they will know we hold them and we are ready to fight!

We will stand! We will stand, and they will break against us as the waves break against cliffs. We will turn them back, and they will flee! Draw your weapons, and prepare yourselves, men! We will turn back this tide!
Death will take come on swift wings.
Death will take come on swift wings.
My blade will taste blood this night.
The hand that is hacked off can no longer steal...
My blade will taste blood this night.
The hand that is hacked off can no longer steal...
I shall see them to their ancestors.
They will trouble you no longer.
I shall see them to their ancestors.
They will trouble you no longer.
I shall see them to their ancestors.
I shall see them to their ancestors.
Put your backs in to it!
Put your backs in to it!
I will send them into the dark.
I will send them into the dark.
My hands are yours to command.
My hands are yours to command.
The greatest admiral Parthia has ever seen.
All must die at the appointed hour.
All must die at the appointed hour.
Great Cicolluis's tits! Our strength knows no boundaries. This army is their last and so we now face a battle to rid this world of this scum! Be ruthless! Be wary! Be deadly!
How can I assist Rome further\?
I could do more in service to the people.
I hope it hurts, you bastard!
I never tire in the peoples service.
I could do more in the service of Rome.
And so it comes down to this. Our precious homes and our families in them. I will not stop until they leave or I die. I ask you to join me and make your families proud!
I never tire in service to Rome.
There is more I could do.
A true Roman's work is never done.
The gods inform me there is more I could do.
More blood, men! I want more blood!
It is a great and glorious thing to die for Rome!
Are you ready to serve Rome\?!
Are you ready to serve Rome\?!

Honour, valour, glory, riches, even women! All that means nothing today. For we fight not for those petty things! Today we fight for survival! Win and our people have a future. Lose and it is all over!
It is a great and glorious thing to die for Rome!
Ask not what your homeland can do for you, ask what you can do for your homeland! Now, in these coming few hours our people's future is at stake. Defend it with your lives!
The impudence! Landing on our shores! So this is the verse in the song when they are massacred on the beaches. We shall overcome this invasion! We shall slaughter each and every one of them!
In your service I never tire.
They think they can come here, disembark and take on my mighty warriors\? Huh\? May their gods bless them for they have caught me on an angry day! Teach them a lesson, boys!
Men, once they have come ashore they will have nowhere to go. We shall hold them here and cut them down. Allow them no time to retreat to their boat. Finish them on land!
Keep fighting! Take them down with us!
So they believe they can simply step off their boat and come to this shore and defeat us, do they\? We are waiting and we shall show them a thing or two about hospitality! Cut them open lads!
I cannot abide it when they attack from the sea! Do they not know who we are! They shall fall at the blows of my wrath! We shall send them back where they came from or send them to their deaths!
I want them slit from ear to ear. I want their entrails gutted and fed to the fish. Understand\? How dare they land on these shores! Beat them back into the sea or leave them dead on the beach!
Hit them hard as soon as they come ashore. They will still be finding their land legs. Do not give them time to settle. Send them all back where they came from!
Last one out buys the beers.
They will have just got off the boat so we strike fast and true! Hopefully they will all be seasick and more concerned about their stomachs than our blades! Give them no time to rest!
We shall fight them on the beaches! We shall fight them back into the sea. The waves will turn red with blood and we shall make this offering to the gods of war!
May Donar strike these unholy wretches down! They are fearsome in their colour and formations. What new evil do they bring! Today we will find out what Pontus has to offer. And we shall be tested!
Give me an oar, we'll get there faster!
Give me an oar, we'll get there faster!
Vulcan's iron blade! I think they want blood this time
Rowing is good for the arms!
I've seen worse. Once the Romans flashed at us.
Cheer than man who gave us victory! Cheer our admiral, lads!
Fight, curse your entrails with maggots! Fight!
Is that the admiral\? What a leader! What a man! I'd happily die for him.
Sir, the enemy are not cooperating today!
You've been at sea too long.
Rowing is good for the arms!
Although I have failed, I will never give up!
I may have failed but I am not a failure!
My honour has turned to falaadah!
I may have failed but I am not a failure!
My honour has turned to falaadah!
It would seem I have... failed.
Although I have failed, I will never give up!
I don't fail. Things don't go as planned. Sometimes.
There's our enemy, lads. Lazy sons of whores the lot.
There is a fine line between failure and fate.
I will battle through my failure.
I don't fail. Things don't go as planned. Sometimes.
It'll take more than that to kill me!
I have failed but I live to fight on!
It would seem I have... failed.
I have failed but I live to fight on!
It'll take more than that to kill me!
I will battle through my failure.
There is a fine line between failure and fate.
If I catch anyone being idle, I'll pitch them into the sea!
Hail to the Mother! How can I help\?
This is not a good place to die.
You know, with a good woman, today could be fun!
Warriors! Repel boarders, if you please!
This is not a good place to die.
You know, with a good woman, today could be fun!
I live to serve the people of Briton!
Keep them fighting, decurions, if you please!
Remember! They're shitting it because we're coming!
Remember who you are! Now fight!
I live to serve the people of Briton!
Hold fast now! They're only elephants!
Hail to the Mother! How can I help\?
I live to serve the people of Briton!
Haul, you miserable wretches, haul away!
I live to serve the people of Briton!
Hail to the Mother! How can I help\?
Hail to the Mother! How can I help\?
Defend to the last man! Send them to the depths of the ocean!
You heard him! Nothing to worry about!
Fire, you sea-wolves! Kill them now!
Fight! We kill them or they kill us!
I've seen dockside floozies who can pull better than you lot!
Steersman! Get those sailors working as if they mean it!
Be brave! We're fighting girls today!
A pity. That was my grandfather's…
Is it me, sir, or are they a bit angry over there\?
Gone, gone, like tears in rain…
They seem a bit cross today, the pigs!
It is a bad cut. You will live.
Put that head down! Stand ready!
This is bad. I seem to have lost my eye.
Give it to them in their bellies!
He's flashing his arse at us!
Then use it as a target.
You should be more frightened of me than those bloody elephants.
The bigger they are, the harder they fall!
The enemy is outside. They want to be in here. Among you. And your women. And your children. They want everything. But we shall deny them! To arms, men! Protect your homes!
Normally I would wish you all well and give a rousing speech. But today we fight for the very future of our people. So I have but one order. DO NOT DIE!

If we fail today we shall lose more than our honour, more than our lives. We shall lose all those lives to come, the future generations of our people. The gods will not accept this! Fight til the last!
I don't care if you live or die today. What I do care about is if there is anything left to live for by the end of this battle! So fight with every last drop of blood in your veins!
A Greek's work is never done.
You have only one order to follow today, men. Do not stop fighting until you die! Understand\? No getting tired! No giving up! No surrender! No excuses! This is our last stand!
I never tire in service to the people.
This is our last stand, men. If we fall here today, our people will be defeated and there will be nowhere left to run. We fight for everything today! We fight for the future of our tribe!

These foreigners mean to sack this place, run riot and take everything from us! Well, we are going to show them the bloody terror of their darkest nightmares. We will make them regret their decision to ever come here!
I could hit their commander from here.
With Mithra as our witness do want a small wager, lad\?
In Rome's service I never tire.
Bit of battle will stiffen you up again!
My pilum has definitely gone all limp.
I'm not going to go die without a fight!
More exciting than hunting, that's for sure.

There is a darkness at the heart of our foes: a dark evil that lurks in their forest homes. It feeds on blood and suffering. That is why we oppose these Germans, because of their barbaric wickedness! Now, to arms!
But you can't eat what you kill today!
Watch it, mate! I can still swung a sword in here!
When the time comes, do not falter. We will take their walls!

I am pleasantly surprised! I think the German scum over there have bathed this year! I am sure that the carrion birds are grateful, as even they have standards about the guts they eat! Anyway, make ready!

Gods give us strength! And grant us strong stomachs so that we don't puke at the smell of these German wretches! We stand against woodland filth and vermin today, men: creatures no better than wolves! Kill them!

Is that Germans I smell\? No other people smell like that! Only German women-folk would find the stench of pigs, forest mud and unwashed arses much to their liking! Well, try not to lose your breakfasts, and good luck!
It's like the insides of your mother's -
I hate Germans! They have nasty beards, nasty tempers and very nasty choppers! Now, with the blessing of the gods, we shall do our best to make their deaths as nasty as possible! Stand ready, men!
Germans! We face Germans here! I am sorry, men, for I had hoped to give you better sport than these bearded lunatics. Still, they may be too stupid to run away, but they die as readily as other men!

Germans are large, men, all respects save one or two. Firstly, their women are very disappointed. Oh! Work it out for yourselves! Secondly, they are stupid. Dull. Thick. As clever as dung. They need killing!
Ha! I'd give them the runs, and you know it!
Fight, you bastards, or I will gut you for the crows!
Hack them down! Kill them all!
Let them carry on. They won't be laughing later.
I think that's the admiral! Look! Over there.
Fight, you bastards! Fight like lions!
Gods bless our glorious admiral! He will prevail today!
Ba'al's beard! Where did those bastards spring from\?
Haul this… Move that… Row… You'd think we were slaves!
The enemy... They trouble my soul.
So. Where do you think we'll be tomorrow\?
You know, I really wish I'd paid that last whore…
The enemy... They trouble my soul.
The ancestors are unquiet. We will die here.
So. Where do you think we'll be tomorrow\?
Any more from you, and I'll have you chained in place!
Soon be over! Once they're dead, find a nice quite whorehouse and enjoy yourselves!
We're going in and we're going to conquer! You hear me\?
For what they are about to receive, gods make them truly fearful!
Hang on to your oars, you fools!
Ares send them boils! Those were my best greaves!
Fire, you curs! Teach them pain!
Fire! Fire, you salt-stained sea-dogs! Fire!
Artillery is the death of courage!
Repel these worms! Feed them to the fish, lads!
Get out the way! Let the sailors do their work, you fool!
Put your backs into it! Heave!
Artillery is the death of courage!
All hands! Make ready to defend the ship!
Send them screaming to the afterlife!
Watch it! You nearly had my head!
We carry no dead weight! Anyone who doesn't pull goes overboard!
Out of the water! Move on now!
Out of the water! Move on now!
Aim for their captain! He's the tall ugly bugger!
I have it on good authority that it is rare to see the faces of Pontic soldiers. Normally, it is only their backs on display to the enemy as they run for cover! Let's give them reason to run!

I have heard that mountain folk are often mad. I think it may be something to do with having one long leg and one short leg. That's bound to unbalance a man! That would also explain these dribbling fools from Pontus!
I want the widows of Pontus to curse us for a hundred years for what we do today! Let their orphans wail! I see no reason to be kind to this race of insolent men! To arms!
I pity the peasants yonder led astray by their cruel Pontic masters. Most likely, they were honest men and were swayed by false promises and lies. Now only death at our hands awaits them. Make ready!
By all the gods, these men of Pontus are fools! And insolent to boot! Who are they to dare to face us in battle\? Have their gods driven them mad\? I care not! Kill them!
Steady, I want a neat advance!
The people of Pontus, it seems, have taken to human sacrifice. That is the only explanation as to why they should have come here to die in such numbers. We had best oblige them! Make ready!
Pontus: I had to look it up on the map. A latrine pretending to be a country, lads! Well, they look like they crawled from the sewers! Let's fight them, but remember to wash your hands afterwards!
Put your backs in to it!
Put your backs in to it!
Put your backs in to it!
Put your backs in to it!
Put your backs in to it!
Kill their leaders! A denarius for the first man to kill a leader!
A Greek's work is never done.
I never tire in service to the people.
They have the upper hand but we will prevail!
Where did they come from\? Are they ours\?
There's enough of us to make it costly. Fight to the last!
Quicker we cross, the safer we'll be.
Keep a close eye on those men over there.
I can smell them from here.
Quiet men. I need to plan.
My failure will surely anger the gods.
I swear I will not fail again!
I swear I will not fail again!
My failure will surely anger the gods.
Forwards, men! Run them down! Take no prisoners!
Thank the gods, the admiral! He wins battles, and no mistake!
He's nothing like the stories they tell…
He waved! Did you see that\? The admiral waved at me!
By Shezmu, you're such a knob!
The admiral\? Who cares as long as he wins in them.
There is our foe. Ready yourselves, men.
Leave me! I will go down with the ship.
Clear the decks, and make ready!
Wine! A good woman! Regular meals! That's all I wanted!
All hands! Make ready to defend the ship!
And I hear blood is very good for the soil, sir!
This would be a good place to farm.
That is most excellent news, old friend!
If you're stupid, and born on a farm.
The omens were good, I hear: untroubled livers all round!
And you get them, along with a chance for glory!
I hear that the wine round here is very fine.
Right! I want a nice clean assault this time!
When this ramp drops, you move! No hanging about!
Elephants\? I'm not scared of- ELEPHANTS!
Elephants! We're in for it now!
You aren't making me happier, sir!
Get out the way! Let the sailors do their work, you fool!
Haul away! Ignore the enemy! The sea will kill us all in time!
Put your backs into it! Heave!
Get that foreign scum off my ship!
Fire! Take down those sons of whores!
I like artillery, but only when it's pointed at them!
Push them back! Send these sea-scum to the depths!
Thank Lady Tanit! We have prevailed! The cowards have been vanquished!
Oarmaster! Punishment for that man later! He's not trying!
I like artillery, but only when it's pointed at them!
All crew! Look to our defences!
At them! Not a moment's rest!
Keep it up, boys. She's away.
Fire! Fire, you salt-stained sea-dogs! Fire!
A hit! A hit! A very palpabe -
Send them all to the underworld!
Shut up and get on with it, you cock!

I won't fail you again, my lord.
I have let the tribe down.
That didn't go as well as I had hoped.
I won't fail you again, my lord.

Sir! Beg to report, sir, that we've no more am-money- shots, sir!

My widow will weep on the shore soon enough!
How many times… We're near. They're far away.
By Toutatis! They mean to fight us!
Hail, and well met indeed, men! There's our glorious general!
Is it too late to get out of this\?
More of them! The gods turn their backs on us!
More of the buggers coming. Still, the admiral will be pleased!
Worry not! A bit of an enemy fleet, man, is nothing!
You landsmen! Stop holding your bellies! You won't die!
Every man will do his utmost, or the fish will be well fed!
Starfish and sharks! Are you not brave men\?
Did you kill the owner of that head\?
No slacking now, men, keep everyone in the fight!
Watch what you're doing with that damned sword, you fool!
What a mess! Here they comes again!
Back! Live to fight another day!
Did you kill the owner of that head\?
No slacking now, men, keep everyone in the fight!
Watch what you're doing with that damned sword, you fool!
What a mess! Here they comes again!
Always is, lad! Why we get paid!
The banner, man, keep it up!
This is not war! This is not honour! It is slaughter!
Glad to see the back of that!
May the gods grant them swift deaths.
Have a care! Look out for splinters!
I am no maid, what would you have of me\?
Oi! I'm not gonna hang about all day!
Are you sure there is nothing else\?
I'm getting a twitchy sword hand!
I could be of further assistance.
I'm a warrior, not a milk maid!
There is more I could do.
They're having a good go, sir.
They can't hit us at this range.
There is more I could do.
I could be of further assistance.

Men! Be humble and pray to the gods! Make your offerings to the Old Ones and serve up your veneration to our ancestors. For today we need all the help we can get! To arms!
Charge home! No quarter! No mercy!
We may die here, but before that, we fight here!
Remember your loved ones! Do not shame them!
Ah. They are shouting insults now. Oh, I'm so scared.
Ah. They are shouting insults now. Oh, I'm so scared.
Ignore those sons of whores, lads! We'll answer soon enough.
Ah, bless, at least it gives them something to shout about before we sink them.
You've seen one shit-pit, boy, and you've seem them all.
Find your courage, men! The day is far from over!
The gods are watching, brothers! Fight like lions!
Keep them steady, Mars curse you!
I can see it from here!
Which way to the brothel\? My blood is up!
We made it. And to think, a whole new land…
Keep your heads down, you idots!
Keep your heads down, you idots!
Excellent! Now my humours are out of balance!
The Gods will see these wound heal swiftly.
Jupiter's cock, rocks and divine arse!
Fear not, I am beloved by the Gods.
So, the enemy think they can sink us\? Ha!
Excellent! Now my humours are out of balance!
All I do, I do for Rome!
All I do, I do for Rome!
Fear not, I am beloved by the Gods.
The Gods will see these wound heal swiftly.
Meet death with a smile in your eye! Get ready to fight with Garm!
That's done, then! Ares be thanked for His help!
Now, let us see if the gods are with us.
The general! He's as brave as three lions they say!
I've forgotten what I'm supposed to do!
More of them, I see. More glory for us, praise the gods!
Now, bosun, let us pray for a fair wind and a good fight!
Curses! That was my father's helmet!
Tell my children I died well…
Blades\? Blades! I'll give them death!
Not the face! Not the face!
I think our enemies are a little hostile at the moment.
Tell my children I died well…
Blades\? Blades! I'll give them death!
Not the face! Not the face!
Steady, man! Have you left your bravery in the winesack\?
Pull! Pull! Pull, you useless buggers! All is lost!
Come on! We'll live to fight another day!

I wish one day to travel peacefully in the East. See the land of Pontus and marvel at their beautiful cities. And women. But I want to see only Gauls there as part of a great Gallic empire. So kill these bastards!
Fight! Throw them from the walls!
My heart is heavy. May Anubis judge us wisely.
Fight and we shall stay free.
Ready yourselves, men. The day is not over yet.
When I was young the women sang of battles such as this. When a few brave warriors outdid the peasant hordes. Let them write new verses of us today! So they may sing of our victory!
The odds are against us, brothers. These are the battles where a true warrior makes his name. And so we fight knowing this day shall make us famous! We shall be remembered for this victory!
When I was a lad I once took on five men and killed them with my bare hands. Today we all need to fight like bears. This horde thinks they have the upper hand. Let them feel our might!
The enemy come in good numbers, friends. We look to be outdone. But my wife says size matters and we are bigger men, man to man! Let us cut them down like wheat! And sow their guts like corn!
Hold fire, you idiots, until you have a good target!
The more the merrier! Come, my fellow warriors, there is much to do this day! The blood of the enemy will soon wash this field in waves. There are so many heads to be removed my heart sings!
Here they come. For better or worse. May Britannia bless us!
Look at the bastards! The cowards seem to think there is safety in numbers! Well, shall we show them just what our people are made of\? Come to battle, my band of brothers!
Look at them all! Marvellous! My sword arm itches in anticipation! Let's to the fight and then feast merrily tonight! They shall regret they got out of bed today! There will be blood!
Men are masters of their fates.
Men are masters of their fates.
Silence! I want no gossip on my battlefield!
I live to serve the mighty Carthage!
I live to serve the mighty Carthage!
I live to serve the mighty Carthage!
I live to serve the mighty Carthage!
Lesser men stop fighting! We do not!
Be brave, my brothers! Take heart! Take heart!
Frightful, barbarous, dark-spawned, gull-shit noise! Ruins a good battle!
Let them shout and rant, men, we'll answer with our weapons.
Don't know. Can't make it out. Something foreign.
Go on, you buggers! Get off and do some work!
Better to die with a fighting chance, than be run down.
If anyone dares bring shame on us I shall kill them myself!
Look to your weapons! Keep steady, now!
Disembark, men! There's work to be done.
Now by Ahura Mazda we have cut the foreign scum down!
So, the enemy mean to sink us. Wind and waves, they are foolish!
Scrape my backside clean of barnacles! They mean to sink us!
That's it, sir! Nothing left to chuck at them!
Ah, you're as filthy as them!

Diana's glorious and virginal arse! Can't you lot fire when it's needed\?

I think I just shat myself!
Riggers! Make sure our banner is flying! Let them see it!
All warriors to their posts, as ordered!
I expect every man to do his duty!
Aside! You are not worthy of death at my hands!
Cut down any man who loots without permission!
Keep it up! They're cowards and will run!
Back! Live to fight another day!

O! Great Posiedon! Why did you not drown these wretches when you had the chance\? Very well, I will dedicate our coming victory to Poseidon, in the hope that He drowns the next fleet! Make ready!
This is getting a touch uncivilized!

What is the matter with those fools over there\? Why couldn't they be happy with enough food to eat, enough wine to drink and the occasional farm animal to molest\? I want them dead, men!

These rebels should have stayed at home! Maybe they were hungry, maybe they were cruelly treated, but so what\? The gods made them to obey, not to talk back! Today, then, we punish in the name of the gods!

These rebels are snarling, rabid dogs and village fools. The fools are about to pay with their lives for their stupidity in leaving the fields. The dogs deserve no mercy, and shall have none at our hands!
Of all the people of this world, I do hate the Gauls more than anyone! Look at them! Smell them! Disgusting, dirty, vile whoresons! I want them dead by nightfall! All of them!
One of my forefathers was killed by a Gaul. Stabbed in the back by a treacherous slave. Will you join me in avenging him\? Will you bring me the head of their leader on a spike\?

Stupid Gauls! Do you know they will eat anything\? I have even heard they eat horses! And frogs! They surely deserve to die for that! Kill the bastards! Think of all the noble horses you will be saving!
The Gauls believe they are better than us! How can such a foul smelling, ugly bunch of bastard sons of whores compare with us! Even their mead tastes of piss! Kill them all!
I would journey to the ends of the world for Makedon!

Bloody Gauls! Look at them! Dirty buggers! They may have druids but I have heard they still sleep with any animal or relative they can find! They are an infestation in these lands that must be wiped out!

As a ram on the prow of a ship we will strike them where they are weakest! Their numbers will count for nothing, when we smash open their lines, and pour like the sea into the shattered hull! Victory can be ours!

Where are we\? I don't know this place. Are we at home, my fellow Britons\? Or are we amongst the disgusting foreigners! No, I see an eagle and a lion playing in the valley… or is that a unicorn\? Someone bring me a drink for Arwen's sake!

Morrigan, we give their soul to you.

We are up against Rome, men! In all her glory, pomp and pretty costumes! They have trained for weeks to fight us. Their masters pay them money to do it! And yet it is our privilege to kill them for free!
Men! I want them dead! Do you hear\?
Fight! FIGHT! Are you stupid, boy\?
This is what we fight for, my brave warriors. We can tell our children we met the might of Rome and we crushed it in our hands. Yes! The gods have blessed us with this battle!

These Romans are disciplined, ruthless and professional. We are rowdy, disorganised and drunk! I know which side I would rather be on! They will not stand a chance as they will not know what I am going to do next!
Watch these Romans, closely. They are a crafty bunch of whoresons! They shall no doubt use all forms of attack. Perhaps some we have never seen before. But we shall be ready for them!
Thanks be to the ancestors. The general's here to fight with us.
This will be tough. The Romans are well trained and professional. They fight with great expertise and entire legions can move as one. I respect them. And yet I relish the chance to be among them!
By the gods, I have always wanted to kill Romans. Ever since I was a small boy and my father told me tales of their deeds. This is a worthy enemy, lads! Today we will be bathed in glory!

Ah, the Romans! How absolutely fitting that we should meet at this time These imperialist arses think they are the best in the world. Well, the druids tell me that, today, we are. So may the gods decide. To battle!
Keep after them! I want them all dead!

I spit on your honour, you bastards!
I'll not have cowards on this ship… Swim if you want to flee!

Pray we don't follow them any time soon.
A thousand years will not be  enough to wash away the shame!

Think on the honour, think of the glory, and of the reward, when we triumph this day! Find your courage and you will wish this rabble numbered more, for all the greater would be your victory!
We are outnumbered, but we are not outmatched in spirit! Gods, grant us courage! If we hold our ground, push them back, I swear to you we can turn this enemy tide and win this day!
Pay no heed to their numbers! We will be as a spearhead thrust with vigour into the flank of an hunted beast. In its pain, in its confusion, the beast will flee, and we will hunt it down!
Bugger honour, this isn't a fair fight! Push them off the wall!
Should we have cowered like dogs in our camp\? Should we have turned tail and run\? No! We will show these curs the meaning of courage. We have taken battle to them, and we will not die easily!

I cannot believe it has come to this. It is indeed a dark day, fellow Britons, when we find an enemy at our gates. Well, take up your weapons, one and all, and defend your home! For the ancestors!
I will not fail Rome again.
Rome deserves better, I am sorry.
Look at all those arses running for cover!
Rome deserves better, I am sorry.

I will not fail Rome again.

I will skin any man who leaves his post!

By sea or by mountain, sire\?
By sea or by mountain, sire\?

I do not like the taste of defeat. Never have.

I will give them to the darkness.

These day's she sells your dad's bum!
Men, there's loot to be had! But wait 'til they're dead!
Steady, lads. No need to worry them idiots over yonder!
Roman men are armoured by virtue!
Those Romans yonder a superstitious lot, men! They will tremble in fear at omens and portents and the like! They should tremble at the sight of us! We are an omen of their defeat! Now, to arms!

Romans are men of iron will, or so they would have you believe! They are also men with iron arses if their cooking is anything to go by! Best of all: they die when an iron sword is shoved through them! To arms!
Roman men are armoured by virtue!
So we have our next opponent by the look of it!

These Romans are humourless, dour people. They stand there, like so many fish-faced, miserable, little children, waiting patiently for permission to relieve themselves. Well, soon we will relieve them of their lives! Stand to!
Harder! Put your backs in to it!
Harder! Put your backs in to it!
Harder! Put your backs in to it!
Harder! Put your backs in to it!
Harder! Put your backs in to it!
You! Punishment detail after the battle! Why\? WHY\? For running out of ammunition!
Harder! Put your backs in to it!
Harder! Put your backs in to it!
Harder! Put your backs in to it!
Harder! Put your backs in to it!
Harder! Put your backs in to it!
Sir, um, it's not just him…
Is it me, or are there more of those bastards\?
Shut up! It's supposed to hurt!
One I do not wish to share.
Vulcan's brazen arse! That bloody hurts!
Sir, sir, sir. Why are they after us, sir\?
I'll take a head home for my children.
I'll take a head home for my children.
I'll see the light leave their eyes.
I will see the life leave their eyes…
I'll see the light leave their eyes.
I will see the life leave their eyes…
They must not take the wall! Drive them back, men!
May the gods bless our great general!
What good has ever come out of those folk\? These so called men we face are vermin to us. They think they are so superior to everyone else. Brew up a storm for them today, my brothers!
I am the fall of night.
I am the fall of night.
We go into battle now with as rough and tough an army as we are. They know how to fight these ones. Be prepared for all our bravery and strength to be thrown right back at us. Onward!
I will see it done, by any means.
I will see it done, by any means.
I will feed the earth with blood.
I will feed the earth with blood.
Woah! This bunch of peasants must be farmers. Or slaves! They stink to high heaven! They must be covered in cow shit. Let's clean them up then, boys! Get stuck in and dispose of them quickly!
Your equipment is a disgrace, man!
Your equipment is a disgrace, man!
Sometimes, the Mother has no mercy.
Assault the wall! Assault the wall!
Spirit of the Oak, guide my blade!
We Briton's thrive on the blood of our enemies.
We Briton's thrive on the blood of our enemies.
Your greaves are a disgrace, man!
Your greaves are a disgrace, man!
Break ranks, and I'll break your legs. We keep going!
