Spirit of the Oak, guide my blade!
Sometimes, the Mother has no mercy.
Let that inspire you, men! We shall prevail today!
There is no turning back! The gods have brought us safely across the sea for one glorious purpose, to win! To claim victory in their names! And I would not deny them! Come! Let us take this land!

We go ashore and, with earth beneath our feet, take battle to these dogs! We will give no ground, but drive the curs before us! Drive them inland, and put them to flight, with their tails between their legs!
Don't matter. Long as he wins for us!
We must take the shore. It will not be easy, even against these curs, but as the gods watch, I swear to you it can be done! If you have the will, it shall be done!
Is that the general\? He looks nothing like his statue!
Wind and sea have borne us to this place and, if we are to be remembered, we must take it! Falter and the sea will wash us away like footsteps in sand, but fight-- and we will never be forgotten!
Use this defence well, my friends!
What do we do now\? That was the last.
Come on! Drive them back from the walls!
We Briton's thrive on the blood of our enemies.
Spirit of the Oak, guide my blade!
Sometimes, the Mother has no mercy.
Who gave you permission to move\?
Well, he can't be very proud at the moment.
Take heart, men! Our general is with us!
Stand! Any man who wants death can have it now, from my blade!
No shame will come to any man who dies with me!
I sincerely hope that harpies gnaw on your nuts!
Steady, lads. No need to worry them idiots over yonder!
Don't let them get away! Chop their bloody legs off!
Looks, though, aren't enough to kill…
Men! Would you attack, please, NOW!
I have an inkling that our foes are a bit cross about something.
They look fierce enough for me!
Men! Would you attack, please, NOW!
You know, lad, I don't like the look of them!
Men, when you know that Romans like rotting fish to flavour their food, is it any wonder that we are at war with them\? Is it any wonder that we ought to kill them\? Well, it's time! To arms!
Shitting themselves just like you, lad…
Other than spoiling my breakfast, what are those Romans for\? They can barely think, their language is horrible, and their behaviour worse! Everyone will thank us when they are dead! So, to arms!

I look forward to this battle being over! By all the gods, we do not deserve Romans today! We do not deserve foes who smell of rotting fish-heads and garlic! Give me honest barbarians, any day of the week!

May all the gods preserve us from Romans and their appalling ways! In equal parts, arrogant, boorish, prudish and dull, they give me indigestion just looking at them! To arms, and let's be done with them!
I dislike fights against Romans. They have a nasty sense of duty that means they are stubborn and unwilling to co-operate in their own deaths! Well, what can't be cured, must be endured! Make ready!

I do not care for Romans, alive or dead. But they are always better dead, I find. That way you don't have to listen to another boring speech about Roman loveliness. Actually, one or two of their women are quite… Anyway, to arms!

By all our forefathers, is there anything more likely to spoil today than a Roman army\? Look at them! Dullards to a man with no sense of fun! All will be greatly improved by death! Ah, well, to arms!
By sea or by mountain, sire\?
By sea or by mountain, sire\?
Neptune's fish! Do not vomit over the side! In fact, do not vomit at all!
By sea or by mountain, sire\?
Why have you stopped shooting\? Did I say you could\? Did I\?
By sea or by mountain, sire\?
The gods of the sea will take what they want!
These seas are the homes of evil spirits! I have seen them!
Men, these rebels must be punished for their impudence! As Catubodua flies over us today I command you to extinguish this threat and send them to their deaths! Their shameful deaths! Tan their hides!
Is there nothing we can do\?

Do we really look like that\? Bugger me, that's depressing! Maybe we are barbarians after all. No. We can't look that stupid. These are nothing but heathen savages! Pray the gods side with us today. To arms!

Barbarians! That's what the Romans call us! They should meet this lot and see the real lowlifes of the world. Flea ridden, dirty, inbred, horse-lovers who drink goat's blood and brew mead that tastes of shit! Kill them!
We have the advantage! They have to come to us!
Hang on they look a bit like us! That hairy one at the front looks like my sister. This should be a lot of fun. I hope they are as hard as us. Come, men! To your positions!
Praise our general, men! Here he comes!
Expect this army to fight tough men! They will cut your heads off in one blow if they get past your defences and they can outlast many a warrior on the battlefield! Work hard out there!
Are we sure we are not related to them\? They're about as hairy as our lot\? But they stand in our way and so they give us no choice. We must wipe them out!
Aha! Today we fight some right angry, ugly, hairy bastards! Just like us! I look forward to sharing some sophisticated banter afterwards with their leader. When I greet him as my prisoner!
Sometimes, the Mother has no mercy.
I do this kindness for Pontus…
They're nothing without this wall, men!
Spirit of the Oak, guide my blade!
Watch for their fire! But keep your heads down!
We Briton's thrive on the blood of our enemies.
Leave the wounded for Anubis. Run!
We Briton's thrive on the blood of our enemies.

This lot are giving us a bad name. They don't drink enough. Never brawl and their singing and dancing is appaling! Let's get to it and clear their grubby arses off this field! Not a warrior amongst them, just peasants!
Anyone that breaks ranks will be staked out in the sun. I will have order!
Their beards are nearly as long as ours! Praise the gods our weapons are bigger though! And our swords! Ha, ha! Come, men, there is much work to do today to massacre this lot!
For our homeland! For our families!
Sleep when you're dead. Life's for living!
Spirit of the Oak, guide my blade!
Sometimes, the Mother has no mercy.
I love seeing sights like that. Cheers me up no end.
Egypt! The land of pharaohs and great pyramids! Today their god Isis had better be prepared for the wrath of our gods. The people of the desert are about to meet their match!
I am satisfied now. I have long heard of these Egyptians and their finery. Now I know all storytellers are liars. They're nothing but a bunch of girls! Let us finish them!
Is that the best they can throw at us\?
This lot are used to fighting in deserts. Let's show them our warrior spirit and some real hard fighting from the mountains and forests! Carve them like wood and cut them like grain!
Our lives. Our honour… And the loot.
This should be an easy day at war, my friends. These camel lovers come with nothing much to offer. Let us send them back to be buried in their little pointy pyramids.
If the general gets all the glory, what do we get\?
These infidels worship a great donkey called Anubis! Or is he a dog\? Or a cat\? Whatever, he's their deity of death! I'm sure they're all dying to meet him today! Ha, ha!
These stinking, desert animals have come to test us. I can smell the camel loving bastards from here! If you don't want to lose your breakfast I would get this done quickly!
We’ll just have to close with them, and fight.
You better not let these fools kill you. If they do they will steal your corpse and wrap it in cloth and put it in a wooden box and only the gods know what after that! Stay alive!
Draw your swords, men! Draw them now!
We Briton's thrive on the blood of our enemies.
Spirit of the Oak, guide my blade!
Sometimes, the Mother has no mercy.
I do this kindness for Pontus…
I want them dead! DEAD! Do you hear me\?
I think so. Served under so many can't tell anymore.
What did you expect\? Hercules reborn\?
By the gods! Is that him\? The general!
All I do, I do for the tribe.
Your will is done, my lord.
My success is for the tribe.
The Goddess honours me with success!
My success is for the tribe.
I have done all you asked and more!
All I do, I do for the tribe.
Your will is done, my lord.
I give this success to my ancestors.
My success is for the tribe.
I have done all you asked and more!
I am proud to serve Pharaoh.
Soldiers! Close watch on those bastards!
The enemy\? Pah! What are they\?
All I do, I do for the tribe.
Your will is done, my lord.
Storms and tempests! What a bunch of dockyard whores!
Come here and say that, you dog!
You'd think with all that wind, that they'd sail faster.
I give this success to my ancestors.
I have successfully completed my mission.
The Gods honour me with success!
I am proud to serve Pharaoh.
The Gods honour me with success!
I give this success to my ancestors.
All I do, I do for the tribe.
Your will is done, my lord.
I give this success to my ancestors.
I have successfully completed my mission.
The Goddess honours me with success!
My success is for the tribe.
Probably not had a woman for months.
Save a woman or two for me, lads!
If they have women in this craphole…
Yes, sir! I can't quite believe it, sir!
What you waiting for lad\? Get off!
Listen to it… They bleat like inbred goats.
Noisy things, barbarians. Not at all… washed.
Those men are the spirits of the dead! Of death!
You! Artillery master! Cheap harlots in Ostia could do better!
The Druids have assured me there will be battle and victory…
A safe predication… But victory for which side\?
And finally there they are! Get ready men!
That there, boy, is what you call your fate. Good luck.
Waiting is better than rushing off, sir!
Two of the three is not bad though.
Good weather, good ships and good crews… It is all I ask.
It is simple: we will sink them. Or they will sink us.
Ignore them! Worry about ourselves, and look to the ship!
It's not just you, you soft sod!
By the gods and waves! Have we come to this\? Defeat\?
Sword of Mars! They're trying to kill me!
I seek a foe worthy of my skill!
Has anybody seen my banner bearer\?
I seek a foe worthy of my skill!
You'll be looking for a very old leper, then…
You'll be looking for a very old leper, then…
It's not the fall that kills you… It's the bastard that pushed you!
Sometimes, the Mother has no mercy.
AAAhhh! That's my other eye! You bastards!
You look like a target, mate.
They know once we're over that's it!
Spirit of the Oak, guide my blade!
Sir, they seem to be aiming at you!
What are you all doing skulking back there\? Get back in ranks.
We Briton's thrive on the blood of our enemies.
We Briton's thrive on the blood of our enemies.
Do we have any wine\? Give it to the men, lift their spirits.
No sleep til we've finished. Come on!
Spirit of the Oak, guide my blade!
Sometimes, the Mother has no mercy.
That will really piss them off.
That should slow them down for awhile.
Here, behind these walls, we defend the last home of our people! If we should fail, not even the gods will remember us! But we will not fail! I will not permit it! You will not permit it!
It's worth following a great general… To the victors go the spoils!
Let them come to us. Then cut them limb from limb.
That's us done... We should retire and watch from the baggage.

By all the gods! Here is a challenge worthy of a general and his good soldiers! The enemy surround us! We have nowhere to retreat! We defend the last of our nation! Very well! We must win! Let's to it!

Everything we hold precious is at risk. Everything! Family, honour, land, freedom from foreign tyranny. That is why we will fight to our uttermost in the hours to come. Now, pray to the gods, and stand to!
After the walls… That’s when the looting starts!
Dis Pater! We will have to fight!
We Briton's thrive on the blood of our enemies.
Do not allow them to enjoy their brief visit to our shores, men! Drive them back into the water and let the creatures of the deep have them! Now, stand ready to defend yourselves!
Spirit of the Oak, guide my blade!
Sometimes, the Mother has no mercy.

They are disgusting little beasts, those Britons yonder. They do little but drink, drink some more and fornicate with sheep when they get the chance. Today we do the world a favour by killing them! To arms!

Over there, under the bloody-handed command of their druids - oh, they may claim otherwise, but they are ruled by murderers and dark priests - are Britons! Foul, ignorant, drunkard, ginger-haired Britons! Kill them!
The Britons think little of death! Their horrid druidic rites encourage them not to worry about this life or the next. Well, if they welcome death we shall give it to them in abundance! Make ready!
Honour the gods and your ancestors!
Honour the gods and your ancestors!
Honour the gods and your ancestors!
Honour the gods and your ancestors!
Make ready, men! The Britons yonder look ready to be cut down! Let us make this a bloody harvest and send them screaming back to their hovels, never to trouble honest folk again!
Gaul is mother to us all!
Gaul is mother to us all!
Gaul is mother to us all!
Gaul is mother to us all!
Make your shots count! They bloody well will!

My forefathers shed blood many times over for our people, but never against such a foul enemy! These Britons wallow in filth and practice bloody rites that would shock even a Carthaginian! They deserve death!
I live to serve the people of Gaul!
I live to serve the people of Gaul!
I live to serve the people of Gaul!
I live to serve the people of Gaul!

Look! A mob of blue-arsed Britons are standing about ready for death! They have no respect for honour, preferring to run away rather than fight like courageous men! I despise them, and want them dead!
Those northern dogs and pigs yonder call themselves an army. I suppose among the Britons such creatures do pass muster as warriors! I relish the whipping and roasting that is to be their lot today!
I live to serve the mighty Carthage!
I live to serve the mighty Carthage!

Today we fight Britons! Keep your wits about you, for although they look like dull cattle in thrall to their druids, they are cunning, spiteful and light-fingered to boot! Keep one hand on your sword, the other on your purse!
Quiet! Next man to speak, I will kill him!
I will have no running off at the enemy without permission!
Look! It's the general! He's here to join us!
He's here for the glory… Or a quick retreat.
That's him, isn't it\? Our general\?
They sing a pretty tune, for a bunch of bottom-munching worms!
I was enjoying that before they ran off.
Hear that, lads\? The dogs bark.
Now that is just wrong! I have never touched my sister!
Those men are the spirits of the dead! Of death!
Chance would be fine thing! I've seen her.
Thank the gods we made it! Land at last!
They bark like dogs. Pay it no thought.
True, but do you think they bite\?
This is all getting a bit noisy!
The enemy\? Pah! What are they\?
Favoured by Mars and Neptune both, our admiral…
That is what the gods have in store for us today.
…and by women in most ports, or so I've heard.
I will not eat fish again.
May the sea swallow their ships!
The fish will grow plump on man-flesh today.
All is lost! And my family's honour…

By Andarta, I wonder why the Greeks do not rule the world. Oh, maybe it's because they are a bunch of wets! They drink wine instead of mead! They eat olives instead of meat! And they love anything instead of women!
Move, you stupid sons of unwashed whores, move!
By Jupiter, man! Pick up that sword at once!
Curse them! That was my grandfather's blade!
He's mine! He's mine! I claim the honour!
I am tired, man. Let me die…
I wanted to see home one more time…
He's mine! He's mine! I claim the honour!
Look out, sir! He means to kill you!
That admiral… He think's he's Poseidon's chosen, the tosser.
I can hear their screams. Poor bastards.
Any more of that and I'll have you overboard!
Stop them taking the wall, men! Throw them back!
Forget your moaning, here's the general.
Watch where you're swinging that thing!
Put your backs into it! Then tear 'em apart.
Still got one eye to watch you miserable bastards.
I'm trying to stop them from hitting me!
Can we not rest\? I can't go on…
Success, lads! Now let's use the advantage.
Prepare, men, prepare! The enemy come ashore and mean to do us harm! Make sure that they regret the day they voyaged from their homes, let alone the day they insolently set foot here!

Do not flounder in the shallows like fish to be gutted. We have the numbers, and we have the will! We take the fight to them! Drive them from these shores! Behind us is the oblivion in the depths! We must go on!
In the name of our ancestors, let us throw these impudent invaders back into the sea! Let the waves claim their lives, and the fishes of the deep eat their bodies! All this I swear we will do!
Our back is to the sea, our enemy before us. Pity them. Their hearts tremble whether to fight or flee. Not us! We are not plagued by such doubts! Victory or a watery grave\? Our choice is simple.
I see our enemies have scraped their bottoms for barnacles, and turned the creatures into an army! They don't even make good eating, so let us return them to the waves! Stand ready!
I had hoped the gods of the sea, theirs and ours, would drown our foes, if only to spare mortals from the stench. Never mind, it seems we must cleanse the world ourselves! Let's to it!
Great gods of the seas! Look at our foes! So many fish-faced fools, thrown up on a beach by the storms of war! Well, like so many fish, they are destined for the pot! To arms, men, to arms!
It's the general… Let's aim to win his gratitude this day.
Gods of the seas! Hear my prayers! I offer you these vile invaders to feed your servants of the deep! If we win, I will sacrfice a hundred bulls in your honour! Men, make ready!
Do you know, men, I think I've seen scarier seaweed than our foes! I can't abide the slimy stuff, and I feel much the same about the enemy! Let us throw them back into the deeps!
We may be outmatched here, but we have the favour of Ares, something our foes utterly lack! They are the sweepings of the farmyard, dust and chaff to a man! Therefore, be confident and make ready!
Get the men ready to fight.
By Taranis, I can't take this anymore! I hate war anyway! It was my father who made become a warrior. I wanted to be a bard. I can sing much better than I can lead an army!
Damn them! I've used my last shot!

By Andarta, I want them all dead! Do you hear\? Dead! Ripped and cut open, castrated, disemboweled, gutted and their entrails put in a tub so I can bathe my poor aching head and body in their blood! KILL THEM ALL!
Thank the gods, thank them for our safe passage! And do so with the blood of our foes! For they wish to see a spectacle, to see us fulfil our promise, and win a great victory in their names!
All that stands between us and plunder is this wall.
There is no turning back now. For the gods of the sea are cruel, and they will not grant us passage again without payment. That payment is blood, ours or theirs! Draw your swords, and make ready!
What flotsam have the waves cast up on our shores\? Warriors, of a kind, I suppose, if a little green from their recent voyages. Green or not, I wonder if their insides are red\?

Unfortunately, I see our foes have made landfall, men! I had hoped that more of them would die in their voyaging, but perhaps the gods do not want to poison all the world's fish! So then, we will fight!
Keep your aim low! Hit them in their fat bellies!
Hold fire, you men, until you have good targets!
By my ancestors of blessed memory, I do not like Britons! And I do not like that army over there! Shall we sell the the survivors into slavery\? And share the profit\? Yes\? To arms, then!
What do we know of Pontus\? Not a lot. They are weak and very ill looking. Ugly and I fear there will be some unusual smells out there when they start shitting with fear. To arms!
This general thinks he is cleverer than me! He thinks the slave army he brings from Pontus is better than my brave warriors! Yes! Do you hear that men\? He thinks he will win today! Not a chance!
Look, lads! The general is with us!
What do the army of Pontus know of war\? What do they know of pain\? Have they ever met the likes of us before\? We shall fight them hand to hand and tear from them our victory!

Pontus\? Pontus\? Who here has ever bloody heard of Pontus\? Who are they, eh\? Give me Romans, Egyptians, Carthaginians or even bloody Parthians! I've heard of them. But Pontus! I ask you… Just go and kill them! To Battle!

These enemies are scum! Make no mistake they are dangerous! Do not be fooled by their hairstyles and women's clothes. I have heard they do kill. Mainly their own children! This is going to be very easy.
I have heard this lot don't drink! Can you believe that! They hate mead or even worse their gods do not allow it! I am sorry for them and their people. At least their lives will end today!

Pontus, is it\? I have heard they eat those they fight. They are a proud, cruel people who even devour their own children in sacrifice! Who knows how their bowels will stink when we slit them open. Make ready!
I suppose this is what Roman idiots call unsporting"."
No one asked if you liked 'em. Just kill 'em!
We fight together! We fight as one!
Then put some bloody effort in!
I would travel many miles for Carthage.
Setting forth in the name of Carthage.
Setting forth in the name of Carthage.
I would travel many miles for Carthage.
Sir! Damage parties at work, sir!
No slacking, just because it's a battle! Keep-ARRGGHHHH!
The enemy\? Not worth a fart, the lot of them!
Where the general\? Still buggering about in his tent\?
The ancestors are watching, my brothers! Show them mortal courage!
Watch it! Bit of respect for the general now!
Show them a mortal arse, more like…
Vulcan's hammer! It's a mercy that thing's destroyed!
I do not want to be ashamed when I join my ancestors!
Any man who flinches will feel my sword!
By Sucellos! We have prevailed, warriors!
You big Roman nancy! Stop that screaming!
A little blood, man, is good for the complexion!
You've had your fun! Let them drown peaceful like!
Ancestors, watch over me while I rest.
Ancestors, watch over me while I rest.

Gods! I pray you give us a worthy foe to fight and not these savage dogs! What honour is there in defeating such filth\? Let us make this swift, men. Their manner offends me, and I would be rid of their stench!
I must stop and chant awhile.
I must stop and chant awhile.

Half our number could dispatch this barbarous filth! Each of you is worth ten of them! We shall swiftly put and end to this rabble. Before the day is out they will kneel in chains, or be carrion food for the birds!

Old men and inexperienced boys, more used to idle chit-chat: that is the Greeks! Do not trouble yourself with fear, for they will either talk us to death, or run away! That is their custom! Greek strength died decades ago!
Let us put these filthy barbarians to the sword! Do not let their insults and shouts unman you! We shall answer their challenge with blood, and put this rabble of fools to flight!

Greeks! Their arrogance is an insult! They think themselves better than us, better than all the world! We will pay back their presumption with blood! Today we teach these Greek philosophers a lesson in humility!

We face a pack of barbarian dogs, men. Their manner, their aspect, may look daunting, but their courage is mead-inspired. They will sober quickly and their blood-lust will dribble away! Draw your swords, and make ready!
What arrogance these barbarous dogs possess! Let us put an end to their insults and them swiftly to flight, for my senses our assailed by just the look and smell of them! Draw swords, and make ready!
I shall rest awhile in this grove.
I shall rest awhile in this grove.

You can smell their fear: that, or they need a good wash! Do not let yourself be unmanned by their shouting, men. They merely try to find their courage and set their fears upon you. We shall answer with swords and blood! Make ready!
I must stop and chant awhile.
I must stop and chant awhile.

Do not be mistaken, men, we have the advantage here! These pretenders and their unwashed levies play at battle, like simple children. We do not! Let us teach these insolent beasts a lesson or put them to the sword! Make ready!
I must let my mind be still.
I must let my mind be still.
I must let my mind be still.
I must let my mind be still.

Do not be afraid of these perfumed pretenders and their unwashed chattel, men. I promise you we are more than a match for their strength. We shall put their masters in chains and liberate the oppressed! Make ready!
Proud peacocks and unwashed slaves, that is the sum of the army arrayed before us! Not a single one would I call a soldier. Each of you is worth ten of them, and they shall know it this day! To arms!

Let us put these proud peacocks and their lackeys to the test! I can promise you they shall be found wanting! We shall show them no mercy! Put any that resist to the sword! Bring me their leaders in chains, or bring me their heads!

Do not fear, men. Our enemy argues and throws insults far better than they throw javelins! They are debaters, not soldiers; olive growers, not generals!  We will show them how to fight today. They will not like the lesson!

Are you afraid of Greeks\? When they are not arguing about the universe, they are chasing goats for all the wrong reasons! They can talk passably well, but they fight lamentably! Excellent! They will pay for that failing today!
Good… For me. But you\? About even I'd say.
No, boy! We're the hard cases here!
Come and fight, you cowardly, cowardly... foreigners!

Romans! They lack even the fun and wit found among Spartans! These stubborn wolves will be hard to beat, but we will drive them whimpering back to Rome! We will break their stubborn arrogance! Make ready, men!
Roman dogs! Whelped and suckled by a she-wolf, they call brutality nobility", and seek mastery over all others! We shall not become their subjects, their house slaves! We shall fight!"
Bugger me! I've just about had enough of all this!
Gods, grant us the strength to beat these Romans! Let us meet their misplaced pride  with honest courage! Gods, let us claim victory in your names, and for our noble people! To arms!

Dour and stubborn are the people of Rome: a rabble of farmers elevated too far above their lowly origins. We will not be defeated by them! Let them throw their legions against us! We shall turn them back! Make ready!
That's not a choice! Maybe it is a choice… I don't know!
Roasting or drowning\? What will it be\?
Praise the Camalus! That should help us today!
He who stands and fights will be remembered!
Captain, sir! You're bleeding sir! The men don't like it, sir!
Sir, you're doing no good bleeding all over! Get down below!
Over the side with their corpses!
My finest wine for the first kill!
This is my day of glory!
There's enough killing today for everyone!
Would you like a last morsel\?
They're just a load of stinking, pig-fondling peasants!
Peasants\? I don't think the enemy are quite that noble!
Honour is all I have left!
Do not rest until the waves are red with enemy blood!
May Tyr rain down his thunderbolts!
This is getting sodding dangerous, by Ares!
Men! Prepare to fight for your lives and your honour!
Carpenter! Look to your work! Make us watertight!
Duty is not always enough to keep us afloat!
Tides will carry a body a long way, sir.
This is the last stand, men! Our capital is at stake today. By dawn will we still own these streets. Our homes\? Or will we all be in Freya's loving arms\? Fight like boars and defend your city!
It's the captain you want to ask, not Mithra.
There's a sight to lift the heart! Enemy cowardice!
May Mithra grant us some rest soon.
Aye, very welcome to see their fleeing arses!
Aye! Save some wine for me!

Unwashed bandits and hillsmen, and their perfumed masters, that is who we face this day. What arrogance! Do they not know who we are\? We shall put the rabble to flight and put their masters in chains!

Strutting peacocks and unwashed swine, that is who we face! They would barely be a match for half our number! This is a banquet for carrion, not a battle! Draw your swords, men, and feed these fools to the birds!
Eyes front! No flinching! Show them how men behave!

What over-confident fools! Their insolence is offensive! They insult me, and they insult you! We shall answer their challenge with sword and spear, and bow! Answer with blood! And we shall break these jackals! Make ready!

We have the advantage here, men. These dogs and their pretty little masters will not hold against us! They are but a pale reflection of our great strength and we will soon put them to flight! Make ready!
Would you dishonour our people, ancestors gods by running from these jackals\? No! No, we will not bring dishonour on our name! We shall put these dogs to the sword, and claim victory for our people!
Would you be unmanned by the peacocks strutting before you\? Would you dishonour our people with defeat to these pretty birds\? No! No, we shall put these women to flight! Make ready, men!
I live to serve the people of Gaul!
I live to serve the people of Gaul!
Gaul is mother to us all!
Gaul is mother to us all!
Honour the gods and your ancestors!
Honour the gods and your ancestors!
This day will be long remembered.

Behind these walls cower the enemies of Pharaoh, blessed be His every act! We have been commanded to take this place and put any that resist to the sword! Victory will not be easy, but we are prepared. Make ready!
We fight for our families, my brothers! We fight with honour!
Put those flames out! Drench them!
I don't want to burn! Not that!
Well jump in the sea, then, you flaming fool!
The deeps… here… the spirits are troubled.
Dirty buggers! They've sent their lovers to have a go.
Neptune give me patience! More of them!
Let not your family's name be shamed!
Where do you think you're going\?
By Taranis, we will fight on!
With Mithra's power we shall hit them hard!
So, brave warriors, to our work!
This was my father's sword. I will not dishonour him.
This is a good place to die!
Show them how real men fight!
You lazy goat-sucking farmboys! Kill them!
I will kill any man with fear in his heart!
Honour! Honour\? We fight for our lives as well!
Get ready, you boarding crews! No accidents!
Let go of your bloody sword!
Now, show them how soldiers fight!
Battle will stiffen you up, lad, just to wait…
Eyes front! Worry about them, nothing else!
My sword has definitely gone limp.
I shall miss the spirits of the ocean.
I shall miss the spirits of the ocean.
I spit on your honour, you bastards!
The gulls are ready to feed, I see.
The fish here taste foul, you know.
I hope we choke them, sir!
I have just had a thought: I think they are trying to kill us.
Cut them up and we can fry for dinner tonight!
Let me see the fire in your eyes! No fear today!
Over the side! He's fish bait now!
No need for aid, man, I am slain!
Straighten those lines, if you please! No untidiness!
Those banners are quite pretty. Nice needlework.
You know, I think I've seen more threatening whores!
Sounds right. You have poor taste in whores.
Which one of you peasants did that\?
I will cut down any man who flinches!
Have at them! Now! Heave the dead over the side!
Men, I will be brief: we face Germans here, and they are a foul, ignorant, barbarous people. The only thing civilized thing they understand is a Roman gladius, to the heart! Give it to them!
Only if you want it, sir.
Aye. Enemies tend to do that!
Men: swords drawn, and make ready!
The unwashed bastards! They're fighting back!

Barbarians! I find their manner and their odour offensive. Let us teach these backward savages what it truly means to be a warrior, to be a soldier. We shall put them to the sword or put them to flight! Make ready!

Barbarians! I spit on them! Why should we fear these unwashed savages\? They are not true soldiers, they are thugs playing at war. We shall end this game of theirs, and put their leaders in chains! Make ready!

Barbarians! What a foul stench! These unwashed sons of whores are more likely to overwhelm us with their odour than their numbers! If you have the stomach for it, men, make ready. Let us put these foul dogs to flight!

Do not let yourselves be unmanned by the insults of these dogs! We shall test ourselves against these filthy barbarians to the test, and we shall not be found wanting! Cut down their leaders and the rest will flee! Draw your weapons, and make ready!
Sailors! Made myself a tidy profit!
Sailors! Made myself a tidy profit!
Aye, like pigs mating with goats!
Do NOT shout at the enemy. It only encourages them.
Bloody barbarian nonsense. Foul noise, too.
Rascals, rogues, thieves. And bastards to a man.
Come and have a go, you bastards!
A thousand years will not be  enough to wash away the shame!
The fish are evil. They will drag us to our doom.
A dog is like any other animal, boys. A good kick between the legs and they're out!
Come on! There are enemies who need killing!
The ancestors can wait a little longer, men. There's still fighting to do.
You there! Pick up that arm! I cannot abide untidiness!
That man! Rusty armour! No wine tonight!
We are fortunate, today, in our choice of friends.
This is not a good place to die.
You know, with a good woman, today could be fun!
And in our choice of enemies, sir!
Jupiter be thanked! One less thing to worry us!
Which one of you peasants did that\?
We should thank the gods, men, for the opportunity that lies before us! Glory as we go over the walls! Plunder aplenty beyond! And wine and a warm woman or two! So, are we ready\?
Those walls will not look tall when we are within them, and laying waste to their precious homes! Then we will laugh as we take what we want and who we want! Now, to arms!

Those walls are like the hearts of the defenders behind them: rotten, ill-made and weak. They are men of soft clay, like their walls! We are men of iron purpose and iron courage. This assault will not last long!
There is no wall in all the world that can keep us out, no man whose bravery matches ours, no swords sharper, no spears keener, no gods as unforgiving as ours! So, we will conquer here!
Shortly, we shall take this place from the enemy. When we do, take what you will for your good efforts here should be rewarded with loot, slaves and wine! Right, look to your arms!
Right now, behind those walls, fear is eating at our enemies' souls. Fear! Fear of you, and what you might do! Use that fear in this attack! Become fear! Become horror! Become conquerors!

Now are enemies stand on their walls, and think themselves safe. Now they look down upon you with contempt! So: show them how foolish they are, how misguided, and how the gods no longer love them! Prepare!
I have come to battle, like my forefathers, in the expectation of victory. We will go over those walls, and into their streets and homes. We will leave them nothing but tears! Make ready!
You! Stop playing with the ship's gear! You are here to fight! Nothing more!
Save an enemy for me! I will boil him with the crabs!
Sir! Sir! Sir! Sir! He's dead, sir!
No shame will come to any man who dies with me!
Grab any flotsam you can, men!
No! No! Not a watery grave!
Sir, sir! We're taking on water, sir!
Rejoin and reform at the double, Mars curse you!
Let us meet these stubborn Romans on our terms! Let us crush their dreams of conquest and expansion, and send them scurrying back to Rome. For Victory! Victory for the divine and magnificent Pharaoh!
I suppose you are right. Incovenient, though…
Up my arse, waiting to be shat out!
Sir, they are the enemy. They are supposed to be hostile. Sir.
Now is the hour! Draw your swords!
Where are the foes worthy to meet me\?
Steady, lads. No need to worry them idiots over yonder!
Looks, though, aren't enough to kill…
I have an inkling that our foes are a bit cross about something.
They look fierce enough for me!

These rebel scum do not know when they're beaten! What stupid insolence! When this day is done, they shall whimper in fresh chains or be carrion for the birds! Their wickedness will not go unpunished!
There is little honour in fighting rebels. Our victory is expected and the rewards are slight. So then, let us make this quick, and crush these rebels before their poison spreads! Make ready, men!

These rebels are fools! Simple, stupid farmers! They think they match our strength but will we endure such an insult\? We shall correct their folly with blood, and with screams for mercy! There will be none! Make ready!

These rebels are fools to believe they can stand against us! They have courage, I grant them that, but it is a fool's courage! They will not surrender, and so we will put them to the sword! Make ready!

What arrogance! We shall put these rebel scum in chains or we shall build mountains from their skulls! The work is beneath us but we cannot let this rebellion pass! Make ready, men! Today we end this uprising!
These rebels are like rabid dogs, they will not be subdued and cannot be allowed to rejoin the pack! They must be put down! Each and every one of them must pay for their insolence!
Move back! Keep them at bay!
Today will be bloody work, but those who show their courage, who show their mettle, will earn the King's gratitude, and earn their title as his shield. We have the advantage here! Make ready, men!
Catubodua, the great crow of battle, will soar above our heads today. Heed his battle cry and cut and cleave for his mighty appetite. We will vanquish this woeful opposition. Remember, heed my calls!

Remember Rudianos watches us today. He expects only victory and we shall grant it. For on this field of battle we shall make the enemy our sacrifice! Drain those bastards' blood! For the big breasts of Cicolluis!
Come now, men! Show me your spirit!
Where's you leader\? Let him show himself, the coward!
I'd rather die with a good woman.
Look, my dear, it's time to fight. That… later.
Fight, curse your gizzards, or you are shark meat!
This weather. It's not good for my knees.
Why does everyone we meet always want to kill us\?
Earn your pay! Kill those bastards!
Show them how real men fight!
If any of you men run, you will answer with your heads!
I do not want a grave here, of all places.
Praise Seth! We are safe. We made it!
No lad, we float here 'til it's done…
We are done, then. Lash me to the anchor stone!
By Mithra! Keep your heads down!
Stand! Any man who wants death can have it now, from my blade!
No shame will come to any man who dies with me!
So many shots! How many men do we face\?
Shitting themselves just like you, lad…
Steady, there. No need to worry about a few idiots over there.
You know, lad, I don't like the look of them!

Rebels! They are a plague upon good order and peace of the world! Like any diseased limb, they must be cut off! We shall make example of these foolish wretches! Leave none alive! Put them to the sword!

Rebels! There is little glory in this, but at least these wretches will not put up much fight! This is not battle, men, for we are the overseer's whip bringing correction and punishement! Today is a bloody lesson, nothing more!
Stand together, men! A horde of brutes surrounds us! They seek to scatter us proud Palmyrenes to the wind and put this place to the torch! May their blades chip and shatter - I will not have this!

Let us put down these rebels! Not content with their simple lives, they have chosen to rise up and challenge their betters! We shall cut off the hands that are risen against the natural order of the world! Make ready!
Let us make this quick, men. There is no honour, no glory, and no riches to be gained here. These brigands are no more than practice for our arms! Let us do this bloody work and be gone!
Move back... Slowly! Keep your eyes on them!
Hold them! As Ba'al watches us, hold them!
Gather around me, your queen! In your mighty hands you now hold my life and honour! Fulfil your duty - do not let the enemy sully them! Do this and victory will come!
Righteous sons of Gaul, say your prayers, make your offerings! For the gods have chosen we shall attack this enemy. Hit them hard and take no prisoners. Today we shall become heroes!

The great-breasted Cicollus has warmed up her cleavage for all those who die today and go to bed down tonight with the gods! May you rest in her peace! Ha, ha! For the rest of us, I promise a great feast shall be had!

We stand before an arrogant buch of sods. A cocky confection of foreigners who think we are wild and barbarous. Well,  let us show them how wild battle can be and how long death will hold them! Send them to Taranis!
Take aim, fire on the shore!
Take aim, fire on the shore!
Take aim, fire on the shore!
Take aim, fire on the shore!
Take aim, fire on the shore!
Take aim, fire on the shore!
Take aim, fire on the shore!
Take aim, fire on the shore!
Take aim, fire on the shore!
They don't look so little to me.
I like artillery, but only when it's pointed at them!
Setting forth in the name of Carthage.
Fight on, my brave men! Fight on!
I would travel many miles for Carthage.
I would travel many miles for Carthage.
Setting forth in the name of Carthage.
Setting forth in the name of Carthage.
I would travel many miles for Carthage.
I would travel many miles for Carthage.
Setting forth in the name of Carthage.
Deck hands! Clear that wreckage, quickly now!
Fight! You are sailors, but you are warriors also!
We fight on! It is only a flesh wound!
The enemy, it is clear, have appalling taste in armour!
This would be a good place to farm.
Wine! A good woman! Regular meals! That's all I wanted!
And that alone is reason to kill them\?
If you're stupid, and born on a farm.
And you get them, along with a chance for glory!
Mars be praised! That was work well done in breaking that machine!
I will cut down any man who runs!
Let us spear these fish as they flounder on our shores! In the name of Lord of All, great Pharaoh, we shall drive them back to their ships! We shall not let invaders pollute our shores!
That's right. They should thank us with ale!
Well, who ever ordered us to do that should be bloody pleased.
Carpenter! Plug any holes below the waterline! NOW!
Gods of the deep! This is ill-luck, to die in such a fashion!
I don't want to be all eaten up by fishes, sir! I don't!
Never you mind about the general! Worry about my opinion!
I say, this is a good day! There's the admiral! Hurrah!
Look! The admiral! I met him, once, you know…
I don't rest, but I will stop awhile.
I don't rest, but I will stop awhile.
I do not sleep, I wait..
I do not sleep, I wait..
We will profit by their death.
We will profit by their death.
This is all getting a bit noisy!
Reckon that's her, over there, trying to kill us!
By Sucellos!  I want to see blood and guts on this field today!
My fellow Britons, I have led you in many a campaign and fought alongside you in many a battle. Today we go once more into the glory of the fight. Look to me, heed my command and we shall conquer!
I stand before you ready as always to do battle and die if I have to to serve our people. By Belatu Cadros, I promise they shall not prevail until I lie dead on the field!
By the waters of the Rhine! That was a great victory, boys!

Warriors, this is our last defence, the last wall between us and utter defeat. If we do not gain victory this day, let us hope that our deaths shall inspire others to resist! May our enemy find no peace while our people yet live!

This is our last refuge, the last beacon of our gods! Should these wall fall, should we fail, that light will be extinguished! I charge you, by all that we hold sacred, to stand! To stand, and guard these walls, and turn back our foes!

This is our last holdout, the final refuge of our people! Should these walls fall, should we fail, all will be swept away, and our homes will be filled with blood and flame! This cannot come to pass! We must not allow it!

Once-proud Rome now trembles! Its Senate and people wail! They fear our coming, fear the slaughter we will unleash! But it is the price of their arrogance! We will shake Rome to its foundations, and slaughter any that resist!

Noble warriors, it has come to this, the defence of our last stronghold! Should we fall, then our people also fall. I do not need to tell you your duty: today we repel these curs or we die! It is that simple! Make ready!

We shall cast Rome down this day! The Senate shall be enjoy chains or the sword! Their temples and buildings will be razed. Never again will Rome threaten our people. Make ready! For today Carthage will be triumphant!
If this be our last battle, then let it be said our courage was unbounded, our ferocity unmatched, and our enemy unmanned! Soldiers! Let us make them pay a high price in blood for these walls!

Here and no farther, there is nowhere left for us! We hold! We drive them back! That, or we die! And our families, our people, shall be enslaved or slaughtered beside us! This cannot be! To arms, men! To arms!

Gods, hear our prayers, hear your people, we stand at the brink! Aid us, give us the strength to hold these walls, to hold out and defend your people! For if we fail, your temples, your homes, will be overrun!
Are they Britons\? They smell like Britons.
We shall cut out the Roman heart today. We shall sack Rome, slaughter its people, and raze its temples to the ground! The world will be ours! Praise Ba'al! Praise Tanit! Victory for Carthage!

What is Rome now\? We shall put this cesspit of thieves and vagabonds to the sword! We shall parade its Senate in chains before its broken people. We will cast Rome down, for the glory of our people and the gods!

We shall not go meekly, my soldiers! Our ancestors, our gods and our people are watching, and we know our duty! We shall fight to the last, fight until either victory is ours or death claims us all! Prepare yourselves!

We make our final stand here! We are the last of our people, men! If we fail today, if we falter and let these dogs overwhelm us, we are done! Our people will become but dust and memory. We cannot let this happen! To arms!
Out of the water! Move on now!
The enemy are nothing! Pray that the Old Man does not send us a true storm!
Artillery is the death of courage!
Bloody cowards have set their pets on us.
Die with me today, boys, and tonight we will drink with the gods!
Think of the songs they will sing of us!
You are wounded sir! You can do nothing while you bleed!
The enemy... They trouble my soul.
The ancestors are unquiet. We will die here.
So. Where do you think we'll be tomorrow\?
You know, I really wish I'd paid that last whore…
Are there any women here\? Or are you warriors\?
You! Fight! Or I'll feed you to the fish myself!
What a mess! Look at them! Blood and guts everywhere.
Ah! We are drowned, then. A pity.
Sir, lord, sir! We're taking on water, sir!
We are lucky, my boy, that we sail with such a good admiral…
I've seen the admiral! And we're winning!
The enemy must never have rest!
The enemy must never have rest!
A sword needs a whetstone, a mind needs scrolls!
A sword needs a whetstone, a mind needs scrolls!
Pharaoh forgive me, I must rest.
Pharaoh forgive me, I must rest.
I will teach them to fear us!
I will teach them to fear us!
So, they have some honour then!
Their fear and doubt are our weapons.
Their fear and doubt are our weapons.
Soldiers! Close watch on those bastards!
The enemy\? Pah! What are they\?
They will learn to fear us!
They will learn to fear us!
I must pause to practice, where is my oud\?
I must pause to practice, where is my oud\?
I shall take a moment to rest.
I shall take a moment to rest.
A rested mind is a sharp mind.
A rested mind is a sharp mind.
I must bath, the road is long and dusty.
I must bath, the road is long and dusty.
I shall take a moment to compose myself.
I shall take a moment to compose myself.
A rested mind is a tool of Isis.
A rested mind is a tool of Isis.
These Greeks are not made for war. They may debate the nature of courage and honour, but the practice of it escapes them! We will show them how soldiers, and true heroes fight! Make ready, men!

The men we face are more suited to debates and running games than battle! Why should we fear the likes of them\? Would you shame our people by fearing Greeks\? No, we will not be beaten by such as them!
May Isis and Nephthys not mourn us today.
Their blood will enrich our soil!
Their blood will enrich our soil!
Their blood will enrich our soil!
Their blood will enrich our soil!
Poets and teachers! Philosophers and deranged loons! We will teach these Greeks a lesson in the meaning of death! We will break their spears, their spirits and their hearts today! To arms!
For them, the war is over…
For them, the war is over…
For them, the war is over…
For them, the war is over…

Poets and philosophers, Greeks are not fit for war! Even the Spartans no longer merit the reputation of their ancestors! We will give these Greeks something to think on: let them think on their deaths, and their defeat at our hand!
Noisy things, barbarians. Not at all… washed.
Those men are the spirits of the dead! Of death!
We will profit by their death.
We will profit by their death.
We will profit by their death.
We will profit by their death.
Ba'al, give us strength… Hold them! Hold them back!

Within these walls cower the Senate and people of Rome! Their stubborn arrogance has been replaced with terror! And rightly so! We shall enter and put them to the sword! We shall burn their homes and loot their temples! Make ready!
Take aim, fire on the shore!
Take aim, fire on the shore!
The fish will grow plump on man-flesh today.
I will not eat fish again.
Ten dikhkloi to whoever takes out their captain!
Choose your ground carefully. You only die once.
Prepare! Make ready, and cheer, you miserable sods!
Don't hold with elephants! Nasty things!
To travel is to be truly free!
May Seker welcome them to the underworld.
To travel is to be truly free!
To travel is to be truly free!
To travel is to be truly free!
Pray to Anubis! You might be seeing him soon!
Stop waving that sword, you utter fool!
Strike low! Strike low! Into their bellies!
Men! I will drown you in your own blood if you weaken!
Give me a sword! Let me have my honour!
My brothers! We stand! We die! Or we triumph!
That's them done. Now who's next\?
Ares curse them! That was a good sword!
I don't care! You're mine now!
Soldiers! Keep out of the way!
Andraste, I beg you for victory! May the sea take them all!
Back to your duties! Let them drown without spectators!
That's our admiral, lad. He's a fine figure of a man.
He's a cunning bugger, our admiral. I like him.
They're running, by the gods! Excellent!
We go to Anubis. May he be merciful!
I do love the feeling of earth between my toes.
I do love the feeling of earth between my toes.
Thoth, bless me with your knowledge.
Better than charging about all day.
I shall see to the needs of the children of the Nile.
Hathor's horns, are we going to just sit here\?
I will do what is best for Pharaoh's servants.
I shall see to the grain stores.
May your next life be even more painful, you pig!
We fight for the glory of our ancestors!
I see Dionysus has been with you!
Have you taken leave of your senses\?
The fire will consume us! It's spreading too quickly!
Do you think me a fool\?
Do not doubt we have the advantage here, but pray that destruction visits our foe this day! With Ahura Mazda's blessing danger will pass over us! This battle shall be bloody, but we shall triumph!
Gods be good! I will not!
Are we done\? Can we go home now\?
Back off, men! Easy as you go!
Put fire in your heart and hate in your belly! For Egypt!
We will not give up! Death will take our foes!
Keep them fighting, decurions, if you please!
Hold fast now! They're only elephants!
You heard him! Nothing to worry about!
Wind and wave do not allow that.
It is a bad cut. You will live.
Kill! Kill! Kill! Kill! How many more times\?
This is bad. I seem to have lost my eye.
Brave shield brothers! Stand fast now!
May they burn for all eternity.
They've gone to meet their gods.
They couldn't hit the Acropolis at this dist- Aphrodite's glorious left tit!
Arse of Ares! He does look better without his head!
Tell my wife I loved her!
Stand by! This will be close!
Give me a sword! Let me have my honour!
By all the gods! Are we not fortunate to be lead by a fighting admiral\?
I've sailed under some dodgy buggers, but this admiral's loved by the gods, I tell you!
Sir, the enemy are not cooperating today!
You smell that\? Enemies always smell real bad!
Whatever happens, do not let the standard fall.
Those swines over there are, are... are complete swines!
Waiting for orders! Their ship's in range, sir!
What say we challenge them to an arm wrestle\?
I shall do what I must.
I shall do what I must.
They will soon forget their allegiance.
They will soon forget their allegiance.
A woman's words can be... persuasive…
A woman's words can be... persuasive…
I am unable to travel this road.
Stop shouting, and put out those flames! Get to it!
That's what she said last night.
Attack. Withdraw. Gods, will you make up your bloody minds!
Less of that, or I'll have your tongue!
Withdraw! In an orderly fashion, mind you!
Gods of the sea! The ship's on fire! We're on fire!
Help put it out then, you whelk-munching Vestal!
By Mithra, I can feel something in my waters…
Our enemies love black wickedness, it seems.
What shame is there in death\?
Don't you worry about them elephants. Stick by me!
Wind and wave do not allow that.
Dis Pater! May the gods dance with you today!
Die with fire in your hearts!
You there! THAT is a weapon, not a pitchfork!
Send them screaming to the afterlife!
Watch it! You nearly had my head!
By Camalus! We fight like true Britons now!
Now, fight like night-spawned monsters, you bastards!
Keep bailing, you fools, unless you want to meet the tritons!
They couldn't hit Mount Olympus at this dist-!
Well, this is better. Less screeching for a start…
I was supposed to die in bed, surrounded by grieving women...
Men! Have you left your bravery in a wineskin\?
I feel strangely happy, watching them drown…
Keep at it, lads! Let the admiral see you working!
Ah! This will be a sea of widows' tears when we are done!
Do you recall the story of Tiresias\?...
Our secrets are safe with me.
I must stop and commune with the gods.
I must stop and commune with the gods.
With the fury of the Gods!
With the fury of the Gods!
With the fury of the Gods!
With the fury of the Gods!
With the fury of the Gods!
I shall take a moment to rest.
I shall take a moment to rest.
A little wine and relaxation perhaps\?
A little wine and relaxation perhaps\?
If we're to die, let us tip the scales, and earn Anubis' favour.
Now's the time. Get it out of you, boy.
Prepare to send the unclean rats to the bottom of the sea!
Fight for your fathers! And your fathers' fathers! And your fathers' fathers' fathers!
That's a lot of old men. Bu I never knew my dad…
I will show them a better way.
Their men will doubt their authority.
Nature teaches beasts to know their friends.
No man can resist a reasoned argument.
I will make them doubt their leaders.
Give the order to withdraw. Don't let them harry us.
Slowly! Step back! Keep your guard up!
Retreat, lads. Our work is done here for now.
I will make my father proud.
I will make my father proud.
They will never see it coming.
They will never see it coming.
I will be a vengeful shade.
I will be a vengeful shade.
They won't miss a few men…
They won't miss a few men…
Take aim, fire on the shore!
Take aim, fire on the shore!
Take aim, fire on the shore!
Take aim, fire on the shore!
Take aim, fire on the shore!
I have chosen where I will die. You should do the same.
Elephants\? More trouble than they're worth, lad!
Do you think you are going to live for long against a giant sodding elephant if you run, you useless TWAT\?
Watch out! It's those big bastard elephants!
Elephants\? I'm not scared of- ELEPHANTS!
Elephants! We're in for it now!
Sword of Ares! What a bunch of nancy, girly, slave-loving, stupid…
They will sing songs of us tomorrow. For today we die!
At them! Not a moment's rest!
Mars! Listen! I'd like to live, and fight again tomorrow, please!
Now, be wolves! Goats are going to die today!
If I die, will you tell my wife\?
Landsmen! Get out of the way!
Leave me! I will go down with the ship.
I have brought you to these walls and I ask you to take this city for Tyr, for Tuisto, for Wodan, for yourselves! These fortifications are strong but if we succeed we shall all be rich!
Now, fight like night-spawned monsters, you bastards!
Do not jeer at the dying! But do not help! They are enemies!
Go and poison the fish, you bastards!
Thank the gods, the admiral! He wins battles, and no mistake!
By the gods! They are not brave then.
Rome's secrets are safe with me.
A pack of desert wolves circles around us, their maws foaming with impatient hunger. We will now show them that Zenobia and her host are not an easy prey! Bleed the wolves!
Form up! Keep those lines straight.
I hope they can swim for their sake.
I don't give a toss. Target in range!
Gouge and cut and slice everything you see, men!
Burn or drown\? Well, I've always liked the sea...
Glad that farce is over with.
Vulcan's iron arse! Put that fire out, you seaweed-sucking fools!
Take aim, fire on the shore!
Take aim, fire on the shore!
Take aim, fire on the shore!
Take aim, fire on the shore!
Take aim, fire on the shore!
I have chosen where I will die. You should do the same.
Hell hounds and little girls hiding behind them! Let's get 'em!
Elephants\? I'm not scared of- ELEPHANTS!
Elephants! We're in for it now!
Elephants\? More trouble than they're worth, lad!
Watch out! It's those big bastard elephants!
That course isn't open to us!
This is a cruel and foul people! They deserve to die! And I will happily lead you into battle against them! They'd best pray to their German gods to welcome them to the afterlife!
I will see you all drinking with our ancestors.
This vile army in front of us are German. You may have heard of them. You will certainly have smelt them by now. They are a dirty bunch of arses. And that's just the women!

The gods these people believe in are evil usurpers of our own revered deities. They carry many of our traditions and even pretend to fight like us. But today we shall show them the true way of the warrior!
The land beyond the Rhine has thrown forth many a worthy warrior. This wild clan of fighters stands proud and we must use all our wiles to defeat them! Prepare for battle!
To drink the new wine next year…
This is an evil day to die. Evil.
You know, lads, on balance, I'd sooner be playing dice.
Where's the general\? Shouldn't we have seen him\?
In the name of all our ancestors who have fallen to this German scum, lift up your weapons! Roar out to those who dare take us on! And then slice them all in two!
Generals\? Don't worry about generals! They don't worry about you!

See the savages from across the Rhine! They are the ones who give us all a bad name, for they are animals. We are lumped together with these louts! Bah! I suggest we kill them and dice them! How civilised!
Boars, boars, boars! They're obssessed with them! When we kill them we should spit roast a few of them and see if they like that. I fancy a bit of hot German meat inside me! Er… that sounds wrong…
Garm, the great German hound of the Underworld, awaits us on this battlefield. Be sure to watch his fangs for he is a hard son-of-a-bitch. Let us go to work and cut him down!
At them! Not a moment's rest!
Has anybody seen the standard recently\?
Soldier! Put that down! RIGHT NOW!
You lazy, horrible litte soldiers! Kill them!

Germans! They are filthy things from the northern end of a pig going south, and you should not fear them! They are beneath consideration as worthy foes! Would you be defeated by them\? No! So: we fight!

Germans! I will not lie: they are a hard-faced people and fierce warriors. But they are not soldiers! They are barbarians, ill-suited to open battle! Follow my commands and I swear we will be victorious against them!

Do not be deceived, men! Their aspect is foul and their stench almost unbearable, but these Germans are not the spawn of evil. No, these are merely men and, like men, they die readily when run through! To arms!
Right men: send them to the Ferryman!

Blood-soaked and uncouth they may be, but the Germans over there are terrified! They face you, and fear eats at their guts! We will shortly go and release them from fear! We will give them the release of death!
Calm down, man, or I'll gut you myself!

Rome! I have longed for this sight! Now, we are heroes! Soon, with one step further, my brothers, we will take this city and we shall become legends! Draw up your  courage! And march with me into history!

These Britons bark and growl like dogs, but we will whip them and their kind into obedience! We will yoke them like any dumb beasts, and put them to work! But first we must break them in battle! Make ready!

These dogs bark, but do they bite\? We will put that to the test, men. We will answer their craven noise with sword, spear and arrow, and teach them the real meaning of fear! We will make them fear us!
We may die here, but before that, we fight here!
Remember your loved ones! Do not shame them!
Best thing for them: a good wash!

What fools! They are as a herd of dumb beasts, easy to outwit and quick to frighten! If we hold and keep our courage, these Britons will break upon us and, fury spent, they will flee back to their hovels!

You can smell British fear, the unwashed swines! Do not let their wailing rob you of courage, men! These Britons only try to cast their own fear upon you. You will see, as they break and run before us. Make ready!
Ha! The enemy captain is taking orders from his mum!
I will guard our secrets, with my life.
Rome's secrets are safe with me.
Today we face an army of pig-lovers, and worse. These beasts lack all human sense. They drink, rut and thieve without restraint! This will not be a battle, but a Gaul hunt! Get ready!

Over there are Gauls, mead-drunk, blood-drunk and pride-swollen, ready for a fight. What fools! There is more to battle than a belly awash with strong drink! Soon they will be soaked with fear! Get ready!
It won't be long now, men. This will be a glorious day.
I shall don the Helm of Darkness…
I shall don the Helm of Darkness…
I will deliver them to Hades.
I will deliver them to Hades.
Let them come a little closer, I think… Make ready!
Our charges are yours to command!
If they're in range… doesn't that mean we are too\?
Our charges are yours to command!
He's not met your wife, has he\?
Think of your wives! Be brave!
May the gods bless us, my fellow men!
Our charges are yours to command!
Keep your prayers to yourself, boy.
Our charges are yours to command!
No! I am a champion of Rome!
Get water on those flames! Do it now!
No! I am a citizen of Rome!
In good order, pull your files back!
Send these whore sons to Anubis!
What shame is there in death\?
Don't you worry about them elephants. Stick by me!
That course isn't open to us!
Bravery! Honour! The gods! And good women! That's why we fight!
No man turns away from the enemy!
Don't panic! Whatever you do don't panic!
Take that man's name! His armour is a disgrace!
We are fortunate, today, in our choice of enemies.
This is not a good place for a battle.
Pray to Nun we stay afloat.
You! What's your bloody name and number\?
And in our choice of friends, sir!
You always say that. Misery guts.
Send them screaming to the afterlife!
Watch it! You nearly had my head!
Mars! Give me a moment longer, for revenge!
He's a modest man, our admiral, for one favoured by Poseidon…

What a stench! But do not fear, men, their smell is the worst we suffer today! These German man-whores will trouble us only by their outrageous prices! The best thing to do is pay them in steel! Make ready!
We may die here, but before that, we fight here!

These Germans are not even fit to be slaves! I fear we will have little profit from our captives today! It is probably best, then, to kill them. Do not think of this as lost gold, but as glory gained! To arms!
Be careful what you wish for, son.

These German thugs annoy me, and insult us! Barbarians! They worship trees and rocks, as if such things could match the true majesty of our gods. We shall put an end to these barbarous dogs! To arms, men!
I could get used to this. I want some more.

I beg your forgiveness, men! The foes we face today are beneath your contempt! That we should have to sully ourselves fighting the likes of these Germans pains me! Let us make this swift, and put them to flight!

Germans! This scum and their black ways are an affront to all civilized men! Aye, and a danger too! I ask you, will we let such a threat go unchallenged\? No, we will face them, and we will crush them!
Do not fear these painted fools, men! They worship bogs and streams, and tiny gods! We shall show them their folly, their hubris, when we put them to the sword and pull down their shrines!

Painted fools! Daubed in mud and tattoos, their stench and manner is only the most public of their many faults! We shall meet their cries ands shouts with sword and spear, and it will be us who are victorious!
The squid of these waters are good eating, I'm told.
Britons! What craven fools they are! They must shout and hurl insults to fill their hearts with courage! Let them shout, and let them screech! Ignore their jibes, men! We shall answer with death!
Do not be deceived, these foul creatures have courage and strength! If we are to break them, we must match British fury! We must become like lions! Find your courage, men! And make ready!
Do you recall the story of Tiresias\?...

Is there anything more admirable than a Gaul's moustache\? Truly, it is facial hair deserving of its own patron gods! The men behind the moustaches, though, are little bastards! We will kill them all presently!
I will guard Rome's secrets with my life.
Our secrets are safe with me.

I will not leave this place without Gaul blood on my sword! This I swear by all the gods, and by the honour of my ancestors! I will have blood! And you, men, will have victory! I have spoken. Make ready!
I do not care for Gauls. Their cooking is awful, their women uncooperative, their religion barbarous and their table manners leave much to be desired. What say you, my soldiers\? Shall we kill them\?
Gauls are by turns cowardly and stupidly brave! Today, I hope, we meet Gauls on a day when their gods of stupidity require proper worship by their followers! Either way, give them no quarter!
By the souls of my venerated ancestors, this is an excellent day for killing Gauls! Any day is a good day for killing Gauls, but today it feels particularly right and proper! So, let's be at them!

An unpleasant folk, the Gauls: short-tempered, unwashed, rude, crude, and given to horrible cruelty when they get the chance. I am sorry that I must ask you to fight them. I am not sorry that we must kill them!
A thinking man is powerful indeed.
I thrive on ledgers and accounts!
Knowledge overcomes ignorance as sunlight does darkness.
If I should fall, make sure my son receives this…
I shall see to the grain stores.

Our Gallic foes are moon-struck fools for daring to stand against us, men! What can ill-disciplined barbarians, incapable of doing more than grunting at each other, hope to achieve here\? We shall give them death!

Men, I must ask you now to face an army of Gauls: barbarians feared by, well, farm animals, mostly. Their practices are unmanly, unclean and not suitable for the delicate ears of honest soldiers! Prepare to fight them!
You may as well get comfy, men!
You may as well get comfy, men!
What are we waiting for\? She is in range, isn't she\?
Remember your families today. Fight with their love in your hearts!
I am a champion of the gods, no!
I will show them a better way.
Their men will doubt their authority.
Nature teaches beasts to know their friends.
No man can resist a reasoned argument.
I saw a flock of ravens over there…
I will make them doubt their leaders.
There goes any chance of getting some loot.
We're done here, boys! Back off!
Dry land! Excellent! I never did like fish!
Thank the gods! I didn't drown!
We will not give up! Death will take our foes!
But have too much good sense!
Hold fast now! They're only elephants!
You heard him! Nothing to worry about!
That course isn't open to us!
To travel is to be truly free!
To travel is to be truly free!
To travel is to be truly free!
No fear, men. Show them no fear.
To travel is to be truly free!
Clear the dead! Over the side with them!
Wipe those brains off your armour! You don't want stains!
It is a bad cut. You will live.
This is bad. I seem to have lost my eye.
Kill! Kill! Kill! Kill! How many more times\?
Lesser men stop fighting! We do not!
Be brave, my brothers! Take heart! Take heart!
Yes! Give thanks to the gods! We have prevailed!
Zeus' thunderbolts! They are quite good shots!
If I see fear in any man, he is dead!
The gulls will grow fat today!
Yonder! See! The admiral. He's a good 'un to follow, lads!
Off you go, you useless tossers! And don't come back!
Men, if you would be so kind: kill them!
I will guard Rome's secrets with my life.
A thinking man is powerful indeed.
Seth save us from these foreign scum!
I thrive on ledgers and accounts!
Knowledge overcomes ignorance as sunlight does darkness.
They dragged us here for this\?
I shall see to the grain stores.
Stop your whining. I won't tell you again.
The Egyptian sands will consume them…
The Egyptian sands will consume them…
The Egyptian sands will consume them…
The Egyptian sands will consume them…
That ship! It still floats! Why\?
Be ready to rip them from this world!
May the gods charge our bows! Aim true, boys!
With the fury of the Gods!
With the fury of the Gods!
With the fury of the Gods!
With the fury of the Gods!
With the fury of the Gods!
With the fury of the Gods!
With the fury of the Gods!
With the fury of the Gods!
With the fury of the Gods!
The bards shall sing of this days for generations to come, men!
Him and his bloody bards! Sick of 'em, I am!
I am a champion of the gods, no!
I am unable to travel this road.
Put those flames out now! Save the ship!
I saw a flock of ravens over there…
What honour is there in this\?
Enough not to throw our lives away, lad.
Are they from Gaul\? They smell like it.
I think I'm going to throw up!
Not on my time you don't!
Did you practice being stupid and cowardly, or does it come naturally\?
Right now, I wish artillery had never been invented!
Prepare! Make ready, and cheer, you miserable sods!
Ares give us strength! I do not like the look of this! Not one bit!
By Teutates, they've called the dogs on us!
That course isn't open to us!
May the gods greet us today!
Damage party! Get to work, you lubbers!
You! Stop bleeding on my deck!
Deck crew! Get those bloodstains washed away!
Throw the dead overboard! Clear away!
You men! Buckets and mops! NOW!

If we are victorious, I swear before you all, I shall make great sacrifices to Ba'al and Tanit in thanks for their aid. But they only aid those who are worthy! Fill your hearts with courage and purpose, men, and we shall strike terror in our foe!
Strike low! Strike low! Into their bellies!
Mars and Jupiter! Protect me! If there's still wine to drink…
If I see fear in any man, he is dead!
Good killing. Now wait for your orders.
Boarding masters! Keep your men at it!
I feel so much better, hearing that.
Lesser men stop fighting! We do not!
Wind and waves! This is a fine day!
Row, you shits! Run for cover, and hope we don't follow!
Anyone who breaks formation will be punished!
I will guard our secrets, with my life.
Thoth, bless me with your knowledge.
I shall see to the needs of the children of the Nile.
I will do what is best for Pharaoh's servants.
They could settle this with champions.
I shall see to the grain stores.
By all that is sacred, by Garm's bollocks and Tyr's wrath, fill your hearts with courage and storm these walls. Who knows what awaits us\? But when we prevail this will be a great victory indeed!
You fire when the officer gives an order, not before!
These waters are spoiled, man. The enemy still float on them!
Target in range! Archers at the ready!

Any of you who desert their post shall face my wrath. And believe me you would not like me when I am angry! I grow fur and fangs and become like the terrible hound, Garm! So to your positions and defend this place!
The Egyptian sands will consume them…
The Egyptian sands will consume them…

What is Rome, but a squalid cesspit of well-dressed thieves\? The men we face lack true honour. Yes, they have a certain arrogance, but the same can be said of wolves! And it was a wolf that they were whelped!
This is what we've waited for, lads!

We face only Romans! We must match their stupidity with stern resolve, their sullen stubborness with courage! Men, I promise you that we shall be victorious if we do! We can break these fools and send them scurrying back to Rome!
You may have. I'd rather be at home.

These Roman dogs are tenacious! Cut one legion down and, like the Hydra's heads, two seem to grow anew. But we will hack them down! We will burn to the heart of the Roman people, and be victorious! To arms!

Romans! They would spread their empire across the world! This must not happen! Would you bend the knee to Rome\? Would you have them decide our fate\? No, no we must fight, and we must drive these Romans back!
No! I am a champion of Rome!
I see Dionysus has been with you!

Mighty Pharaoh, the Sword of Two Lands, and all of Egypt are watching us today! We stand here in His name and in their defence. We must not shame Him by fleeing before this inbred rabble! No, we stand! And we must triumph!
Have you taken leave of your senses\?
Put the fires out! Dampen the flames!
Do you think me a fool\?
Work quickly, men! Get those flames out!
Stop squeaking like a girl and help put it out!
No! I am a citizen of Rome!
Gods be good! I will not!
Don't ask you fool! Just get out of here.
Withdraw! Steady now! Keep your guard up!
Why does he want us to retreat\?
The gods love us! They give us more enemies, and more glory!
More of the enemy join the madness.
Ships ahoy! Here comes more scum.
By Nun! They have more coming to help!
Our duty will sink the enemy, as long as we hold to it!
Honour will sink enemy ships, if we act honourably!
Be sorry for the crabs. They will have poor fare today.
Want to live\? Then get us moving, you curs!
I've had enough of this! Can't we surrender!
Keep those dogs at bay! Deal with them quickly.
To travel is to be truly free!
You're fast, for an old man.
How do you think I got to this age, lad\?
To travel is to be truly free!
To travel is to be truly free!
Maybe... but a sign for us, or for them\?
Last night's sky was a sign from Poseidon, I tell you!
I would have land beneath my feet!
Don't be strangers! Send us a letter!
And I a deck beneath mine. Sir!
Leave our dead where they've fallen. There will be time for them later.
Leave him! Leave him! Fight, you idiot!
I've defended gates, then I took an arrow in the knee…
That path is blocked, my lord.
If they hit us we've had it, sir. We must move!
Gods help us! We can't take this punishment for long.
That\? That is a banner of fools, carried by fools!
There he is, swanning about like he knows what he's doing…
To be honest, I was getting bored with sailors!
Best when he stays in his tent, though.
He's a very important man, the general…

Let us bring down the walls of Carthage! Let us bring their shining city low! For the glory of our people and our gods, we shall sack this place. Its treasures and wealth shall be ours! Make ready, men!

Let us end the dominance of Carthage! Bring its merchants and nomad sons low! Too long we have suffered their arrogance. We shall teach them humility as we sack this place, and claim its riches for our own!
They block My path\? Do they know who I am\?!
I cannot do that, my lord.
What is this madness you speak\?
How dare they stand before me!
I am unable to do as you ask.

Cowering behind these walls is the former might of Carthage. Merchants and a few hired mercenaries are all that stand between us and victory. Victory and eternal glory! Victory and the wealth of Carthage!
Only those touched by the Moon would do that!
No one blocks my path and lives to tell the tale!
Sadly I cannot do as you ask.
How dare they\?! I'll have their heads!
I am sorry, my lord, I cannot.
O Gods! My mouth is as dry as the sands.
Well, sit me down and get me a fat one! That's a bloody relief!
Today we will bring Carthage low and its people to their knees! We shall teach them humility. Either they will accept our yoke or we shall put them to the sword! Victory! Victory over Carthage!
What do you wish of me\?
How can I be of assistance\?
By Andarta, that was terrible. Give me war any day!
I cannot do what you ask of me.
It's too late. You're a dead man.
Come on, you monkeys, do you want to live forever\?
To our shame, this day will long be remembered.
Eyes front! No flinching! Show them how brave Romans behave!
We hunger for blood and battle!
We hunger for blood and battle!
I had something like that in mind…

Listen to them! That is the sound of cowardly Gauls looking for courage! Drink has addled their wits! Strange rites have clouded their thoughts! We shall now show them divine Pharaoh's magnificent army in action!
How anyone gets used to that I have no idea.
We're here! Wherever that may be.
I will guard your secrets, with my life.
I shall see Rome's people are well served.
I will see to the needs of the people.
I will do what is needed.
The gods have shown me what is best for the people.
I will make an offering to Athena.
The people need the wisdom of the Gods.
Take me away from all this death!
Get your men aloft! Riggers! Now!
Oarmaster! I need a steady beat from your musician, if you please!
Death is but a short voyage for men like us!
Try not to be so cheerful, old thing!
Face me! Come fight me, you sons of bitches!
Courage men. We'll get our chance!
Battle drunk fool! Protect the commander!
My widow will weep on the shore soon enough!
More of them! The gods turn their backs on us!
More ships, mean more spoils, lads. Be happy!
More of them come to join the party.
All hands! Keep a weather eye out!
You landsmen! Stop holding your bellies! You won't die!
Every man will do his utmost, or the fish will be well fed!
We're going to need a bigger boat.
You always say that. But you're usually right…
Unpleasant\? Yes, but not as bad as my old mum's cooking!
Turn us about! Make ready to withdraw.
Blow! Blow, like tritons! And raise a storm!
Take aim, fire on the shore!
Take aim, fire on the shore!
Take aim, fire on the shore!
Take aim, fire on the shore!
Take aim, fire on the shore!
Take aim, fire on the shore!
Take aim, fire on the shore!
Take aim, fire on the shore!
Take aim, fire on the shore!
I'll have the men calm and quiet, if you please!
That was good work! The foul thing needed to go!
Glad to see the back of that!
Our captain, it is said, is the brother of Charon himself!
If I fall, keep them at it!
Oi! Bring us back some loot! Or some good wine!
Keep them busy! Plenty of blade work yet!
Take a trophy! Leave the rest to the birds.
By Jupiter and Mars! Do not run from the enemy, my soldiers, my sons! You are Romans and each worth a thousand of them! Stand, I say!
I feel like a fish, in a ship sized barrel!
That's our admiral, lad, and we're royally buggered.
No, lad, we get the risks, the general gets the glory.
General's here to take a few risks with us!
You expect me to do that!\?
I cannot do that, my lord.
The goddess informs me that this would be madness.
I am unable to travel this road.
