Today I ask you to fight Egyptians. They think rather highly of themselves. They are entirely wrong-headed, for they die and run like other men, as we shall shortly prove! To arms!
I am sure we will reach an arrangement…
You cannot ask me to do this!
What is this madness you speak\?
I am unable to do as you ask.
Today we fight that fine collection of dung beetles and crocodile bait, the Egyptians! There's not one of them worth the piss needed to put him out if he was on fire! However… Make ready.
Only those touched by the Moon would do that!
Sadly I cannot do as you ask.
I cannot do as you ask.
My way is blocked, my lord.
A well placed threat has great power.
Of course we won, you prat. I'm here!
So, they have some honour then!
This things you ask, is impossible!
I am sorry but I cannot.
Let the men loot the dead, they've earned it today.
Carefully chosen words are as powerful as any weapon.
We've won! I can't believe it! We won!
I am sure we will be able to come to some arrangement.
The Goddess will not allow this.
Anyone who breaks formation will be punished!
Anyone who breaks formation will be punished!
Anyone who breaks formation will be punished!
Anyone who breaks formation will be punished!
Anyone who breaks formation will be punished!
As a Gaul I love fighting the Egyptians. They are so funny in their hats and colours. Their banners and chariots. Oh, please let them have some chariots! I want to ride on a chariot!
I swore, before you and the gods, that I would put our foes to the sword. That I would not rest until their last army was utterly broken and we stood victorious! The day has come! Make ready, men!
Someone seeks to bar my passage.

I will not call on the gods for their will is clear! Before us is all that remains of our enemies' strength. The gods have favoured us, not them, and today we repay that honour by doing bloody slaughter!
I cannot do as you ask.
My path is blocked, my lord.
That is an end to it. Now let me rest.
Don't never mind me, boy, just them!
Draw swords, men. And pray to Mars!
The way appears to be blocked.
Run well, you bastards! It was an honour to serve with you!
Before us is the last strength of our foes. Victory will end the war and bring the peace we have long sought. I ask of you one last glorious effort, one last bloody battle! To arms, men! Make ready!
Before us stand the last of our enemy. Their last army capable of opposing us… Victory today means glory and honour, and the end of this war! The rewards of conquest are soon to be yours! Make ready!
My wits and words are yours.
I feel ill. Can't believe we have to fight now.
What do you wish of me\?
The enemy will never know our secrets.
Our secrets are safe with me.
The roots of knowledge are bitter, but the fruit is sweet.
My hand! I can't feel my hand!
It's right beside you, down there!
Do not worry about the enemy, you men! Look to your duties!
Who said you could be seasick\? Clean it up!
To travel is to be truly free!
To travel is to be truly free!
Fight! Drive them back! Break them!
Bloody artillery! Typical of such cowardly vermin.
Come on, you men! It's a big bloody target, so hit the buggers!
More of them, I see. More glory for us, praise the gods!
More fish for our nets, I see.
Any slackers will be boiled alive! With crabs!
Now, bosun, let us pray for a fair wind and a good fight!
Don't splash about! This is a battle, not a children's outing!
Don't let the dogs into our ranks!
Regroup, you bastard sons of whores! Regroup!
Sir, shall we kill them all now\?
Poseidon! Send your fishy minions to eat their faces!
Posiedon! Give me an easy death, I beg it!
Your neighbour. He's probably feeding" your wife too…"
Who is going to feed the chickens\?
You will stand or, by Jupiter, I will have you beaten with rods after my victory! I will have no cowardice! Now, fight like Romans!
I will skin any man who leaves his post!
So, the enemy think they can sink us\? Ha!
For now… But not for much longer under this fire.
That, lads, is our admiral. Splendid figure of a man, I'm told.

By all the gods of our people! I did not think it was possible to smell an Egyptian army from quite so far away! Still, that's what happens when people spend their lives kissing divine Pharaoh's glorious arse! Bah!

Egypt is an ancient land, men. And luckily for us, it's people fight like old women. Now, there isn't much glory in killing grandmothers, but it's something that sometimes has to be done. Put aside your softer feelings!
You expect me to do that!\?
I cannot do that, my lord.
I will show them a better way.
I am sure we will reach an arrangement…
You cannot ask me to do this!
I am unable to do as you ask.
Give the Ferryman some work! Kill the cowards!
Stab the bastards in the back, if that's what it takes!
Keep going! They're running! They're running!
Kill them all, lad, especially the ones who run!
Sadly I cannot do as you ask.
No man can live in a world without trust.
Men, I will not ask much of you today, only this: send these Egyptian sand flies back to their dry, dusty hovels! I am almost ashamed to ask real soldiers to fight such wretches! Prepare!
A well placed threat has great power.
Where are the foes worthy to meet me\?
This things you ask, is impossible!
I am sorry but I cannot.
That was thirsty work. You! Go fetch me some wine.
Over there is an army of Egyptians and their Greek masters. They are here to escape their miserable dung-filled lives of drudgery for their Pharaoh! I say we oblige them with the escape of death!
Carefully chosen words are as powerful as any weapon.
Up my arse, waiting to be shat out!

I dedicate our coming victory to my ancestors! By all we hold sacred, I hope those camel-loving Egyptians will never know why their gods abandoned them to our non-existent mercies! Now, prepare yourselves!
I am sure we will be able to come to some arrangement.
I will make them doubt their leaders.

It is time to send that rabble back to the sands that spawned them! Those Egyptians, servants of a foreign Pharaoh, are too sun-addled to realise that they are being used. Will they notice being killed\?
Over there is an army of the Egypt. Not one of them would make a good husband for an honest woman, unless she was dead, dried out, and wrapped in bandages. Strange folk, then, and best killed!
Get the men out of the water

This Egyptian army is most insolent to stand against us! Shouldn't they all be at home, worshipping a goat or something\? Or licking Pharaoh's... toes clean\? Isn't that work more suited to them\? Bah! Make ready, men!
I cannot do as you ask.
I will stand here until ordered!
My wits and words are yours.
Anyone seeing me on a boat again has my permission to kill me!
What do you wish of me\?
Deck master! Close up your boarding parties!
A wise man whispers his secrets.
The enemy will never know our secrets.
Our secrets are safe with me.
Your secrets are safe with me.
The roots of knowledge are bitter, but the fruit is sweet.
Who has vomited on my deck\? Who was it\?
Um, that was me, deckmaster, sir!
Anchor stones and arseholes! Are you idiots, or what\? Fire!
Men! Mark your targets carefully! Do not shoot into the sea!
May Andraste give us one more blessing so that we may be spared today on the field of battle. We are the last, we happy few. Now we carry the honour of all the ancestors and our fallen brothers!
Widows' wailing will keep the tritons awake for years!
More of our foes join the chaos. The gods are truly fickle!
There's more of them over there!
All warriors to their posts, as ordered!
I expect every man to do his duty!
Our enemies will poison the fish today.
Dogs! The cowards have set dogs on us.
Always glad to see a bit of kit taken down lad, always glad!
I'm not dying easily! Not like those bastards!
Regroup on our standard, men. Find your courage!
Right now, I could use a cup of good wine!
So this is glory… I hoped for better!
Look to your weapons! Keep steady, now!
That path is blocked, my lord.
Now, fight like cursed monsters, or I'll have your skins for drumheads!
By the gods! They mean to rain terror down on us!
Either they hit you… Dead! The ship… Sunk! Or miss… They try again!
Over there! It's the admiral. Nice helmet, I'll give him that.
Our admiral. Well... Thing is, he's a lover, not a fighter…
Lover of the enemy, more like.

Would we allow these creatures of Pontus to bring disgrace to noble Pharaoh, the light of Egypt\? A thousand times: No! We shall show them how to fight, and let them show us how to die! To arms, sons of the Nile!
What about us having a breather\?
I will show them a better way.
What is this madness you speak\?
The Goddess enjoys a little meddling.
Don't let them rest! Kill! Kill the buggers!
Push them back! Push them back!
Keep at them! Don't let them rally!
Only those touched by the Moon would do that!
Back! Live to fight another day!
Steady, there. No need to worry about a few idiots over there.
Without trust an army is nothing.
Round up any of the enemy able to walk. Leave the rest.
Back! Live to fight another day!
Bless the boar's arse! We routed them good and proper!
The Goddess has told me what must be done.
Dry land! Excellent! I never did like fish!
I want their banner! To me, men, to me!
If you're going to be sick, you bunch of girls, make sure it's over the enemy!
I will pluck out their eyes.
The enemy will never know our secrets.
I will guard your secrets, with my life.
Our secrets are safe with me.
I shall see Rome's people are well served.
Do I look like I care that you are seasick, oarsman\?
Clear for action! Quickly now! Last man in place will be punished!
Lay in and down from aloft! Clear away!
Who gave you permission to be sick\?
Sir, no, sir. Not a bit, sir.
I love my calling. It does allow me to meet new, interesting people and here are the Seleucids. Not even the druids know much about them. Still, pity we have to kill them. Onwards!
Aim at the men, not the woodwork, you lump of gull-shit!
Make sure it hurts, by all the gods!
I can see more ships. Are they ours, boy\?
Pluto's dead arse! What a bunch of fish-faced twats!
Are you sure they're not on our side\?
The sharks will feast well today!
Riggers! Make sure our banner is flying! Let them see it!
The sharks are hungry. Stay out of the water.
No… Worse luck, it's more of theirs.

These Carthaginians think themselves a pious people, and value sacrifice to their gods most highly. Let them be their own sacrifices today! But do not, I beg you, look for omens in their entrails! Haha!
Those filthy curs, they've set dogs on us!

We march today against a rabble of Carthaginian mercenaries and military whores! Carthaginians lack all courage and pay others to fight for them! We need only kill a few for the rest to run! Make ready!
Always glad to see a bit of kit taken down lad, always glad!
Form up, you curs! Form up on our standard!
Let's look to a fair wind, if Proteus is kind!
Go on, you buggers! Get off and do some work!

Parthians! Merchants and masters of the short measure, not warriors! Would you allow the likes of them to unman you\? I thought not! Today we shall break these cheating pedlars, and show them war in all its glory!
Look to your weapons! Keep steady, now!

Parthians! We may as well be fighting a flock of peacocks, for all their finery and clucking. Do not be afraid of their display, these timid birds shall soon turn tail! Draw your swords, men, and make ready!
Men! Would you attack, please, NOW!

I swear before you and the gods, that I walk from temple to temple in slave's garb if we do not have victory over these Parthian peacocks! They are as witless as birds, and it shall to my eternal shame if they defeat us!

Parthia! Pah! We shall teach these patterned and perfumed fools for daring to oppose us! They are little more than bandits from the hills and slaves with spears thrust into their hands! We are soldiers! And we will triumph!
Scrape my backside clean of barnacles! They mean to sink us!
Sir! Captain! Sir! Your wine is shot through, sir! It's gone!
Stop skulking below! Man your posts!
A little gold buys many friends.

We shall send these unwashed goats fleeing back to the mountains of Pontus. These spawn of Persian whores and Thracian dogs are no challenge to true soldiers! We shall put any that stand to the sword! Make ready, men!
Weak men are so easily corrupted…
The way is blocked, my lord.

What strength has Pontus\? Their lords are craven, their armies are unwashed wretches from the hills, simpletons who are scared of the Moon! Their only true power is their stench! Prepare, men, for we claim victory this day!
Everyone has dark secrets they wish to hide.
I am unable to travel this road.
Doubt is a terrible thing, my lord.
I will show them a better way.

These goats are not overburdened with courage! Like goats they bleat and will flee back the hard mountains of Pontus when scared! I promise you they will run, men! This is not battle, we simply chase fools!
The Goddess enjoys a little meddling.

We face farmers, goat-herders and slaves: the might of Pontus! Would you be beaten by such wretches\? Would you bring dishonour on our people, on the gods, by falling to such as these village oafs\? I thought not! To arms!
Trust in one's superiors can be fragile…
My sword has swayed many men.
My sword has swayed many men.
My sword has definitely gone limp.
How dare they stand before me!
I will show them a better way.
Without trust an army is nothing.
I will make them an offer they can't refuse.
I'm so happy I could cry!
Battle will stiffen you up, lad, just to wait…
I will make them doubt their leaders.
The Goddess has told me what must be done.
Let us pray, that this is not the beginning of our own Odyssey.
With the fury of the Gods!
Mithra has abandoned us! More of them!
Fight, curse your entrails with maggots! Fight!
Now we show them Roman courage, men! Stand ready!
The way is closed to me.
Warriors! Repel boarders, if you please!
I will pluck out their eyes.

This is their last refuge! Here they make their final stand! I will not lie to you, the fighting today will be bloody and hard, for they have nowhere else to flee. What I can promise is glory! Glory, and the spoils! Begin the assault!

This is the last, their final refuge. Do not be mistaken, they are far from done! Even a rat when cornered will find courage to fight fiercely. It will not avail them though, and we shall crush them utterly!
We stand at the edge of greatness and our actions today will long be remembered! These walls cannot keep us from our destiny, men. Today they will fall, and this war shall, I think, come to an end!
The enemy will never know our secrets.

We have cornered them here but, like a lioness guarding her cubs, they will not give up easily. We have time and numbers on our side, but what glory is there in delay\? No, we attack! We end this now!
Our secrets are safe with me.
I've seen dockside floozies who can pull better than you lot!
Steersman! Get those sailors working as if they mean it!
Give it to them in their bellies!
Give them some fire, you sea-dogs! Kill them, lest they kill you!
The tritons here defend their fish. This is not a good place.
More of them, I see. More glory for us, praise the gods!
I haven't had guts like this since that banquet in Ostia!
The enemy expect to feed us to the fish, the bastards…
Let us make this a floating nightmare for the enemy!
The sharks already circle! They are cruel!

Over there is an army dedicated to vice, corruption, greed, gold and probably the unnatural love of elephants! They are Carthaginians, and we all know that means they are all scum! Kill them! Kill them all!
I'll worry about those ships. You, get on with your work!
Don't splash about! This is a battle, not a children's outing!
The gang of scorpions yonder are waiting to die for Carthage. Apparently fiece but... Cut off their stings and they are just insects. Beware the stings as you cut them! Make ready!
Tritons curse them! They are good!

Men, behold a Carthaginian army! It is a sight to gladden the heart of absolutely nobody, except panderers, pimps, whores, catamites and undertakers! Why the last\? Because they are better dead! Make ready!

Men, if any of you doubt that our enemies need killing, think on this: the Carthaginians throw their own children into fires! What kind of people do that\? What kind of people are proud of that\? Give them death!

It is often difficult to tell Carthaginians from elephant droppings! Both smell appalling! Carthaginians, men, are the ones with swords and spears! Kill them, and try not to tread in the droppings! Now, to arms!
It is unusual to see so many Carthaginians in one place without them wriggling about in front of some brazen idol! Never mind, shortly they will be wriggling about on our spear points! To arms!
Dogs always look hungry. But they look extra hungry.
Carthaginians love gold and unnatural murder more than they love life itself! We do the gods a great service if we wipe out the stain of their existence. Now, make ready to shed their blood!

Do not concern yourself with those Carthaginians" yonder. Few will be honest sons of Carthage, if there is such a thing. Carthaginians, cowards all, pay others to die for them. Let us give them death!"
Find your courage! And we'll take back our honour!

Let us break the dominance of Carthage and unite these lands under the rule of Pharaoh, blessed be He! Our glory will be unmatched! Your rewards the rich pickings of Carthage, the spoils of battle! Make ready!
Poseidon's bearded blessings! A good day for killing!
Off you go, landlubbers! Go and earn your pay!
Hey! Is your mum still selling her arse to merchants\?
Men, there's loot to be had! But wait 'til they're dead!
Romans! Stand and prepare to fight once more! Put some iron in your bellies and good Roman courage in your hearts! Now, to war again!
These day's she sells your dad's bum!

Perfumed, craven fools and their hired brigands: that is who we face today! They may look impressive, but they will not stand for they are not brave warriors! We shall soon put them to flight, I promise you! Make ready!

The Parthians look impressive, do they not\? Dressed in finery but, hear me, men, they are not warriors! They may parade like peacocks, but we shall pluck those feathers and roast them shortly! They lack your courage! To arms!

We are our people's shield, the last hope of Carthage! Would you have their light gone from the world\? Would you have our people, your wives, sons and daughters, become slaves\? No, we must fight! For Carthage!

These Parthian goats bleat of glory, but they lack the wherewithall to triumph! They are a dishonoured people, in want of strong leadership ever since birth! Today we shall show them what men can achieve! Make ready!

Would you dishonour our people and our gods, by losing to these perfumed fools and their caravan guards\? No! The shame would be too much! We shall put these fine Parthian birds to flight! Now, let's hunt!
So, the enemy think they can sink us\? Ha!
Curses, I've got a splinter in me!
Yes, they're having a good try.
Good manners prevent me speaking ill of the admiral…
So that's the admiral. Can't say I'm surprised we're in trouble…
I will show them a better way.
I will show them a better way.
How dare they stand before me!
The Gods have shown me what must be done.
No one blocks my path and lives to tell the tale!
No man can live in a world without trust.
Men: swords drawn, and make ready!
How dare they\?! I'll have their heads!
Without trust an army is nothing.
I'm so hapy I could kiss you!
They don't need good boots where they're going, do they\?
I speak with the voice of my people.
I will make them doubt their leaders.
Good... We could do with some colour about the place.
Brave men, hear the voice of Zenobia! Numbers hold meaning only for merchantmen and peddlers! We are neither! We are warriors and being outnumbered only adds to the glory of our victory! Attack!
Anyone who breaks formation will be punished!
Anyone who breaks formation will be punished!
Anyone who breaks formation will be punished!
Anyone who breaks formation will be punished!
Anyone who breaks formation will be punished!
Anyone who breaks formation will be punished!
Anyone who breaks formation will be punished!
Anyone who breaks formation will be punished!
Anyone who breaks formation will be punished!
By all the gods, we have been favoured today! That army is the last of our enemies, the very last! Divine disfavour has been their lot, and I for one, am not surprised. Now, let us finish them!
My uncle was a sailor. Never got on with him.
See them off now, lads! Smartly does it!
A wise man whispers his secrets.
Your secrets are safe with me.
Haul, you miserable wretches, haul away!
Sailing master! Keep your men at their duties!
Sir! Already at their duties, sir!
Recruiting more ships for the tribe!
We're going to need a bigger fleet!
Recruiting more ships for the tribe!
We're going to need a bigger fleet!
Fire, you sea-wolves! Kill them now!
We're gonna need a bigger fleet!
We're gonna need a bigger fleet!
Parthians\? Are they wearing eye make up\? Or are they all women\? Where do they come from\? Why are we fighting such a worthless enemy\? Oh well, let's get on with it.
Look at this bunch of fools! They've come all dressed up! What do they think this is\? A party\? I'm not sure if they want to dance or fight. Let's find out, shall we\?
I lead you today, men, against the army of Parthia. They will, like all easterners, be treacherous and evil in their fighting. They are not men but demons! So watch your guard and fight as one!
I have heard told that the Parthians are evil and ruthless. They boil their babies and skin their women. I think we should teach them some manners. I think we should crush them!
The gods play with us... But the more enemies, the greater the glory.
Has anyone heard of Parthia\? Has any of our people ever fallen to a Parthian blade\? Have any of you warriors ever feared a Parthian before\? NO! But today they shall fear us!
We're done for! Look at that lot!
Apparently the Parthians love themselves. Really! They marry their sisters and make love to their dogs. And they eat their children. They are the demons of this world and it is our job to kill them!
All hands! Be proud! We go to glory!
When we are finished, the gulls will be bored with enemy gizzards!
All hands! Be proud! We go to glory!
Worry not! A bit of an enemy fleet, man, is nothing!
This ship… there is a smell of death to it…
Can I just go home instead\?
Shut up! Jupiter give me strength!
Curse them! That was my grandfather's blade!
He's mine! He's mine! I claim the honour!
Tell my children I died a soldier!
Look out, sir! He means to kill you!
Take aim, fire on the shore!
Take aim, fire on the shore!
Take aim, fire on the shore!
Take aim, fire on the shore!
Take aim, fire on the shore!
Take aim, fire on the shore!
Take aim, fire on the shore!
Take aim, fire on the shore!
Take aim, fire on the shore!
Sons of bitches, they've loosed the dogs on us!
Who are this lot\? Eh\? Prat-he-ans! Look like a load of prats to me! Come on, lads, let's teach these idiots how to fight! You have my permission to cut them to pieces!
Glad to see the back of that!
That was good work! The foul thing needed to go!
Easy, lad. Find your courage. Better this than being cut down.
But I only need to run quicker than you, old man.
Men! We will sail the waters of the Styx, if so ordered!
Twats. Who in his right mind gets off a boat to charge to a battle\?
May Ankou greet us on the other side!
Keep them busy! Plenty of blade work yet!
Men, you may be tired and scared. But so what\? You are Romans! Romans do not weaken or tire! Now, face your foes!
Artillery\? How in Hades' name did they get those\?
You there! Stop gawping and get to your - oh too late!
They've got us in range! Curse them!
No use cowering. If they hit us, they hit us!
They sing a pretty tune, for a bunch of bottom-munching worms!
Put your backs in to it!
I will show them a better way.
I am unable to travel this road.
The goddess informs me that this would be madness.
Put your backs in to it!
How dare they stand before me!
What is this madness you speak\?
The Gods have shown me what must be done.
No one blocks my path and lives to tell the tale!
Only those touched by the Moon would do that!
My way is blocked, my lord.
I cannot do as you ask.
I'll tell her after I shag her tonight.
How dare they\?! I'll have their heads!
Without trust an army is nothing.
I never tire of this part.
Yes! A noble and great victory. I must tell mother!
Victory\? No... You mean the looting.
I speak with the voice of my people.
The Goddess will not allow this.
At least he didn't fall on his face.
See! I take this land with both hands.
Not yet! Wait for it... Wait...
Someone seeks to bar my passage.
Fight, you bastards, or I will gut you for the crows!
My path is blocked, my lord.
The way appears to be blocked.
Yonder stands the last army of our enemy has that is capable of opposing us. They have been brave, but soon their worth will only be measured in widows' tears. Now, fight well!
Ha! I'd give them the runs, and you know it!
Those men over there fight for their homes, their wives and families and for the shreds of honour the gods have let them keep! This makes them dangerous! Keep your wits about you and a sword to hand!
Today, we face the last of this particular breed, men! It has been a long struggle to reach this ending and I, for one, will not be sorry when they are sent to the afterlife! Prepare your weapons!

The gods can be cruel, men, when they punish an entire people. Over there are soldiers the gods have decided to punish. It falls to us to exterminate them such is the will of by the gods. Now, make ready!
This will not be a day of glory, men! It will be messy, cruel and hard! We face their last army, and they will want to hurt us, even as they die! Be cruel in return! Let them die!
It is a humbling thing, to see an army the gods have abandoned! Look at our foes! They are all that is left to defend their people, because their gods no longer love them! Make ready!
So it has come to this: perhaps the last battle, against a foe almost worthy of our swords. If each man does his part, without showy heroics, then victory in this war is assuredly ours!
At last! Back on dry land, men.
Gods of our forefathers! Give us the strength, in this last battle, to fight without mercy and to finally destroy these vile creatures! Now, men, put aside all thoughts of home one more time! Fight!
All maybe lost! I fight on!
Now can we stand up and say we fought to the last\? Come on!
I swear, upon the honoured souls of my ancestors, that I will not rest until our foes are utterly destroyed. This is their last army and I am glad of it! Now, make yourselves ready!
Thank you. Deal with it, there's a good man.
All hands! Make ready to defend the ship!
Sir! We're on fire. Thought you'd like to know, sir!
Hang on to your oars, you fools!
Oarmaster! Punishment for that man later! He's not trying!
Hera! We offer you these enemies. Praise be unto you!
Men of Gaul! We defend today! When your brother falls beside you then make sure you double your efforst and fight for both of you! Listen for my commands and obey them! Hold this ground!
I would journey to the ends of the world for Makedon!
I would journey to the ends of the world for Makedon!
Men of Gaul! We fight today by standing our ground! Let them attack. Let them come to us and tire in their great exertions. We shall wait patiently and annihilate every wave!
Fire! Fire, you salt-stained sea-dogs! Fire!
Would that I were as swift as Hermes!
Would that I were as swift as Hermes!
The gods love us! They give us more enemies, and more glory!
There's more of them coming now.
Ah! For a good wind and a fine day…
The waves will wash your fear away, boy, you'll see!
Like crabs, we must rip our prey to pieces! And feast!
When we are done, even sharks will be bored with man-flesh!
Is there something he's not telling us\?
Has anybody seen my banner bearer\?
I seek a foe worthy of my skill!
You'll be looking for a very old leper, then…
Look at the size of them dogs!
Better to fight, than be run down like dogs.
A prayer to Poseidon might be a good idea!
All ashore who're going ashore! No hanging about, now!
You twats! Never get off the boat!
Remember your gods! Remember your fathers, once proud of their sons! Do not shame them more by running!
This is about as much fun as a cruise on the Styx!
Sir! Sir! Sir! Sir! Sir! Sir! Sir! Sir! Sir! Are we going to sink, sir\?
Look to the skies! They're  using artillery!
There he is. Our admiral. Bloody great loser.
Storms and tempests! What a bunch of dockyard whores!
Someone told me they have a staute of Taranis inside there stolen from our homeland. If it's true I want it! Their gods are foul! Take this city and take everything from these beasts!
A little gold buys many friends.
Weak men are so easily corrupted…
The way is blocked, my lord.
Everyone has dark secrets they wish to hide.
They block My path\? Do they know who I am\?!
Doubt is a terrible thing, my lord.
I am unable to travel this road.
I cannot do that, my lord.
How dare they stand before me!
I am unable to do as you ask.
No one blocks my path and lives to tell the tale!
Trust in one's superiors can be fragile…
Sadly I cannot do as you ask.
Goats of Pontus! These unwashed bandits and their lords are a poor match for our arms! We shall sweep them before us and send them scurrying back to their mountains! Let them brood on defeat!
How dare they stand before me!
How dare they\?! I'll have their heads!
I will show them a better way.
I am sorry, my lord, I cannot.
Collect weapons, armour, anything of value from the dead.

Gods, give me a worthy foe, from somewhere other than Pontus! I pity thse simple farmers and hillsmen, whipped by their princes into this battle. Most will die without understanding or a chance to defend themselves! Ah, well, to arms!
I will make them an offer they can't refuse.
I will make them doubt their leaders.
What do you wish of me\?
Our foes from Pontus think so little of us that they send farmers, brigands and hillmen against us! We shall drive the poor wretches back to their  mountain hovels and caves! Make ready!
Like being fish\? No\? Get out of the water then! Move!

Pontus\? It is a land of bloated flies feeding off the corpses of others' conquests. Let us swat these flies! This unwashed rabble and their ignoble princes are as likely to flee as fight. Make ready!
The Egyptian sands will consume them…
The Egyptian sands will consume them…
The Egyptian sands will consume them…
The Egyptian sands will consume them…
How can I be of assistance\?
Ready your weapons, men. But hold until I give the order.
I cannot do what you ask of me.
Sir! I think we can hit them now!
Fight, you bastards! Fight like lions!
The way is closed to me.
And all who sail in her!
Thank the gods! Land, sweet land!
May the gods bless my wife !
Deck crew! Look to the boarding gear!
All crew! Look to our defences!
If someone doesn't put that fire out we will all die!
I will see to the needs of the people.
I will do what is needed.
The gods have shown me what is best for the people.
I will make an offering to Athena.
The people need the wisdom of the Gods.
Get out the way! Let the sailors do their work, you fool!
Haul away! Ignore the enemy! The sea will kill us all in time!
Put your backs into it! Heave!

Men of Carthage, look to your brothers, look to our strength… By Ba'al in all honour, I swear to fight to my last breath beside you! Swear this sacred oath with me! For victory will be ours, brothers, if we hold true!
You aren't making me happier, sir!
Warriors of Palmyra! See the foes standing yonder, their every breath an offence to your queen! Follow me and we shall put an end to their pathetic existence!

Our foe did not seek battle, but we have pressed the attack! Soldiers of Carthage, let your hearts be filled with courage! Our enemy know they're outmatched and would rather cower than face us! Victory is ours for the taking. Victory for Carthage!
Fire! Fire! Make life hot for the nasty buggers!
Is it me, or are there more of those bastards\?
We will probably die here, Mars willing, but we take them with us!
More the merrier. The bastards are breeding like flies.
Someone let the captain know we are going to lose at this rate!
Good work, men! Keep it up!
Strike, man, strike! Take his head off!
A sword! A sword! Give me a sword!
Leave him! He's dying, but he's dying well!
How do we fight against such hate\?
Shut up, and put your back into it! We can still get away!

The islanders over there have no real heritage. They are a mix of so many other peoples, bastards one and all. For us purebloods they are an insult and should be wiped out! Death to the Britons!
My father fought the Britons. And his father before that. They both died against these wild animals from across our seas. Now I want revenge. Take up your swords and fight with this fearless foe!
Hairy, dirty, hard as nails, cunning, bloody ugly... And that's just you lot! What about those Britons over there! They're even worse. This is going to be one big scrap! Let's go break some bones!

Defence is the best form of attack, someone once said! Probably some idiot who had never set foot on a battlefield. We go forward! And we never retreat! Especially not against the bastard Britons! Take up your arms!
Look to your brothers! And fight, Mars curse you!

Against these Britons, Death shall roam the field today. In a few hours we shall be picking through the mountains of bodies. Greet Death as your guest and lead him to this banquet from that rotting island!
Do the killing. Leave the rest to Ba'al Hammon.

Today we face the Britons. They shall fight bravely and are not afraid to send their women and children into battle. Their druids will cast magic against us and their witches are evil. The omens are not good.

Our foe make a last stand here, trapped behind these walls! We should raze this place to the ground, burn their homes and their temples, and bring this bitter war to an end! Make ready, men!

Our foe cowers here, a frightened rabble, hidden behind the walls of this, their last refuge. Today we shall show them what courage is, what true soldiers are like, when we take their walls! Prepare yourselves, men!

This day will long be remembered. We have driven these curs back, hounded them to this, their final kennel, and now stand ready to overrun their defences! Be thankful to the gods, men, to be granted such opportunity!
What do we do about the artillery\?

Thank the gods, men! Thank them for this day! We have driven our foe before us in their names, and now they are trapped, cornered behind these walls! This battle will be glorious and our triumph long celebrated!
And that, men, is how we win battles: by killing the buggers!
Clear away! Move those ropes! Clear those buckets!
Move, you miserable wretches, and haul away!
Steersman! Make sure they can see our banners!
I don't mind dying when you can see their eyes. But this!
Oh shut up, you big wendy showoff!
Jump to it! Keep the arrows coming!

I think I hit their captain!
Landsmen and soldiers! To your stations for hauling!

Those mighty walls are the last defences of Carthage. But you are the men to take them! Beyond, in that city of thieves and merchants, is enough gold to make each of you wealthy beyond your dreams! Now, go take it!

Carthage must be destroyed! It is a simple mission, perhaps too simple, but it is entirely worthy of soldiers to plunder this city, exterminate its people, and destroy all memory of the beasts! Let's be about it!
Courage, lads! They can't keep this up.

Today we attack Carthage! It is the heart of evil in their empire, the source of much cruelty in the world. When we are done, its people must be in chains, its great buildings cast down! Now, prepare yourselves!

Within those walls the wicked, greedy, gold-loving, baby-murdering Carthaginians are awaiting Roman justice! We have only to knock, enter and give them the righteous judgement of our swords! Now, soldiers of Rome, prepare yourselves!

Put your backs in to it!

I will come from the darkness.
Give them no mercy! Kill the cowards!

The enemy strength and will is broken. This pack of dogs is all they can muster! Very well! We end this! We will chain these curs or send them sreaming to the afterlife! Make ready, men!

Slipping into the shadows, my lord.
We can end this war today! All the strength our enemies can muster stands before us! They do not look so much: a rabble of boys and old men, not soldiers. Today we end this!

Our victory here will be remembered and retold forever. We will break their strength and their spirits. This is our last great task, and the glory and honour will be ours! Today we triumph over our foe!

Our victory today will put an end to the war, I hope! It will certainly put an end to their power! Never again will these fiends threaten our people! Get ready, men! Today we become the champions of our people!
I must pause awhile, my lord.
I must pause awhile, my lord.
All maybe lost! I fight on!
We face our foes one last time. This day, men, we put these monsters to the sword and end this conflict for good! The gods have favoured us above them, and by the gods' favour we will be victorious!
My work is done… for now.
My work is done… for now.
By everything you hold sacred, draw your last breath and fight, men!
We have fought and bled alongside each other, and this day will be no different! But before us is the last of our enemy, and if we break them that will be an end of it! Make ready, men!
Make sure that fire doesn't take hold!
Keep formed up! We won't be broken by artillery.
Keep at them! Do not help the wounded!
You can stop that now! They're all dead!
Excellent! They will not trouble any more farm animals!
I'll have the men calm and quiet, if you please!
Is it me, or are there more of those bastards\?
Pay those ships no thought, follow your orders, you curs!
Poseidon hole and sink them! Have they no honour\?
Get to work! Turn us about and set sail!
We're going to die at this rate!
Curses! That was my father's helmet!
I think our enemies are a little hostile at the moment.
Tell my children I died well…
Blades\? Blades! I'll give them death!
Not the face! Not the face!
Pull! Pull! Pull, you useless buggers! All is lost!
Come on! We'll live to fight another day!
Come on! We'll live to fight another day!
Not very dignified, is it\? Dying with your arse in the air.
Still, he's ready for a passing Greek!
Oh, for a bed and a warm woman!
I need a drink after that. Did you bring any wine\?
Send them to Aegir! Send them down to his realm!
The Ferryman will be busy today!
You are a right cheerful bugger, you know…
Keep your heads down, you idots!
Look to the wounded! Clear the decks!
Ah. They are shouting insults now. Oh, I'm so scared.
By Poseidon's scaly buttocks! Solid ground!
That's him. Although he'd be more use fighting for them!

I can smell all the elephant shit from here! This pisshole in the desert. Why did we ever want to come here\? I suppose we better go in and say hello. Forward men!

Behold the walls of Carthage! This great city is ours for the taking, men! And then once inside we can feast on meat and fish and mead to our hearts' content. Shall we assault these walls then\?

Brave warriors, hear my voice! Numbers have meaning only for merchants! We are warriors - being outmatched only adds to our glory! Attack!
No retreat! No surrender! Be as the wall is to the city. Deflect the enemy's blows and counter with greater! Hold your position!
We're going to need more ships!
If I am the victor this day, I will sacrifice to the gods for their favour in our defence! But we mortals must do our parts as well. Fight with honour!
Swiftly, men! Attack! Attack, before they can regroup!
By the gods, the sea is now behind us. I feel the ground - stable beneath my feet. The enemy awaits and we shall not test their patience any longer. March on! To battle!
Is this how my reign ends\?...
Egypt, forgive me… I have failed you.
Those dogs outnumber us, but each of us is worth ten of them and, should we fall, we will have cost them a great deal of blood! Spit your defiance! That is glory in death!

My people, drive away your doubts, for today there is no room for fear. Instead, fill your hearts with hate and fire! Spit your wrath upon our enemy! Be swift and deadly, deceitful yet true-hearted. Do this and the enemy will rout at once! To arms!
This is no place for us.
Do you have what it takes\?
We need to get there first!
Press on! It's not far now.
Faster, we need to move faster!
Anyone who breaks formation will be punished!

Ah, the Romans! How absolutely fitting for them to interfere with other peoples' business. These imperialist arses think they are the best in the world. I would rather throw myself off Orjen Peak, then live by their ways! The priests have spoken that we are favoured today, so may the gods decide. To battle!

By my bowels! This will be a good fight, brothers! They love their gold in the East and wear a lot of jewellery and even decorate their beasts. Yes, your queen will make you rich at the end of the battle! Whoever gets the most kills gets the better loot! Don't spare them!
I had a dream that one day a great army would rise up and destroy all barbarians. That may be some years away but, today, let us make a start!

I count myself fortunate to stand here before you. I would not wish to be anywhere else this day! For, if the gods will it, we shall break this enemy, and put them all to the spear! We will stand here until the enemy are shattered!
Take heart, for we stand ready to meet our foe. This rabble, these dogs, may bark and cry out, but we are above such petty insults. Words shall not rob us of our courage or our purpose!
The sea does as I command!
Battle group ready and awaiting orders!
We have landed ourselves a poor catch! Look at the motley haul spewed upon our shores! When we're done, the carrion can have what is left. Make ready!
I live to serve my people!
Not even a queen can do that.
This is not in my power.
I would make my ancestors proud today! I would give our people glory today! And I would have you win honour today! All this is possible, if we fight hard, and with intelligence! Now, make ready!
We're going to need a bigger fleet!
I never sheathe my sword until it has tasted blood - I expect nothing less from you either! The gods, too, look on in keen expectation! Let us show them!
To travel is to be free!
I have no intention of letting the enemy take our capital! I have every intention of making them pay for their insolence! When we are done we will toast our success with wine from their camp!
Battle group ready and awaiting orders!
I promise you victory if we hold our purpose! Give no ground! We will whip these dogs! Take the fight to them!
Hold! Do not panic! Form up and face the enemy! Move!

They think themselves warriors, but they are nothing but poets and teachers! Philosophers and deranged loons! We will teach these Greeks a lesson in the meaning of death! Your queen guides you to break their spears, their spirits and their hearts today! To arms!
A lesser commander would be disheartened today. We face a mighty foe, but the omens are excellent. You, my soldiers, are brave and true. I will do my part. And we will prevail!
Look at this angry, ugly bunch! They look like they'd stab you as soon as blink. We owe it to the ancestors to fight them. To your positions!
We have enough supplies. For now.
I give thanks to the sea for a safe journey. And now, let us be as the current: smashing aside the enemy, throwing them into confusion and despair! To arms, soldiers, to arms!
Should we cower like dogs in our camp\? Should we turn and run\? No! We will show these curs the meaning of courage. Take the battle to them - we will not die easily!
This is not in our power.
This is what we fight for, my brave warriors. We can tell our children we met Rome's might and crushed it in our hands. Yes! We are blessed by the gods.
Now, we will take this settlement, fighting through its streets with hatred for those who cower behind its walls! Show them no mercy, warriors - kill all you come across!
O sea spirits, why did you not drown these wretches when you had the chance\? I dedicate the coming victory to the gods - perhaps they will take them this time\? Make ready!
Gods be praised - the sea is at our backs! I feel the ground - sturdy and hard. The enemy lies in wait, let us not test their patience any longer. March on! To battle!
The weak will be left behind!
Take aim, fire on the shore!
Watch these Romans closely. A crafty bunch of whoresons, they may use tactics we have never seen before but we will be ready for them!
We need to hold this port!

Be thankful the creatures of the sea didn't drag them into the depths; the dogs have managed to get ashore! Drive these whelps back to their ships! Send them home, with their tails between their legs!
Behind these walls cower our enemies! You are commanded to take this place - put any resistance to the sword! Make ready!
Many of us carry scars gained in defence of our people. Today, we stand ready again. We will die for this cause. Better yet, we will help our enemies to die! Stand ready!
I see not farmers, but soldiers!
To defend your home, you will have to come with us.
They are only Romans we face. We must match their stupidity with resolve, their stubbornness with courage! I promise victory if we do! Break these fools and send them back to Rome!
Here we stand! We will guard this place and our people to the last! Gods, grant us the strength to throw back our enemies! Soldiers, today we are the shield of our people - we must not shatter!
We may be outmatched here, but the gods are on our side this day, not theirs! They are the sweepings of the farmyard - dust and chaff to the last! Make ready for battle!
Greeks are no kind of enemy - an effete bunch, clinging to their notions of democracy like a shield. Well, a shield can be broken if you strike hard enough!
They think their numbers bring advantage, but their army is a lumbering beast, slow and easy to outwit. Today, we are the hunter - we will wear them down!
Our prayers have been answered. The day of battle has finally come. We shall not dishonour the gods by failing them! With sword, spear and bow, we shall bring down the enemy! Make ready!
I stand with you today, confident of victory! The gods will bless our efforts, and crown them. When we win, we feast, as their baggage is well stocked with vittles!
I've not led you here to die.
Gather around me! In your mighty hands you carry my honour! Fulfil your duty - do not let the enemy sully it! Do this and victory will come.
Let us meet these stubborn Romans on our terms! Let us crush their dreams of conquest and expansion, and send them scurrying back to Rome. For Victory! Victory for the divine and magnificent Pharaoh!
The treacherous vultures are upon us! Rally to me! Stand fast, we shall prevail!
I dislike fighting Romans - they have a stubborn sense of duty and do not go easily to their deaths! Well, what can't be cured must be endured! Make ready!
Take aim, fire on the shore!
The patient hunter gets the prey.
A good place for an ambush.
You are no use to me dead!
Romans make slippery allies and dogged enemies. If you give them a foot they'll take a perch! Yet it is merely their nature, as it is ours to kill them! Let's go!
Warriors! See the foe over there\? Their every breath offends me! Follow my lead; we shall put an end to their pathetic existence!
There they are, a herd of gazelles blind to the approaching lion. Attack! Attack them now!
Plunder as you will! Burn the rest!
Is there anything more amusing than an army of easterners\? Do they not realise how ridiculous they look\? Are they here to fight or dance\?
I had a dream that one day a great army of ours would rise up and destroy all the barbarians. That may be in years to come but today we shall start by sweeping away this lot.
Out there, waiting like cowardly dogs, are an enemy keen to plunder our capital! By my honoured blood and ancestors, I will not give them the satisfaction! We will bar the way! Make ready!
Burn or steal, but take it from them!
Do with them as you please.
Merciful gods, you have carried us to these shores and in return we pledge victory! In the name of your blessed Pharaoh, put these dogs to the sword!
I dislike fighting Romans - they have a stubborn sense of duty and do not go easily to their deaths! Well, what can't be cured must be endured! Make ready!
Grant us the strength to beat Rome! Let us meet their arrogance with honest courage! Let us claim victory for our noble people! To arms!
Your mighty Pharaoh, the Sword of Two Lands, and all Egypt, is with you! We must not shame our land by fleeing before this inbred rabble! No, we stand! And we must triumph!
We have a plan! They stand no chance.
Make haste! Look to the enemy! Form up to face them!
Is there anything more amusing than an army of easterners\? Do they not realise how ridiculous they look\? Are they here to dance or fight!
Let them cower before our might!
For the glory of our people!
Take aim, fire on the shore!
Today we will fight as our forefathers did: against dreadful odds! And, like them, we will triumph and add further glory to the name of our people! The hour approaches! Make ready!
We are up against Rome, in all her glory, pomp and pretty costumes! They have trained for weeks to fight us. Their masters pay them money and yet it's our privilege to kill them for nothing!
Attack! Attack! We shall feast well after this!
Let us spear these fish as they flounder! We shall drive them back to their ships! Do not let invaders offend your queen!
For long years, these walls have stood, proud and defiant! Today is not the day they will fall! We will not be crushed by this enemy's might. Today, we hold! And win!
Hear me, sons of Egypt! Victory will be ours! Your Pharaoh, who shelters and feeds all, will vanquish that rabble! Give no ground to these wretched whelps! In the name of Isis, attack!
You will NOT throw your lives away!
Ambush! Don't panic! They're coming for us!
This is not how it ends!
Proud peacocks and unwashed slaves man the army arrayed before us! They are no match for us! Each of you is worth ten of them, and they shall know it this day! To arms!
Their walls may be high, but nowhere is impregnable! We will scale them - any who resist shall know death or servitude.
We take this settlement for the tribe!
May the gods grant us the strength to hold these walls and throw back the enemy! Defend this place in the people's name! There is no room for cowardice here - we stand, and hold this place!
That course isn't open to us!
Let them cower before our strength!
No ordinary man can know the future - that is for the gods to know! But we can win in battle, as we have many times before! Follow my orders! Make ready!
By Sarapis and all the gods! I pray for a worthy foe, not these savage dogs! What honour is there in defeating such filth\? Let's make this swift. Their manner offends your queen! Engage!
Our foe may outnumber us but, if the gods will it, we can still triumph today. If not, at least our hearts will be filled with courage and Anubis will find us worthy!
The weak may as well be dead!
Today is a good day to die!
Our ships have reached their destination.

Sons of Egypt, would you dishonour your  glorious Pharaoh, whose breath perfumes the heavens\? Would you allow our lands to fall into ruin\? We stand before destruction and enslavement! For your queen!
We can rest when we arrive.
There they are, a herd of sheep blind to the approaching wolves. Attack! Attack them now!
Greeks are no kind of enemy - an effete bunch, clinging their notions of democracy like a shield. Well, a shield can be broken if you strike hard enough!
Let us meet the imbecile Romans on our own terms! Let us crush their dreams of conquest and expansion! I will not eat or sleep - send them scurrying back to Rome. For victory!
They mean to march upon our capital and overthrow us! They mean to cast down our gods and enslave our children! This, we cannot allow! Hold these walls to the last breath! Make ready!
It seems I have spent my life fighting. I pity this enemy for they do not know who they face. My warriors, know that I am with you. Onwards!
They have much to answer for!
I wish I could serve up a nobler enemy but this lot will have to do. Be prepared, get angry and enjoy yourselves. There's nowhere to run so do not let them in!
Anyone who breaks formation will be punished!
At the end of our road.
When we are done here today, the survivors will shudder when they hear our name! The few who live will suffer afresh the horrors each day. Now, to the walls!
We will go ashore and take battle to these dogs! We will give no ground, but drive the curs before us! Drive them inland - put them to flight!
Take aim, fire on the shore!
